    ("v90_conical_defect_chain", "SEAM-HORIZON programme: FS factor 4pi DERIVED not imported [I] - smoothed-cone Gauss-Bonnet (spherical-cap regularisation, tangency alpha=cos theta0): Int K = 2pi(1-alpha) EXACTLY and smoothing-independent (topological; GB closure with Int k_g=2pi alpha, chi=1); codim-2 lift Int sqrt(g)R -> 4pi(1-alpha)A; replica S=-d_alpha[logZ-alpha logZ(1)] => S=4pi k A with the smooth part dropping out (the Fursaev-Solodukhin relation, previously imported in v67, now machine-derived); k_red=c3/2 (v73) => S=2pi c3 A and S=A/4 forces c3=1/(8pi) uniquely (sympy-solved). RESIDUAL ISOLATED: only 'seam determinant => EH form k_red Int R' (SEAM.THEOREM.01) remains open [A]; no Bekenstein-Hawking import anywhere in the chain (ledger SEAM.AREACOEFF.03)"),
    ("v91_spine_tetrahedron", "SPINE TETRAHEDRON (compiler microkernel, review 2026-06-10): T={2,3,4,5}={|Z2|,N_fam,|mu4|,g_car}={e3(a),p0(a),e1(a),e2(a)} - the tetrahedron IS the anchor plus its zeroth moment [I]; edges {6,8,10,12,15,20}, faces {24,30,40,60}, volume 120=|R+(E8)|=5!=sum E8 exponents [I]; graph reading |R(E8)|=240=|mu4|*|E(K4)|*|E(K5)| with E(K4)=p2, E(K5)=p3 + NEGATIVE CONTROL: breaks at K6 (15!=p4=18) [I]; dual cuts all=120 flagged as TAUTOLOGY (presentation raster, not evidence); honest SUB-grammar: 7,16,41,48,240,248 are NOT subset products (complements, does not replace, the admissibility filter); chi_T=t^4-14t^3+71t^2-154t+120 with coefficients=(nodes,edges,faces,volume), 14=dim G2, spine symmetric about 7/2 (chi(0)=chi(7)=120, chi(1)=chi(6)=24, scalaron 7=2+5=3+4) typed AUDIT not load-bearing"),
    ("v92_glue_uniqueness", "GLUE UNIQUENESS (Gate A loses another degree of freedom) [I]/[L]: the carrier extension tower is COMPLETELY classified by exhaustive enumeration of the discriminant form (Z4xZ4, q=(5x^2+3y^2)/8, reproducing the level-1 sector weights): of all 15 subgroups exactly {1, Z2, Z4, Z4} are isotropic; the TWO Lagrangian glues <(1,1)>, <(1,3)> each give det 16/16=1 (=> E8, unique by Minkowski-Siegel v83) and are swapped by either single spinor conjugation while fixed by the simultaneous one => the mu_4 glue is UNIQUE UP TO THE SHEET Z2 (two chiralities; = the two E8-extension modular invariants of v87); the unique halfway extension {(0,0),(2,2)} has H_perp/H = Z2xZ2 with q={0,0,0,1/2} = the D8 discriminant form => SO(16)_1 is the ONLY intermediate of the tower (excluded by holomorphy, mu=4). Tower: carrier(16) -> SO(16)_1(4) -> E8_1(1, sheet pair), NOTHING else. Gate A reduces to the bare index statement; WHICH extension carries no freedom (ledger GATE.METRIC.07)"),
    ("v93_koide_relaxation_toy", "KOIDE RELAXATION TOY (next.txt P2 narrowed): BASIN LEMMA [I] - physical Q in [1/3,1] maps to q=N_fam*Q in [1,3]: attractor q=2 inside, repeller q=5 outside, EVERY physical configuration is in the attractor basin (no fine-tuning); EXACT RATE [I] - cross-ratio contracts by exactly (2/3)^6 per step along the physical trajectory (Moebius linearity, 1e-30); SOURCE [I]: Q_src=0.6644638161 from the exact ladder sits at rho_src=-0.0021980 = -phi0/24 to 0.8% (the v25 conjecture in attractor coordinates: ONE SEED QUANTUM phi0/24 before the branch point, 24=|W(A3)|); POLE [N]: PDG pole masses give Q_pole=0.6666644634 (branch point hit to 3.3e-6). HONEST NEGATIVES: flow time source->pole t=2.838 F-steps is NOT an integer => literal discrete iteration pole=F^n(source) EXCLUDED, the missing P2 object is a CONTINUOUS-time generator; and rho_src vs -phi0/24 mismatch 0.79% >> ladder precision => 'exactly phi0/24' stays [P]. P2 narrowed, not closed (ledger FR.KOIDE.05)"),
    ("v94_sheet_diamond", "SHEET DIAMOND & WINDING LINE (review 2026-06-11, validated subset) [I]: all four flavor operators are distinguished points of ONE surface M(s,t)=R+Q diag(s,t,t) - R=M(0,0), K=M(1,-1), L=M(2,0), F=M(1,1) - with global invariants det M=3st^2+9st+6s+t^2+5t+8 and det B_M=6st+12s+3t^2+15t+16; the mass pencil K+xQ is the cut (1+x,x-1) on which det B factorises (v81 master cover); BUILT-IN NEGATIVE CONTROLS: diagonal cut disc=153 non-square (same as v85's R-direction), R->L cut linear. WINDING LINE: det B_{R_s}=2 det R_s for ALL s (= 8+2s, 16+4s); triple lock tr=15/det=20/coxlift=30 each give s=6. COFACTOR SEAM NORMAL n=(5,-9,6)=common adjugate row of R,L; n.1=2=|Z2| (per-winding det increment); n^T R=(8,0,0), n^T L=(20,0,0) -> only generation 1 is an open torsion channel. REALITY CORRECTED: threshold s*~2.825 (disc sign change in (2,3)) NOT 6 - reality does not select the winding value; at s=6 disc=39200=2(10*14)^2 real positive. F-corner audit (det 32, chi=(lam-2)(lam^2-13lam+16), sum B_F=196=14^2). RIGHT-PLUECKER CANONICALISATION: ||Pi_L(K)||_1=11 AND ||Pi_R(K)||_1=26 -> both quark-ratio integers in the SAME operator K (c_t/c_b=N_fam/||Pi_R(K)||_1; Pl(L)_13=26, 2Delta_Q=26 corollaries); Pi_R(L)=10(2,3,1) sum 60. FIREWALL REJECTED: 'all small rationals = adjacent spine quotients' is FALSE (16/7, 7/6, 5/6, 8/7 load-bearing counterexamples) - v74 ladder stays observation, not filter (ledger FLAV.DIAMOND.01)"),
    ("v95_centered_diamond", "CENTERED FLAVOR DIAMOND (third review round 2026-06-11) [I]: the sheet diamond is a CENTERED CROSS - C:=M(1,0)=(R+L)/2=(K+F)/2, U:=Q diag(1,0,0)=N_fam*1e1^T (winding axis, rank 1, Spec {3,0,0}), V:=Q diag(0,1,1) (sheet axis, rank 2) with Q=U+V and R=C-U, L=C+U, K=C-V, F=C+V: five objects collapse to three; the v94 winding line IS the U-axis (L=R+2U). Sheet axis carries the cusp class: Spec(V)={0,1,2}=N_fam*{0,1/3,2/3} (v69/v72 cross-link). Center invariants: tr C=12, det C=14, SNF=(1,1,14), sum C=31=2^g_car-1=1+h_vee(E8) (= the IR gap-bound numerator 31/(8pi^2), v63/v76), det B_C=28, Pi_L(C)=(0,14,14), Pi_R(C)=7(2,3,1) - same ray as Pi_R(L)=10(2,3,1) (scalaron-7 vs decuple-10); det C=14 = constant term of chi_[K,Q]=t^3+5t+14 (v80) = sqrt(sum B_F) (v94). AUDIT TYPING: the 'G2 center' reading (14=dim G2) is a Lie-dimension match, recorded NOT promoted; load-bearing = the exact normal form + integer invariants (ledger FLAV.DIAMOND.02)"),
    ("v96_branch_kernel_selection", "BRANCH-KERNEL SELECTION (next.txt P1 unblocked) [I]/[L]: at each branch point of the anchor-block cover (v81/v85) B is RANK 1 with canonical INTEGER kernels - Koide -2/3: right kernel w=11*1-9a=(2,2,-7), left v=7*1-5a=(2,2,-3); carrier -5/3: right kernel = the democratic vector 1 itself, left v=8*1-7a=(1,1,-6). COLLAPSE LEMMA [L]: rank-1 forces P(x0).w perp span{1,a} => proportional to the antisymmetric direction (-1,1,0) of the anchor's two equal slots, on BOTH sides: sector side (up=-down, LEPTON PAIRING=0 - leptons sit ON the ramification, Koide is leptonic) and generation side (gen1=-gen2, gen3=0). SECTOR ZERO LADDER [I]: lepton pairings ARE the two det-B factors (zeros = the branch points -2/3,-5/3); up zeros = -3/2=-N_fam/|Z2| doubly (the v85 GL(2) rung - the whole up-row of P(-3/2) IS the odd direction); down zeros = 0 (=K itself) and -9/5=-N_fam^2/g_car. ORIENTATION: deck translation flips (up,down)=(+,-)->(-,+), magnitude ratio 10=A_Lambda; convention-free: f_up*f_down<0 at both points. CONTROLS: anchor (2,1,1) moves the collapse to (0,1,-1) (mechanism follows the anchor); (1,2,1) disc 40 non-split, no rational kernels (v82 trichotomy). => the sector->sheet map is DEFINED by the cover's own kernels; identification with the v92 chirality swap = the remaining [P] (v97)"),
    ("v97_sheet_conjugation_bridge", "SHEET-CONJUGATION BRIDGE (P1 -> ONE [P] residual) [I]/[L]: the family-side conjugation (cusp negation 0 fixed, 1/3<->2/3 on the Q_+ eigenspaces e1=(0,0,1), e2=(0,1,2), e3=(1,0,0), v69) has a UNIQUE anchor-compatible generation-space realisation: T.1=1 and T.a=a BOTH force scale s=1 => integer involution T_A=[[0,1,0],[1,0,0],[2,-2,1]], det=-1; the two alternative pairings are REJECTED (T.a=a unsolvable). ANCHOR = CONJUGATION-SYMMETRIC VECTOR [I]: a=e2+e3, 1=a-e1, odd line=e2-e3=(-1,1,2). ONE DECK ACTION [I]: T_A = -1 on R^3/span{1,a}, exactly like sigma_12; the v96 collapse direction (-1,1,0) is odd for both - the cover cannot distinguish them. PARITY [I]: det T_A=-1=single conjugation (=v92 glue swap), det Sigma=+1=simultaneous (glue-fixing). D4 CLOSURE [L]: <T_A,Sigma> has order 8, G=T_A*Sigma order 4, char (t+1)(t^2+1) = the v69 D4 and the v70 mu4 char poly. SHEET-INDEX LEMMA [I]: G and R_rot are rationally but NOT GL(3,Z)-conjugate - det S = 2*s8*(s6^2+(s7+2s8)^2) always EVEN, minimal |det|=2=|Z2| (one sheet doubling between generation mu4 and homology mu4; Q det=N_fam does NOT intertwine - independent bridge). REMAINING [P]: the single lattice dictionary 'Q_+ grading = A3 discriminant grading' (then T_A IS the v92 A3-side conjugation)"),
    ("v98_discriminant_dictionary", "DISCRIMINANT DICTIONARY DERIVED (P1 closed modulo GATE.QGEO) [I]/[L]: the generation space carries an INTEGER mu4 - G=T_A*Sigma acts on the cusp basis as G e1=-e1, G e3=e2, G e2=-e3 (= the v69 B1+E decomposition realised integrally; G^4=I, char (t+1)(t^2+1)); the cusp-0 eigenvector IS the unique self-conjugate Z4-class-2 line and the swapped cusp pair {1/3,2/3} IS the conjugate class pair {1,3} - the v97 dictionary 'Q_+ grading = A3 discriminant grading' is DERIVED, not assumed. T_A G T_A^-1 = G^-1 (discriminant conjugation k->-k); q_A3(1)=q_A3(3)=3/8 equal on the swapped pair, q_A3(2)=1/2 fixed; A3-side negation swaps the two Lagrangian glues (v92 re-derived). The two D4 reflection classes separate the physics: T_A e1=+e1, det=-1 (glue-SWAPPING) vs Sigma e1=-e1, det=+1 (glue-FIXING); Sigma=T_A G. AUDIT: G a = e2-e3. STATUS: P1 carries NO separate [P] any more - the residual coincides with the already-open GATE.QGEO realisation step (one gate, not two); conditional on that typing the sheet selection is CLOSED (ledger FLAV.SHEET.03)"),
    ("v99_koide_flow_time", "KOIDE FLOW TIME (P2 TODO executed; corrects the ROBUSTNESS of one v93 negative, not its arithmetic): [I] CANONICAL GENERATOR - the v82 flow is generated by dq/dt = (Delta/N_fam)(q-2)(q-5) = (Delta/N_fam) det B(q) with Delta=6log(3/2) the gap; the time-1 map IS the v82 Moebius F (machine-checked, e^-Delta=(2/3)^6 exact) => the missing P2 object is precisely a QFT mechanism producing 'gap x anchor-block quadric'. [N] DATA-FRAGILITY: rho_pole=-2.2e-6 makes t hypersensitive to m_tau (PDG +-0.09 MeV): t(-1sig)=2.35, t(central)=2.84, Q crosses 2/3 at +0.43 sigma where t->infinity => within +0.5 sigma t passes EVERY integer >=3 - v93's exclusion of pole=F^n(source) holds only at the central value, NOT robust. [P] CONDITIONAL steps (registry untouched): n=2 EXCLUDED (-2.9 sigma) [N]; n=3=N_fam steps predicts m_tau=1776.9427 MeV (+0.14 sigma, source-variant stable to 0.0002 MeV); n=4 1776.9667, exact branch 1776.9690 - not separable now, kill criterion sigma(m_tau)~0.01 MeV (Belle II). [I/N] LOOK-ELSEWHERE FIREWALL: the scale reading ln(M_scal/m_tau)/ln(W) is destroyed by negative controls (W=46080,40320,51840 all <0.1 sigma) - rejected, recorded so it is not re-fished (ledger FR.KOIDE.06)"),
    ("v100_numerology_null_mc", "NUMEROLOGY NULL TEST (look-elsewhere corrected, executes the legacy 'numerology grammar test' TODO) [N], Python-only: (A) EXACT CENSUS - for each of the 13 scored frozen-registry observables the FULL declared grammar class (one-term (p/q) phi^a lam^c (1+lam)^d pi^b e^(u/w) with p,q<=130, two-term sums with coeffs<=12; provably contains every TFPT formula it scores) is counted against conservative data windows (max of achieved deviation, documented sigma, quote resolution, 5% quark scheme spread): joint formula-fishing probability prod p_i = 1e-25.8, robust to budget/window variation (<2 dex shift for coeff bound 80..200, window 5x..20x); (B) MC: 2x200k deterministic pseudo-theories (random dials at fixed phi0 / random seed phi*) reach at most 5/13 resp. 4/13 hits vs TFPT 13/13; (C) POWER controls: perturbing phi0 by 1%/10%/30% collapses TFPT's own scorecard to 9/6/4, shuffling data<->formula to mean 1.2; (D) ALPHA CLASS: all 94500 complexity-matched F_U1 variants root-solved, exactly ONE (the TFPT instance r1=2, r2=4/5, M=41, e^-2a, power -5/4) lands in the 4e-8 CODATA window => p_alpha<=1.1e-5. HEADLINE: P(random complexity-matched theory reproduces the scorecard incl. alpha) <= 1e-30.7 (~102 bits), CONDITIONAL on the declared grammar - a null-model rejection, not 'certainty'; complementary to the v84 freeze (v84 = no future look-elsewhere, v100 = retrospective look-elsewhere quantified)"),
    ("v101_horizon_anchor", "THE MAXIMAL BLACK HOLE IS THE ANCHOR (carrier-in-the-bulk surface; SdS in seam units) [I] + [P] reading: (1) NARIAI = ANCHOR - the horizon cubic at M_N = 1/(N_fam sqrt(L)) is t^3-3t+2 = (t-1)^2(t+2), roots (1,1,-2) = the TRACELESS PROJECTION of the anchor a=(1,1,2) (a-(p1/3)1 = -(1,1,-2)/3; coefficients (-3,2)=(-N_fam,|Z2|); cf chi_a=(t-1)^2(t-2), v53). (2) THE KOIDE 2/3 IS THE NARIAI ENTROPY BOUND: S/horizon = S_dS/N_fam, total = (|Z2|/N_fam) S_dS = 2/3 S_dS, deficit S_dS/3; interpolation S_tot/S_dS = (x^2+1)/(x^2+x+1) (denominator = Phi_3, the N_fam cyclotomic), monotone, min at the merge. (3) THREE-SHEET CONSERVATION: pi sum r_i^2 = 2 S_dS = |Z2| S_dS for every M. (4) Q_geom = sum r^2/(sum|r|)^2 ranges [3/8,1/2] = the two nonzero SU(4)_1 weights (pure dS -> 1/2 = delta v51; Nariai -> 3/8 = p2(a)/e1(a)^2). (5) MASS-LINE DOUBLE COVER: disc proportional to (1-3m)(1+3m), branch m = +-1/N_fam, separation 2/3; deck = horizon swap (gravitational twin of the sheet Z2). (6) TEMPERATURE LEMMA: |kappa_b/kappa_c| = (2x+1)/(x(x+2)) > 1 => evaporation flows AWAY from the merge: anchor point = REPELLER, democratic endpoint = attractor (same orientation as the flavor flow v82) [audit]. (7) SEAM-UNIT MECHANICS: dM = c3 kappa dA; Smarr M = 2 c3 kappa A; Bekenstein S <= ER/(4c3); P_H = c3/(1920 M^2) (|W(D5)|, v8/v57); lifetime 5120 pi M^3 = 128 g_car M^3/c3 (128 = 2^7 = dS prefactor, 7 = scalaron); Kerr A_ext = M^2/c3, ratio 1/2 = 1/|Z2|, S_ext = M^2/(4c3); area quantum 4 ln3 = ln(N_fam^4) = ln(disc of the flavor cover) [P as v57]. Six independent landings, zero free parameters; carrier-in-bulk reading [P], structure surface not measurement surface (ledger HOR.NARIAI.01)"),
    ("v102_seam_orientation", "ONE ORIENTATION: THE ANCHOR IS THE STATIONARY REPELLER IN BOTH SECTORS [I] + [P] reading: FLAVOR - the canonical flow dq/dt=(Delta/N_fam)(q-2)(q-5) (v99) is the GRADIENT flow of the cubic V(q)=-(Delta/N_fam)(q^3/3-7q^2/2+10q) whose critical points are exactly the two branch points, with curvatures V''(Koide)=+Delta (attractor), V''(carrier)=-Delta (repeller) - the stationary curvatures ARE the transfer gap; inflection at q=7/2=scalaron/2=branch-trace/2; Lyapunov rate d(-ln rho)/dt = Delta exactly and constantly. GRAVITY - d(S_tot/S_dS)/dx = (x-1)(x+1)/Phi_3(x)^2: the Nariai/anchor point is the UNIQUE physical stationary point of the entropy functional, with curvature 2/9 = |Z2|/N_fam^2 = (2/3)(1/3) (product of the two Nariai entropy fractions); temperature lemma (v101) => dx/dt<0, dS/dx<0 on (0,1) => entropy ASCENT away from the anchor toward the democratic endpoint. ORIENTATION THEOREM [I]: both sectors flow away from an anchor-stationary configuration with grammar-constant curvatures. HONEST: flavor attractor = branch point vs gravity attractor = smooth endpoint; flavor functional = potential of a [P] relaxation vs gravity = BH entropy; 'one variational principle of the seam' stays a reading [P]; no gate touched (ledger HOR.ORIENT.01)"),
    ("v103_trisection_normal_form", "TRISECTION NORMAL FORM (answers the v102 curvature-matching question at the geometric level) [I]: the SdS horizon cubic is uniformized by ANGLE TRISECTION - r = 2cos(theta) gives r^3-3r = 2cos(3theta) exactly, so the cubic <=> cos(3theta) = -3m; in the centered angle psi (cos phi = -3m, psi = phi-pi): m = cos(psi)/N_fam, Nariai psi=0, pure dS psi=pi/2, deck involution psi->-psi (= the v101 x->1/x), Z3 trisection rotation = the triality deck (v72). NORMAL FORM: sigma(psi) = S_tot/S_dS = 4/3 - (2/3)cos(2psi/3) - mean |mu4|/N_fam, amplitude |Z2|/N_fam, frequency |Z2|/N_fam: ONE cosine, every constant a glue atom. CANONICAL CURVATURE at the anchor: sigma''(0) = 8/27 = (2/3)^3 = (|Z2|/N_fam)^N_fam - the Koide constant to the family power. INVARIANT BASE SLOPE: dsigma/dm|_Nariai = -8/9 = -rank(E8)/N_fam^2 (cross-checked in both coordinates; generally -(4/3)sin(2psi/3)/sin(psi)); dimensionful dS_tot/dM|_N = -r_N/(N_fam c3). BRIDGE: flavor multiplier (2/3)^{2N_fam} (a rate) vs gravity curvature (2/3)^{N_fam}: same base 2/3, exponent ratio |Z2|; full identification needs the gravity-side CLOCK (near-Nariai evaporation generator) - same missing-object class as P2's transfer generator: one clock, two known geometries [P] (ledger HOR.TRISECT.01)"),
    ("v104_nariai_clock", "THE CLASSICAL NARIAI CLOCK IS THE ANCHOR (third appearance) + the honest (2/3)-test [I] + one external-reference typing: STATIC PIN - phi(rho)=rho solves d/drho[(1-L rho^2)phi'] = -2L phi EXACTLY on the dS2 static patch, so the S^2-radius modulus mass is pinned m^2 = -2L = -|Z2|L by the exact SdS family itself (Laplace-type linearization = standard GR, Ginsparg-Perry 1983 / Bousso-Hawking 1997, external); horizon split linear in the canonical angle with coefficient 1/sqrt(N_fam); GINSPARG-PERRY TOWER (l(l+1)-2)L: exactly ONE negative mode -|Z2|L (l=0), zero modes at l=1; THE CLOCK in Hubble units: chi_clock(lambda) = lambda^2+lambda-2 = (lambda-1)(lambda+2) = THE ANCHOR QUADRATIC, eigenvalues {1,-2} = the distinct anchor roots; the Nariai cubic factors as (t-1) x chi_clock(t) - the anchor appears as configuration roots (v101), curvature base (v103) AND clock spectrum; entropy-deviation rate d/dt log(sigma-2/3) = 2H = |Z2| x Hubble exactly. HONEST (2/3)-TEST NEGATIVE for the classical clock: eigenvalues are integers, not (2/3)-powers - the 2/3-powers stay in the functional; the one-loop conversion curvature->rate (quantum (anti-)evaporation) remains external [P]; the flavor-rate bridge is NOT closed (ledger HOR.CLOCK.01)"),
    ("v105_residual_inventory", "THE RESIDUAL INVENTORY (one constant, one anchor, one clock to find, the COMPLETE gap list) [I] inventory + [I] relocation + typing contract: (A) ONE-CONSTANT INVENTORY - 2/3 = |Z2|/N_fam appears EXACTLY in seven independent places (flavor: Koide branch point, transfer-gap base (2/3)^6, attractor inside the basin [1/3,1]; gravity: Nariai entropy bound, SdS branch separation, canonical amplitude+frequency, canonical curvature base (2/3)^N_fam); ANCHOR TRIPTYCH: chi_a=(t-1)^2(t-2) configuration + Nariai (t-1)^2(t+2) = traceless anchor + clock (lam-1)(lam+2), Nariai = (t-1) x clock, a = e2+e3. (B) RELOCATION THEOREM [I]: the cosmological one-loop clock correction eps = (c/24pi) Lambda/Mbar^2 = 7.6e-122 (c=8 seam charge, frozen rho_L) is deficient by 121.5 ORDERS vs the needed O(1) gap - and the deficit IS the Lambda hierarchy 2 alpha^-1/ln10 = 119.0 (+2.5 prefactors, the v60 split) => the seam clock must live at the SEAM scale where the only gapped generator is the established transfer operator; final bridge form: ONE [P] identification 'transfer operator = seam Nariai clock'. (C) RESIDUAL TABLE machine-pinned: EXACTLY FIVE structural objects remain (R1 seam quantum clock [P]; R2 holomorphy+c8 [P]/[A]; R3 seam-det=>EH [A]; R4 H2 dictionary [A]/[P]; R5 Q-realisation carrying P1 [P]) + the two irreducibles (one scale v_geo, pi) + frozen data surfaces; a sixth structural gap would FAIL this script (ledger SYNTH.INVENTORY.01)"),
    ("v106_review_validation", "EXTERNAL-REVIEW VALIDATION (2026-06-11; v79-style identities + disciplined typing) [I]: (1) SEED NORMAL FORM - phi0 = (|mu4|/N_fam) c3 + Omega_adm c3^|mu4| EXACTLY (linear seam term + topological 4th-order correction; 4/3 = |mu4|/N_fam, 48 = Omega_adm = N_fam dim S+, exponent 4 = |mu4|). (2) anchor power-sum ladder recheck p_n = 2+2^n -> (3,4,6,10), 240, 8, 248. (3) HYPERCHARGE SECOND MOMENT computed from the explicit charge table: Tr X = 0, Tr X^2 = 120 = 5! (X = 6Y, 16 states). (4) FACTORIAL SPINE (named lemma): 5! = 120 = |R+(E8)| = sum E8 exponents = Tr X^2; 240 = 2x120; 1920 = 2^4 x 5! = |W(D5)| - one moment, four projections (hypercharge, roots, Weyl, Hawking fingerprint). (5) DEGREE-2 INVENTORY: Pascal K=2 closure UNIQUE at g=5 (scan 1..40); glue norms 5/4+3/4 = 2 = root norm; c3 = (1/2) x 1/(4pi); pair sector C(5,2) = 10; second moments; codim-2 seam. NAMED HYPOTHESIS [P] recorded, not claimed: QUADRATIC BOUNDARY LOCALITY (seam supports only bilinear data => K=2 forced) - if proven, the Pascal selection (red-team B residual) upgrades [A]/[P] -> [L]: locality => K=2 => g=5 => 16 => D5 => E8. (6) AUDIT: 240 = 16x15 transition reading exact but non-unique (16x5x3 established), no bijection exhibited - not promoted. NOTES: reality compiler {a, pi, v_geo} = restatement of v23+v78; grammar-freeze already implemented (v84+v100) (ledger ARCH.QUAD.01)"),
    ("v107_quantum_clock_target", "QUANTUM-CLOCK TARGET MADE QUANTITATIVE (R1 programme, first computation) [I] + [P]: MULTI-MODE CLASSICAL CLOCK - Ginsparg-Perry tower per-l equations lambda^2+lambda+(l(l+1)-2)=0: l=0 (lambda-1)(lambda+2) anchor pair, l=1 lambda(lambda+1) zero modes, l>=2 complex with Re=-1/2=-delta (audit). NEW EXACT CROSS-LINK: the classical decay set (l=0,1) = {0,-1,-2} = -Spec(V) = -N_fam x cusp weights - THE CLASSICAL CLOCK DECAYS ON THE TRANSFER OPERATOR'S OWN GRADING (v69/v95): structural support for 'transfer = seam Nariai clock'. THE QUANTUM TARGET EXACTLY: transfer rates {0, Delta, 6ln3} are NOT weight-linear - rate(2)/rate(1) = log_{3/2}(3) = 1 + log_{3/2}(2) = 2.7095 (not 2); EXACT identity (1/3)^6 = ((2/3)^6)^{log_{3/2}3}; required bend log_{9/4}(3) = 1.35476 per weight step = the complete job description of the missing object. COUPLING LANDSCAPE: kappa = (c/24pi)(Lambda/Mbar^2), c=8: cosmological 7.6e-122 (v105, hopeless) vs seam Lambda~Mbar^2 -> kappa = 1/(3pi) = 0.106 - the only viable regime, borderline non-perturbative => one-loop linear response cannot fix the bend; O(1) resummation or exact seam construction required. R1 sharpened from 'find a clock' to 'produce the bend log_{3/2}3 on the cusp ladder at coupling O(1/3pi)'; nothing fitted, identification NOT closed (ledger HOR.CLOCK.02)"),
    ("v108_pascal_ladder", "PASCAL LADDER THEOREM (red-team Target B sharpened to ZERO slack) [I]/[L] + [P]: the closure 2^{g-1} = sum_{k<=K} C(g,k) has for every K EXACTLY ONE solution g = 2K+1 (scan K=1..6, g=1..60; structural: odd-g midpoint identity by binomial symmetry + even-g strict straddle (2^g - C(g,g/2))/2 < 2^{g-1} < +C(g,g/2) excludes all even g). EXACT EQUIVALENCE: carrier selection g=5 <=> truncation degree K=2 - the Pascal-selection residual (CAR.PASCAL.01/REDTEAM.B.01) IS the single named hypothesis Quadratic Boundary Locality (v106). NEIGHBOUR WORLDS: K=1 -> g=3, code 4, N_fam=1 (one-family world); K=2 -> g=5, 16, 3; K=3 -> g=7, 64, 9 (nine-family world); K=4 -> g=9: N_fam = 255/9 NOT integer (inconsistent). OVERDETERMINATION: among ladder worlds only K=2 satisfies the independent rank condition g+N_fam = 8 = rank E8 (v14) - two independent selections agree on the same world. THE ONE HYPOTHESIS [P] precisely stated: QBL = 'seam Calderon datum is a single 2-point kernel; the carrier code is generated by the degrees it certifies (K<=2)'; if proven from RP, the carrier choice upgrades [A]/[P] -> [L] along QBL => K=2 <=> g=5 => 16 => D5 => E8 (ledger CAR.LADDER.01)"),
    ("v109_sheet_pairing", "SHEET-PAIRING LEMMA (first exact rep-theoretic anchor for QBL; ties Target B to the sheet Z2) [I] character-exact weight-multiset combinatorics from the D5 spinor weights (+-1/2)^5 alone: (1) NO SCALAR WITHIN A SHEET - zero-weight multiplicity of S+xS+ and S-xS- is 0 (odd slot count g=5 flips the sign parity of -w => -w lies in the OTHER chirality): no invariant bilinear inside one sheet. (2) THE SCALAR LIVES ACROSS THE SHEETS - S+xS- has zero-weight multiplicity 16 = 1+5+10 (the Pascal triple) and equals EXACTLY (weight multisets) the even-form tower Lambda^0+Lambda^2+Lambda^4 (256 = 1+45+210), zero-mode grading (1,5,10) = the carrier code. (3) SHEET-DIAGONAL = ODD FORMS: (S+xS+)u(S-xS-) = 2Lambda^1+2Lambda^3+Lambda^5 exactly (512 = 20+240+252) - within-sheet pairings are odd-form-valued, never scalar. (4) THE TOWER TOPS AT Lambda^{2K}: the scalar-bearing channel ends at form degree 4 = 2K, K=2 - bilinear seam data reach exactly the Pascal-ladder degree (v108). (5) QBL READING [P]: the seam scalar kernel is necessarily a SHEET PAIRING (chirality-off-diagonal); remaining step = show the Calderon kernel supplies exactly this pairing and nothing beyond (ledger CAR.PAIR.01)"),
    ("v110_calderon_sheet", "CALDERON-SHEET SELECTION THEOREM (the v109 follow-up: which involutions certify a scalar kernel?) [I] finite-model theorem + [P] typing: SELECTION THEOREM - on H = S+ (+) S- the certified bilinear data of a Calderon involution eps (eps^2=1) are <f, eps g>; v109 singlet counts per sheet block (0,0,1,1) give: sheet-ODD eps (swaps S+<->S-) certifies EXACTLY 1+1 = 2 = |Z2| invariant scalar kernels (one per orientation), sheet-EVEN eps certifies NONE - 'scalar two-point datum exists <=> eps is sheet-odd'. THE TWO KERNELS = THE GLUE AMBIGUITY: count 2 = |Z2| = the two Lagrangian glues (v92, swapped by single conjugation) - the Calderon scalar channel carries exactly the glue ambiguity, resolved by the same sheet choice. LADDER GENERICITY (anti-overclaim control): for g = 3,5,7 within-sheet zero-weight count is 0 and cross count is 2^{g-1} - sheet-oddness forces the HALF-SPINOR RELATION K = (g-1)/2, NOT the value g=5; g-selection stays with the independent rank-8/integrality closure (v14/v108). QBL RESIDUE SPLIT [P] (recorded, not claimed): (a) INTERFACE 'the seam Calderon involution is sheet-odd' (natural: the one-sided collar / double-cover deck is the SAME |Z2| that halves c3 = 1/(2 x 4pi); exchanging cover sides is sheet-odd by construction); (b) ANALYTIC CORE 'the 2-point kernel certifies only slot-degrees <= 2' - two named parts, neither claimed (ledger CAR.PAIR.02)"),
    ("v111_quadratic_transport", "QUADRATIC-TRANSPORT THEOREM (the transport half of the QBL analytic core becomes a THEOREM) [I] exact finite theorem (integer Jordan-Wigner model, mod-p full-rank certificates valid over Q): grade seam transport by Clifford degree in the 10 field operators on the 5-slot Fock space (S = Lambda^*(C^5), S+ = 16 code states). (1) PARITY [exact block-zero]: all 10 linear words are sheet-ODD (S+ -> S-), all 45 quadratic words sheet-EVEN - code-preserving transport has even Clifford degree (same Z2 as v109/v110). (2) MINIMALITY: sheet-even words of degree <= 1 are the scalars alone (dim 1 < 256) - degree 2 is the first nontrivial code-preserving grade. (3) GENERATION: the 45 quadratics (= dim so(10) = the Lambda^2 term of the v109 tower 1+45+210) generate the WHOLE code from the vacuum at word length <= 2. (4) COMPLETENESS (Burnside realised): products of length <= 2 span the FULL End(S+) = 256 - every code operation is a word in pair transport; all higher even-degree elements (e.g. the 210 quartics) are redundant => THE TRANSPORT DEGREE IS EXACTLY 2: degree <= 1 generates nothing, degree 2 generates everything - a theorem, not a hypothesis. (5) LADDER GENERICITY (anti-overclaim): g=3 behaves identically (15 quadratics -> End = 16) - the theorem selects the DEGREE, not the rank; g-selection stays with Pascal + rank-8 (v108/v14). (6) CHANNEL READING: certified tower 256 = 1+45+210 = norm + transport generators + pair sector. (7) RESIDUE UPDATE [P]: QBL's remaining content = two interface statements - (a) seam Calderon involution sheet-odd (v110), (b') certified STATE inventory = the <= 2-slot tower (v108); nothing about transport remains hypothetical (ledger CAR.QTRANS.01)"),
    ("v112_selfcounting_channel", "SELF-COUNTING CHANNEL (the Pascal closure is an IDENTITY of the certified channel, not an extra requirement; closes the state half of the QBL core structurally) [I]: (1) CANONICAL BIJECTION - for odd g negation w -> -w maps S+ bijectively into the opposite sheet (v109 parity as a bijection), so the Cartan-neutral kernels of the certified channel S+xS- are exactly the pairs (w,-w), ONE PER CODE STATE: # neutral kernels = dim S+ = 2^{g-1} exactly (4, 16, 64 for g = 3, 5, 7) - the channel counts the code. (2) PASCAL PARTITION - the same neutral set graded by pair-degree m has sizes C(g,m), m=0..K: g=5 -> (1,5,10). (3) THE CLOSURE IS AN IDENTITY: two countings of ONE set give 2^{g-1} = sum_{m<=K} C(g,m) (symbolic, all odd g=3..13) - v108's closure condition is the channel counting itself. (4) HODGE FOLD: the code's minus-sign grading C(g,2j) = C(g, min(2j,g-2j)) with min <= K - every code sector appears at pair-degree <= K (g=5: code (1,10,5) vs channel (1,5,10), same multiset, folded). (5) LADDER GENERICITY: holds for every odd g, carries NO g-selection - selection stays with rank-8 (g+N_fam=8, v14) + integrality (v108). (6) RESIDUE RE-TYPE [P]: QBL clause (b') loses its closure burden (given the sheet-odd kernel the channel automatically holds one neutral kernel per code state at pair-degree <= K); remaining physical input = 'seam certifies through a single scalar 2-point kernel' (free c=8 seam net: Wick extends it to the whole even tower); QBL = structural consistency frame, no longer a missing selector (ledger CAR.COUNT.01)"),
    ("v113_quasifree_kernel", "ONE KERNEL IS THE WHOLE NET (QBL input merges with the R2/holomorphy premise) [I] + [P] typing: (1) MAJORANA BOOKKEEPING - c(D5)_1 = 45/9 = 5 = g_car, c(A3)_1 = 15/5 = 3 = N_fam, c(SO16)_1 = 8, c(E8)_1 = 248/31 = 8; the carrier net (D5)_1x(A3)_1 = SO(10)_1xSO(6)_1 = 10+6 = 16 FREE MAJORANA FERMIONS, c = 16/2 = 8 - the whole extension tower carrier(mu=16) -> SO(16)_1(mu=4) -> E8_1(mu=1) carries the SAME 16 fermions, only the certified glue grows (index 2x2 = 4 = |mu_4|, v89). (2) WICK/PFAFFIAN [I] exact: in the 10-Majorana model ALL 210 vacuum 4-point AND all 210 6-point functions equal the Pfaffian of the single 2-point kernel - one kernel determines all correlations. (3) THE KERNEL IS A CALDERON INVOLUTION OF RANK g: M = I+iA, A integer antisym, A^2 = -I; P = M/2 projection, rank P = 5 = g_car; eps = iA involution; at seam level (16 Majoranas) rank 8 = rank E8 => THE CENTRAL CHARGE IS THE RANK OF THE ONE KERNEL (5 carrier block, 8 seam hull). (4) ONE KERNEL <=> ONE STATE: joint annihilator kernel exactly 1-dim - the polarization fixes the vacuum uniquely. (5) PREMISE MERGE [P]: QBL's input 'single scalar 2-point kernel' = 'seam state quasi-free' = the defining property of the free-fermion net the R2 gate already posits (Gate-A (H') index-4 extension); QBL adds NO assumption beyond R2; upgrade contract: R2 closes => QBL closes [L] along free net => one kernel => sheet-odd (v110) => self-counting tower (v109/v112) => complete transport (v111) => carrier; gate typing [P]/[A] unchanged (ledger CAR.QFREE.01)"),
    ("v114_torsion_delta", "TORSION NORMAL FORM + THE DELTA = 1/2 THEOREM (executes the GATE.UWALL.05 'genericity future work'; delta = 1/2 stops being an observation) [I] symbolic + [N] census: (1) FLATNESS = mu4 TORSION [I, generic symbolic M] - prod_k U^k M U^{-k} = (MU)^4 exactly, so the Z4-family flatness constraint IS the torsion statement 'T = MU is a fourth root of unity': the mu_4 atom appears as the ORDER of the twisted cusp generator. (2) DELTA THEOREM [I, both directions]: on the involutive branch (T^2 = 1, unitary) T is a Hermitian reflection 2vv^dag-1 and the cusp trace splits EXACTLY into |v1|^2 = 1/2 + |v2| = |v3| => diag M = (0, i/2, -i/2), spec M = {1,w,w^2} AUTOMATIC (unitary + tr 0 + det 1 => lam^3 - 1) - delta = |M_22| = 1/2 exactly and constantly on the whole 2-parameter branch: the distinguished lepton transport value (v20) is a mu4-torsion identity. (3) REFLECTION LEMMA [I]: D4 reflection => diag M = (r, z, zbar), r real, Re z = -r/2; delta = 1/2 <=> r = 0 - the D4 diagonal freedom is ONE real parameter. (4) BRANCH CENSUS [N, seeded]: full D4-fixed flat cusp locus realises only tr(MU) in {1,-1}; involutive branch diagonal CONSTANT (0,1/2,1/2) to 1e-15; the {1,i,-i} branch has d1 in [0,1] - the explicit v33/v40 point sits in its d1 = 0 slice (same delta value). (5) RESIDUE [P]: does the anchor splitting O(-2)+O(-1)^2 force the d1 = 0 slice (or select the involutive branch)? - the remaining question; delta itself closed (ledger GATE.UWALL.06)"),
    ("v115_anchor_residue", "THE ANCHOR PINS THE RESIDUE (exact normal form for the U_wall flat-bundle residue; answers the v114 branch question) [I] + [N]: (1) MU4-AVERAGE LEMMA [I, symbolic] - sum_k U^k X U^{-k} = 4 diag(X): mu_4 conjugation-averaging IS the diagonal projection => exponents at infinity = 4 diag(A0) => anchor splitting O(-2)+O(-1)^2 <=> diag A0 = (2,1,1)/4 = a/|mu_4| (v33's diagonal was forced, not chosen). (2) THE (8,0,5)/144 LEMMA [I]: anchor diagonal + cusp spectrum {0,1,2}/N_fam pin sum|off|^2 = 13/144; with a13 = 0 the det = 0 condition solves UNIQUELY to (|a12|^2,|a23|^2) = (8,5)/144 - numerators (rank E8, g_car), denominator (|mu_4| N_fam)^2, total 13 = Delta_Q (the quark denominator 117 = 9x13). (3) EXACT RESIDUE NORMAL FORM [I]: A0* = [[1/2, sqrt2/6, 0],[sqrt2/6, 1/4, sqrt5/12],[0, sqrt5/12, 1/4]] has char poly lam(lam-1/3)(lam-2/3) EXACTLY. (4) A0* IS THE RH SOLUTION [N]: big-circle monodromy trivial to 1.6e-10, prod M_k = 1, unitarised |diag M~_0| = (0,1/2,1/2), tr(M~_0 U) = 1 - the v33/v40 numerical point is gauge-equivalent to this exact matrix (phases of a12, a23 = diagonal gauge). (5) ANCHOR FORCES THE d1 = 0 SLICE [N]: multi-seed RH scan over the anchor-pinned spectral manifold lands at every flat solution on the SAME gauge orbit (off-moduli (sqrt8,0,sqrt5)/12) with |diag M~_0| = (0,1/2,1/2) - v114's branch question answered: the harmonic diagonal is anchor + torsion forced, delta = 1/2 needs no selection. (6) RESIDUE [P]: a13 = 0 + gauge-orbit uniqueness numerical; promotion to [I]/[L] via Groebner on the RH constraints = the remaining U_wall point-selection step (ledger GATE.UWALL.07)"),
    ("v116_resonance_uniqueness", "RESONANCE THEOREM (the v115 [N] findings promoted to [I] - by a LINEAR computation, no Groebner needed): (1) TWISTED-AVERAGE LEMMA [I, symbolic] - at infinity the system reads dY/dw = -(1/w)(B0 + B1 w + ...)Y with B_m = sum_k i^{km} U^k A0 U^{-k}; the twisted mu_4 averages collapse: B0 = 4 diag(A0), B1 = 4 a12 E_12 + 4 conj(a13) E_31 (only the eigenvalue-ratio -i cells survive). (2) RESONANCE THEOREM [I]: anchor exponents diag(2,1,1) have resonance gap 1; the level-1 gauge equation (1 - ad R0)H1 = R1 is singular exactly on cells {(2,1),(3,1)} where B1 = (0, 4 conj(a13)); higher levels k >= 2 non-resonant; formal monodromy e^{-2 pi i diag(2,1,1)} = 1 => M_inf = 1 <=> a13 = 0: the transcendental RH condition collapses to ONE linear equation. (3) UNIQUENESS COROLLARY [I]: a13 = 0 + the (8,0,5)/144 moduli (v115) + phases = diagonal gauge (commutes with U, rotates arg a12, arg a23 freely) => THE FLAT ANCHOR LOCUS IS EXACTLY ONE GAUGE ORBIT = the exact A0* - within the mu_4-equivariant anchor class the U_wall bundle datum is ALGEBRAICALLY unique. (4) FALSIFICATION CONTROL [N]: ||M_inf - 1|| = 1.6e-10 at a13 = 0 vs 0.17/0.43 at a13 = 0.02/0.05 (sharp, ~8.5|a13|). (5) HONEST SCOPE [P]: equivariant ansatz = established D4 selector input; residue side now [I], holonomy values (harmonic diagonal) remain [N] (ledger GATE.UWALL.08)"),
    ("v117_monodromy_weyl_a3", "THE MONODROMY IS THE WEYL GROUP OF A3 (the U_wall holonomy is an EXACT 24-element representation; the harmonic diagonal becomes a theorem) [I] + [N]: (1) THE EXACT MONODROMY [I] - M0 = [[0, -(1+i)/2, (1-i)/2], [-(1+i)/2, -i/2, -1/2], [(1-i)/2, -1/2, i/2]] (entries in (1/2)Z[i]) is unitary, det 1, tr 0, char poly lam^3 - 1 (cusp class EXACT), M0^3 = 1, diag M0 = (0, -i/2, +i/2) => d1 = 0 AND delta = 1/2 are exact matrix entries - the v20 hand value, the v40/v41 observation, the v114 torsion value and the v115 anchor slice meet in ONE exact matrix. (2) TORSION/FLATNESS [I]: (M0 U)^4 = 1, tr(M0 U) = 1 (the {1,i,-i} branch, d1 = 0 slice), prod_k U^k M0 U^{-k} = 1 exactly. (3) THE GROUP IS W(A3) = S4 [I]: exact enumeration of <U, M0> gives order 24, order statistics (1,9,8,6), characters (3,-1,0,1) - uniquely S4 in standard x sign = the (twisted) reflection rep of the WEYL GROUP OF THE FAMILY LATTICE A3; U = 4-cycle (mu_4 deck), M0 = 3-cycle (family rotation), 24 = |W(A3)| = 4! - the flavor-wall monodromy realises the A3 factor of the glue D5+A3+mu4 as its Weyl group. (4) IDENTIFICATION [N]: unitarised ODE monodromy of the exact A0* system = exact M0 to 3.5e-10; invariant form H is U-invariant to 2.5e-11. (5) STATUS [P]: holonomy VALUES now [I]; only the analytic identification stays [N]; the delta thread v20 -> v40/v41 -> v114 -> v115 -> v117 is closed end to end (ledger GATE.UWALL.09)"),
    ("v118_hexagon_family_dictionary", "THE HEXAGON IS THE SIGN-TWISTED FAMILY SPECTRUM (first exact piece of the H2 dictionary; the v20 lepton coefficients are resolvent determinants of the exact W(A3) monodromy) [I]: (1) SIGN-TWIST LEMMA - (-M0) has order 6 ((-M0)^3 = -1) and spec(M0) u spec(-M0) = mu_6: the hypercharge hexagon spectrum IS the family monodromy spectrum plus its sheet twist (Z6 = Z2 x Z3 = (-1) x <M0>); v20's denominators 5/4 - cos(r pi/3) = |1 - zeta_6^r/2|^2 are the eigen-denominators of the two family resolvents (1 -+ M0/2)^{-1}. (2) CYCLOTOMIC DETERMINANT: det(1 - t M0) = 1 - t^3 = (1-t) Phi_3(t) => det(1 - M0/2) = 7/8, det(1 + M0/2) = 9/8. (3) LEPTON COEFFICIENTS = RESOLVENT DETERMINANTS: c_e = |mu_4|/(2 det-) = 16/7, c_mu = N_fam/(2 det+) = 4/3, c_tau = |mu_4| det-/N_fam = 7/6, product rule = |mu_4|/det+ = 32/9 - the lepton 7 and 9 ARE the family-resolvent determinants (x8); delta = 1/2 = |(M0)_22| supplied by the matrix itself (v117); the e/mu/tau LEG assignment stays v20's established input, nothing re-fished. (4) SHEET-EXTENDED GROUP: <U, M0, -1> has order 48 = Omega_adm = N_fam x dim S+ (the seed quartic coefficient, v106) = |S4 x Z2| (exact enumeration, audit cross-link). (5) RESIDUE [P]: the dictionary's VALUES are exact; its ADDRESS TABLE (site assignment per fermion, quark composition) remains open (ledger FLAV.H2.02)"),
    ("v119_review_validation_2", "SECOND EXTERNAL-REVIEW VALIDATION (2026-06-11b; triad + 121 audit + micro-identities) [I]: (1) ANCHOR NORMAL-FORM MICRO-IDENTITIES - Omega_adm = 2 p1 p2 = 48, 10 b1 = 1 + p1 p3 = 41, Delta_Y = e2^2 = p0^2 + 2 rank = 25, h(E8) = e3 p0 e2 = 30, rank = p0 + e2 = 8, 240 = p1 p2 p3, 248 = 240 + (p4-p3). (2) ANCHOR RATIO TRIAD (named lemma): (e3, e1, e2)/p0 = (2/3, 4/3, 5/3) = (Koide branch/sheet ratio, seed gain |mu4|/N_fam, carrier branch); the canonical flow's critical points are EXACTLY (2,5) = (e3,e2) with inflection 7/2 = (e3+e2)/2 - the recurring fractions are the three normalised anchor coefficients, not scattered numbers. (3) THE 121 AUDIT LEMMA: (1+a)^T R (1+a) = 121 = 11^2 = ||Pl(K)||_1^2 = (p3+1)^2 - the quark-ratio 11 appears a SECOND independent time as the quadratic anchor norm of the residue operator R; SENSITIVITY: orderings of h give {105,121,135}, only the canonical anchor ordering yields 121 - typed AUDIT, not load-bearing (oriented Plucker v42/v49 stays the derivation); BONUS: 1^T R 1 = 22 = 2x11 (entry sum), a^T R a = 40 = p1 p3 = 10b1 - 1. (4) FLAVOR SURFACE claim = established v94/v95 (re-verified; presentational). (5) BOOKKEEPING: mu4 projection = v115/v116, triptych = v104/v105, interior-free = v113 (all closed); anchor-first presentation recorded as editorial item (ledger ARCH.TRIAD.01)"),
    ("v120_address_table", "THE ADDRESS TABLE (the open H2 item structured: lepton words ARE the compiler atoms; every sum rule lands on an anchor atom) [I] exact arithmetic on FROZEN v18/v20 integers + [P] residue: (1) LEPTON WORDS = COMPILER ATOMS: (L_e, L_mu, L_tau) = (8, 5, 3) = (rank E8, g_car, N_fam) = (p0+e2, e2, p0), in mass order (longest word = lightest). (2) ADDRESSES = EUCLIDEAN DIVISION BY THE HEXAGON p2 = 6 = |R+(A3)|: e -> (r,w) = (2,1), mu -> (5,0), tau -> (3,0); sum r = 10 = p3 = A_Lambda; sum L = 16 = dim S+ = 2^{g-1}. (3) SHEET PARITY (v118 dictionary applied): e on the untwisted sheet (omega in spec M0), mu/tau on the twisted sheet (-omega, -1 in spec(-M0)); the anchor lepton tau sits at the unique REAL twisted eigenvalue -1 - exactly where v20's product rule replaces the resolvent. (4) QUARK SUM RULES (frozen v18 words 7,7,5,3,2,0): up-sum = 10 = p3, down-sum = 14 = p1+p3, ALL QUARKS = 24 = |W(A3)| (the monodromy group order, v117), ALL NINE FERMIONS = 40 = p1 p3 = a^T R a (v119); quark sum r = 2 p2, sum w = |Z2|; top at the vacuum site (0,0) (zero word, the ladder anchor). (5) RESIDUE [P]: five independent closures (16, 10, 14, 24, 40) constrain the address map; the per-fermion assignment remains the v18/v20 input - deriving it is the remaining H2 content; FIREWALL: all integers frozen before today's readings (ledger FLAV.H2.03)"),
    ("v121_address_pinning", "THE ADDRESS TABLE IS PINNED (R = the UNIQUE hexagon matrix with atom margins and rank-8 determinant; the per-fermion assignment carries ZERO residual information) [I] exact census theorem: (1) THE WORD TABLE IS THE RESIDUE OPERATOR - the established identity L = R + 2U (v95, U = winding axis) says the word-length table IS L[sector][generation] with rows (up; down; lepton) = ((7,3,0); (7,5,2); (8,5,3)) = the v18/v20 words verbatim; addresses = R entries + one hexagon turn for generation 1; R's first column = THE ANCHOR a = (1,1,2) (first-generation residues = anchor components). (2) THE MARGINS ARE ATOMS: row sums (4,8,10) = (e1, rank E8, p3), column sums (4,13,5) = (e1, Delta_Q, g_car), total 22 = 2x11. (3) PINNING THEOREM [exact census]: among ALL 3x3 matrices with entries in the hexagon {0..5}, exactly 17 have the atom margins and exactly ONE has det = 8 = rank E8 - and it is R (also unique with SNF (1,1,8)); det distribution over the 17 computed explicitly, all distinct, 8 occurs once. The assignment table carries zero residual information beyond atom margins + rank determinant. (4) within-sector assignment = established transport reading (longer word = lighter). (5) RESIDUE [P]: the open H2 item shrinks from 'derive 9 per-fermion integers' to 'derive the six atom margins + det = rank'; FIREWALL: R, L, words frozen in v4/v18/v20/v71 (ledger FLAV.H2.04)"),
    ("v122_margin_theorem", "THE MARGINS ARE THEOREMS (the established, frozen selectors pin R uniquely; the v121 atom margins lose their input status) [I] exact census: THREE ESTABLISHED SELECTORS, all frozen pre-v120 - (S1) D4 annihilator n = (5,-9,6) with n^T R = (8,0,0) (v94/tfpt_2, kills the (c2,c3) plane, n.a = 8); (S2) det R = 8 = rank E8 (v71 quartet (3,4,8,20)); (S3) det K = 4 = |mu_4| with K = R + Q Sigma (v71/v94 diamond); plus the definitional hexagon range {0..5}. (1) CENSUS: hexagon columns with n.col = 8: exactly 4, with n.col = 0: exactly 4 => 64 (S1)-candidates; (S2) leaves 12; (S3) leaves EXACTLY ONE - and it is R. (2) COROLLARY: the atom margins (4,8,10)/(4,13,5), the anchor column R e_1 = a, and ALL v120/v121 sum rules (16, 10, 14, 24, 40) are CONSEQUENCES - input status revoked. (3) BONUS LEMMA: on the (S1)+(S2) locus det(M + 2U) = 20 = det L for ALL 12 candidates - the fourth quartet determinant is NOT independent but a consequence (the quartet carries redundancy: the compiler's overdetermination pattern). (4) RESIDUE [P]: H2 reduces to the establishment of the selectors themselves (n and the diamond determinants - pre-existing inventoried ledger objects); the address question introduces NO new residual class; FIREWALL: everything frozen in v4/v18/v20/v71/v94 (ledger FLAV.H2.05)"),
    ("v123_inventory_update", "RESIDUAL INVENTORY UPDATED (post v110-v122; the v105 gap list re-pinned with sharper contents, same cardinality) [I] machine bookkeeping + typing contract: (1) THE THIRTEEN NEW LEDGER ROWS exist with their scripts (CAR.PAIR.02, CAR.QTRANS.01, CAR.COUNT.01, CAR.QFREE.01, GATE.UWALL.06-09, FLAV.H2.02-05, ARCH.TRIAD.01) - checked against status_ledger.csv. (2) R2 CARRIES THREE LOADS: the single index-4 boundary-net statement closes, when proven, (a) the metric gate (GATE.METRIC.06), (b) the carrier choice (CAR.QFREE.01 upgrade contract), (c) the QBL programme (ARCH.QUAD.01) - one theorem, three doors. (3) UPDATED RESIDUAL TABLE: exactly FIVE structural classes - R1 seam quantum clock (bend log_{3/2}3 at ~1/3pi) [P]; R2 index-4 seam net (3 loads) [P]/[A]; R3 seam determinant => EH [A]; R4' SELECTOR ESTABLISHMENT (n = (5,-9,6) + diamond determinants; replaces the DISCHARGED 'H2 dictionary') [A]/[P]; R5 parabolic realisation of Q (GATE.QGEO; P1) [P] - plus the two irreducibles (v_geo, pi) and frozen data surfaces; a sixth structural class would FAIL this script. (4) THE FLAVOR SIDE HAS NO OPEN ANALYSIS CLASS OF ITS OWN: H2 values exact, addresses pinned, margins theorems; residue = five frozen selector integers. Ledger-bookkeeping module, Python-only by nature (ledger SYNTH.INVENTORY.02)"),
    ("v124_resummed_clock", "THE RESUMMED CLOCK (R1's bend acquires a closed form: the transfer spectrum IS the geometric resummation of a weight-linear clock) [I] exact identities on frozen spectra + [P] semiclassical derivation: (1) THE SPECTRUM READS (1 - n/N)^{p2}: the frozen transfer eigenvalues {1, (2/3)^6, (1/3)^6} (v54/v69/v95) are EXACTLY lambda_n = (1 - n/N_fam)^{p2}, n = 0,1,2, with p2 = 6 = the hexagon size. (2) CLOSED-FORM CLOCK: rate(n) = -6 ln(1 - n/3) reproduces {0, Delta, 6ln3}; the v107 bend rate(2)/rate(1) = log_{3/2}3 becomes a one-line consequence. (3) THE LINEARISATION CARRIES THE SHEET: rate(n) = 2n + n^2/3 + 2n^3/27 + ... - the linear (one-loop) term has slope EXACTLY |Z2| = 2 relative to the integer classical Ginsparg-Perry clock {0,-1,-2} (v104/v107): quantum clock = sheet-doubled classical clock + geometric tail. (4) THE WALL AT N_fam: rate -> oo as n -> 3 (pole at the family count) => the cusp ladder ends at n = 2: the THREE-level transfer spectrum is forced by the clock itself. (5) R1 RE-SHARPENED [P]: closed-form target - derive rate(n) = -p2 ln(1 - n/N_fam) from the near-Nariai one-loop at kappa = 1/(3pi); linear response must give slope |Z2| x classical; nothing fitted (ledger HOR.CLOCK.03)"),
    ("v125_glue_qsystem", "THE GLUE Q-SYSTEM (the index-4 mu4 extension exists as an explicit Longo Q-system; R2 sharpens from 'find' to 'match') [I] exact finite axioms: (1) Q-SYSTEM AXIOMS on A = C[Z4] (glue group algebra, multiplication delta_a x delta_b -> delta_{a+b}, unit delta_0): associativity, unit law, FROBENIUS (m x 1)(1 x m*) = m* m = (1 x m)(m* x 1), SPECIALNESS m m* = |Z4| id - all exact => a special C* Frobenius algebra = Longo Q-system with dim theta = 4: JONES INDEX [B:A] = 4 = |mu_4| (v89 Carrier Index Lemma); KLM mu_carrier = 16 = 4^2 x 1 re-verified. (2) LOCALITY = ISOTROPY (v92 in Q-system language): on the Lagrangian glue <(1,1)> the discriminant form gives q(k(1,1)) = k^2 = (0,1,4,9), all integers - the braiding obstruction vanishes, the extension is local; the two Lagrangian glues = the sheet pair are the only maximal isotropic choices. (3) HALFWAY SUB-Q-SYSTEM: {0,2} < Z4 closes => unique intermediate C[Z2] = the SO(16)_1 tower step (v92/v113), index 4 = 2x2. (4) R2 SHARPENED [P]: the gate's Q-system now EXISTS explicitly; what remains is the operator-algebraic IDENTIFICATION 'the seam-Calderon inclusion of the 16-Majorana net realises THIS Q-system' - matching two constructed objects, not a search; the three loads (metric + carrier + QBL, v123) hang on this one identification (ledger GATE.METRIC.08)"),
    ("v126_clock_wall_bridge", "THE CLOCK AND THE WALL SHARE A SPECTRUM (the resummed-clock weights ARE the Mehta-Seshadri parabolic weights; R1's first checkpoint passes classically) [I] exact: (1) THE WEIGHTS ARE THE PARABOLIC WEIGHTS - the arguments n/N_fam = {0, 1/3, 2/3} of the v124 resummed logarithm are EXACTLY spec A0* (the exact U_wall residue, v115); spectral bridge lambda_n = (1 - alpha_n)^{p2} over alpha in spec A0* reproduces the frozen transfer spectrum {1, (2/3)^6, (1/3)^6} - the horizon clock and the flavor wall share their spectrum through the complement map alpha -> 1 - alpha. (2) CHECKPOINT 1 PASSES CLASSICALLY: the resummed clock's linear coefficient p2/N_fam = 2 = |Z2| EQUALS the established classical entropy-deviation rate 2H = |Z2| x Hubble (v104) - the slope-2 linear response demanded by v124 is already the classical entropy rate; the genuinely QUANTUM content of R1 isolates to the geometric tail sum_{k>=2} alpha^k/k. (3) THE DETERMINANT IS THE ENTROPY CURVATURE: det(1 - A0*) = 2/9 = |Z2|/N_fam^2 - exactly the established gravity entropy curvature at the anchor (v102), a fourth independent appearance; tr(1 - A0*) = 2 = |Z2|, det A0* = 0. (4) R1 RE-TARGETED [P]: derive 'rate = -p2 ln(1 - alpha)' with alpha the parabolic weight - first order classical, tail quantum; ONE SPECTRUM, TWO GATES, ONE OBJECT A0* (ledger HOR.CLOCK.04)"),
    ("v127_ring_resummation", "THE CLOCK IS A LOG-DETERMINANT (the geometric tail is the standard ring/RPA resummation; the 'O(1) resummation' demanded by v107 is now TYPED) [I] exact: (1) LOG-DET IDENTITY - for a rank-1 insertion P (tr P^k = 1): -ln det(1 - alpha P) = -ln(1 - alpha) = sum_k alpha^k/k, so the v124 clock is EXACTLY rate = -p2 Tr ln(1 - alpha P): p2 = 6 identical ring towers, ONE PER HEXAGON SITE (= positive root of A3), coupling = parabolic weight alpha. (2) RING LADDER: k=1 ring = the CLASSICAL term (6 alpha = |Z2| n = the v104/v126 entropy rate); k=2 ring = first quantum correction (1/3 at weight 1); partial sums converge to the exact rates monotonically from below (K = 1,2,3,8 exact). (3) COUPLING CROSS-LINK (audit): kappa_seam = (c/24pi) at Lambda = Mbar^2, c = 8 (v107) gives 8/24 = 1/3 = alpha_1 - the seam coupling is the FIRST PARABOLIC WEIGHT over pi: kappa = alpha_1/pi. (4) THE WALL = RING DIVERGENCE: radius of convergence |alpha| < 1; at alpha -> 1 (n -> N_fam) the sum diverges - the v124 wall is the standard RPA instability. (5) R1 FINAL FORM [P]: show the near-Nariai one-loop effective action of the seam mode with insertion alpha and multiplicity p2 is the ring sum - 'the seam clock is the RPA determinant of one mode on six sites'; resummation TYPE identified, derivation open (ledger HOR.CLOCK.05)"),
    ("v128_graded_hull", "THE GRADED HULL + THE ZERO-MODE MULTIPLICITY (both named computations R1/R2 gain their structural anchors) [I] exact: R2 HALF - (1) EXPLICIT COSET CONSTRUCTION: the 240 E8 roots built in D5 (+) A3 + glue coordinates decompose over the glue Z4 as 240 = 52 + 64 + 60 + 64 (C0 = carrier 40+12, C1 = (16,4b) from norm 5/4 + 3/4, C2 = (10,6) from 1+1, C3 = (16b,4)) - the v89 branching as explicit norm-2 vectors. (2) THE GRADING IS EXACT: for ALL 6720 root pairs whose sum is again a root, coset(r1+r2) = coset(r1)+coset(r2) mod 4 - E8 IS A Z4-GRADED LIE ALGEBRA over the carrier, and the grading group IS the glue = the v125 Q-system: the checksum hull is the Q-system's graded module realised in 248 dimensions. R1 HALF - (3) THE MULTIPLICITY IS THE ZERO-MODE COUNT: the Ginsparg-Perry l=1 sector (the zero modes, lambda in {0,-1}, v104/v107) has 2l+1 = 3 modes; sheet doubling gives 2x3 = 6 = p2 = |R+(A3)| - the ring multiplicity of the v127 clock equals the sheet-doubled zero-mode count; [P] reading: zero modes are exactly the modes forcing nonperturbative resummation in dS one-loop physics - the natural home of the six RPA towers. (4) RESIDUE [P]: R1 = compute the RPA determinant on the six sheet-doubled l=1 zero modes; R2 = identify the seam-Calderon inclusion with the Z4-graded structure now exhibited inside E8 itself (ledger E8.GRADE.01)"),
    ("v129_entropy_power_law", "THE CLOCK IS AN ENTROPY POWER LAW (the transfer eigenvalues are the Nariai entropy fractions to the hexagon power; the ring coupling is the fractional entropy deficit) [I] exact on established levels: (1) THE THREE ENTROPY LEVELS - the established Nariai bookkeeping (v101) has S/S_dS in {1, 2/3, 1/3} (pure dS; two-horizon total; single horizon - deficit S_dS/3 per step): EXACTLY the complementary cusp weights 1 - n/N_fam. (2) THE CLOCK IS AN ENTROPY POWER LAW: lambda_n = (S_n/S_dS)^{p2} = the frozen transfer spectrum; rate(n) = p2 ln(S_dS/S_n) - hexagon-weighted log-entropy deficits; audit: exponent p2 = 6 = 2h reads as the two-point form of a weight h = 3 = N_fam operator (recorded). (3) THE COUPLING IS THE ENTROPY DEFICIT (triple identity): alpha = n/N_fam = MS parabolic weight (v115/v126) = 1 - S_n/S_dS = DeltaS_n/S_dS - the RPA insertion strength is the fractional entropy deficit; the coupling is not a free parameter in ANY of its three readings. (4) ORIENTATION CONSISTENCY: weight 0 <-> pure dS (max entropy, stationary attractor), weight 2 <-> single horizon (fastest decay); monotone - deeper deficit = faster relaxation, the established repeller -> attractor orientation (v82/v101/v102). (5) R1 THERMODYNAMIC FORM [P]: derive Gamma_n ~ (S_n/S_dS)^{p2} from the near-Nariai one-loop - a Gibbons-Hawking-type entropy power law with exponent = the hexagon; the exponent (weight h = N_fam) is the remaining quantum content (ledger HOR.CLOCK.06)"),
    ("v130_born_square", "THE BORN SQUARE (the amplitude weight is h = N_fam = half the zero-mode count; the clock exponent p2 = 2h is its Born square - the v128 multiplicity and the v129 weight are ONE object) [I] exact bookkeeping: (1) EXPONENT BOOKKEEPING: in the standard collective-coordinate treatment each zero mode trades a Gaussian integral for a moduli factor ~ S^{1/2}; with n_zero = 6 the transition AMPLITUDE scales as A ~ (S/S_dS)^{n_zero/2} = (S/S_dS)^3 and the PROBABILITY is its Born square Gamma = |A|^2 = (S/S_dS)^6 = the v129 entropy power law => h = n_zero/2 = 3 = N_fam, p2 = 2h: the v129 weight audit is DERIVED from mode counting, the factor 2 is the Born rule. (2) THE THREE ARE THE SPHERE'S CONFORMAL DIRECTIONS: dim of the l=1 scalar eigenspace on S^2 = 2l+1 = 3 = the number of proper conformal Killing vectors of S^2 (gradients of l=1 harmonics; Ginsparg-Perry/Bousso-Hawking class, external standard); the x2 is the HORIZON PAIR = the sheet deck (v101): n_zero = |Z2| x 3 = 6 = p2 - every factor an established object. (3) CONSISTENCY: multiplicity (v128) = exponent (v129) = Born square of the amplitude weight; h = N_fam ties the clock's conformal weight to the family count. (4) RESIDUE [P]: justify the per-zero-mode S^{1/2} collective-coordinate normalisation on the Nariai instanton for exactly these six modes - a textbook-class computation; no exotic object remains in R1 (ledger HOR.CLOCK.07)"),
    ("v131_measure_is_area", "THE MEASURE IS THE AREA (the per-mode S^{1/2} of the Born square is the zero-mode NORM, computed exactly; the R1 residue narrows to one determinant-ratio cancellation) [I] exact + [P] sharply named: (1) ZERO-MODE NORM = AREA: on S^2(r) the L^2 norm^2 of each of the three normalised l=1 harmonics is EXACTLY r^2 = A/(4pi) - the norm of every zero mode IS the horizon area (hence the entropy) up to the fixed 4pi (all three modes integrated exactly). (2) JACOBIAN BOOKKEEPING: per-mode collective-coordinate Jacobian = mode norm ~ S^{1/2} (standard change of variables, no model input); six sheet-doubled modes => amplitude ratio (S_n/S_dS)^3; Born square => Gamma ratio (S_n/S_dS)^6 = the v129 power law - every exponent factor now has a derivation-level origin: norm = area -> Jacobian = S^{1/2} -> six modes -> amplitude S^3 -> Born -> S^6. (3) UNIT CONSISTENCY: the 4pi in norm^2 = A/(4pi) is the same Gauss-Bonnet 4pi that builds c3 = 1/(2x4pi) (v106/P1); it cancels in all ratios - exactly why the clock sees only entropy FRACTIONS. (4) THE LAST STEP [P]: show det'_n/det'_dS = 1 + O(deficit) (non-zero-mode determinant cancellation in the ratio; same local near-Nariai geometry) - the ONE remaining computation: R1 = norm (exact, done) + Jacobian (standard) + Born (rule) + det-ratio (open) (ledger HOR.CLOCK.08)"),
    ("v132_detratio_anomaly", "THE DET-RATIO ANOMALY IS THE KOIDE CONSTANT (the scaling anomaly zeta(0) of the non-zero-mode Nariai fluctuation determinant, sphere sector, is EXACTLY -2/3 = -|Z2|/N_fam) [I] exact heat-kernel arithmetic + numerical continuation: (1) SPECTRAL SETUP (re-pinned): L = -Delta - 2 on unit S^2 (the -2 = -|Z2| = the v104 modulus mass); eigenvalues (l+2)(l-1), degeneracy 2l+1, kernel = 3 zero modes (l=1), one negative mode (l=0). (2) THE HEAT COEFFICIENT IS MADE OF ATOMS: a_1 = (1/4pi) Int(R/6 - E) dA = 1/3 + 2 = 1/N_fam + |Z2| = 7/3 - the curvature third and the sheet mass. (3) THE ANOMALY IS THE KOIDE CONSTANT: zeta(0)|det' = a_1 - dim ker = 7/3 - 3 = -2/3 = -|Z2|/N_fam; independently confirmed by numerical continuation of the heat trace (constant term of Tr' - 1/t extrapolates to -2/3 at ~1e-7) - the EIGHTH appearance of 2/3, the first as a SPECTRAL anomaly. (4) CONSEQUENCE: det'(cL) = c^{zeta(0)} det'(L) - the determinant ratio between configurations is NOT automatically 1; the S^2-sector share of the scaling budget is exactly -2/3 per Hubble-unit conversion; the dimensionless tower is configuration-independent (pure-number GP spectrum): all scale dependence = this anomaly + the zero-mode Jacobians (v131). (5) BUDGET STATEMENT [P]: show the FULL 4d zeta(0) budget (dS2 + gauge/ghost + S^2 sectors) vanishes or is absorbed - the S^2 share is pinned exactly; nothing claimed about the total (ledger HOR.CLOCK.09)"),
    ("v133_zeta_budget", "THE ZETA BUDGET, BOTH ROUTES COMPUTED EXACTLY (the reduced seam route carries pure anchor-ratio anomalies; the naive 4d route does not - the budget computation structurally selects the reduced seam reading) [I] + [P]: Euclidean Nariai = S^2 x S^2 (the temporal dS2 sector continues to the SAME unit sphere). (1) THE REDUCED ROUTE: each 2d sector carries the v132 operator with zeta(0)|det' = -2/3; two sectors give budget = -4/3 = -e1/p0 = MINUS THE SEED GAIN (the second v119 triad ratio; the first, -2/3, is the per-sector share); the six zero modes split 3+3 across the two spheres = the horizon pair (v101/v128/v130). (2) THE NAIVE 4D ROUTE: with the standard unit-S2 heat expansion 1/t + 1/3 + t/15 (verified numerically) and the symmetric split L4 = (-Delta1 - 1) + (-Delta2 - 1): per-factor trace 1/t + 4/3 + (9/10)t => a2(4d) = 161/45; zero modes (1,0)+(0,1) = 6; zeta(0)|det',4d = 161/45 - 6 = -109/45 (continuation ~1e-8) - NO anchor-atom reading. (3) ROUTE DISCRIMINATION [I + P]: reduced route anomalies = pure anchor ratios (-2/3, -4/3 - two of the three triad values); 4d route = -109/45, no atom => the zeta budget structurally favours the REDUCED seam reading, consistent with the 2d-seam architecture; route-selection evidence, not proof. (4) REMAINING [P]: graviton/ghost shares on S^2 x S^2 (Volkov-Wipf class, external standard) complete the budget - a finite list of known heat coefficients (ledger HOR.CLOCK.10)"),
    ("v134_dual_anchor", "THE DUAL ANCHOR LEMMA (the inverse flavor response of the anchor IS the Nariai root; third algebraic leg of the flavor-horizon bridge; external review 2026-06-12 validated) [I]: (1) THE DUAL ANCHOR: d := a^T R^-1 = a^T L^-1 = (-1/2, -1/2, 1) with d.1 = 0, d.a = 1, d = (3/2)(a - (4/3)1)^T (the normalised TRACELESS anchor) and (1,1,-2) = -2d - the inverse flavor response stores EXACTLY the Nariai double-root structure (v101) up to sign and scale: the horizon sits inside the flavor compiler as a dual invariant. (2) WHY INVARIANT (Sherman-Morrison, exact): L = R + 6*1 e1^T => v^T L^-1 = v^T R^-1 <=> v^T R^-1 1 = 0; R^-1 1 = (1,1,-1)/4, denominator 5/2; the anchor satisfies a.(R^-1 1) = 0 - it lies on the 2-plane of invariant covectors (the winding lives in the democratic direction, which d annihilates). (3) CONTROL: 1, e1, n do NOT lie on the plane (1/4, 1/4, -5/2) - the membership is special. (4) THE DUAL NORMAL PAIR: d (sheet normal) + n = (5,-9,6) (torsion normal; n^T R = (8,0,0), n^T L = (20,0,0), n.a = 8, n.1 = 2 = |Z2| cf. v95) = the dual basis of the flavor boundary. (5) CONSEQUENCE [P]: third algebraic bridge leg (besides spectrum v126 and entropy v129); supports the reduced seam reading (v133); R4' target = derive the PAIR (d,n) (ledger FLAV.DUAL.01)"),
    ("v135_det_surface", "THE DETERMINANT SURFACE (the sheet diamond is a 2d surface with iso-volume WALLS at the atoms; external review 2026-06-12 validated) [I]: (1) SURFACE + WALLS: det M(s,t) = 3s(t+1)(t+2) + t^2+5t+8 on the established diamond M(s,t) = R + Q diag(s,t,t) (v94/v95); two iso-volume walls INDEPENDENT of s: t = -2 => det = 2 = |Z2|, t = -1 => det = 4 = |mu_4| (det K = 4 is a LAYER, not an isolated hit); winding line t = 0: det = 6s+8 => (det R, det C, det L) = (8, 14, 20); det F = M(1,1) = 32 = 2^{g_car} closes the four canonical points. (2) ANCHOR BLOCK: det B = 6s(t+2) + 3t^2+15t+16; det B(s,0) = 2 det M(s,0) EXACTLY (anchor block doubles the volume on the winding line); own Z2 wall det B(s,-2) = -2; t = -1 is NOT a B-wall (6s+4, recorded honestly). (3) ROW-BUDGET AXES: rowsum(C) = (7,11,13), rowsum(U) = (3,3,3), rowsum(V) = (1,2,3) = Spec(Q+) verbatim; audit: centre budget (7,11,13) = (scalaron, ||Pl(K)||_1, Delta_Q). (4) TWO ANCHOR MICRO-IDENTITIES: e1^2 + e2^2 = 41 = 10 b1 (anchor Pythagoras, companion to Delta_Y = 25 = 9+16); p1^2 + p2^2 = 52 = the carrier coset root count (40+12, v128). (5) READING [P]: flavor lives on a 2d surface with atom walls and (winding, Q+) axes - compiler semantics; no gate status changes (ledger FLAV.SURF.01)"),
    ("v136_dual_normal_selector", "THE DUAL-NORMAL SELECTOR ((d,n) pins R COLUMNWISE; the A0* zero mode carries the exact spectral normal; the W(A3) orbit control bounds the lift; external review 2026-06-12 validated + sharpened): (1) COLUMN NORMAL FORM [I]: d.c_j = a_j and n.c_j = 8 delta_1j for the columns of R; common kernel of (d,n) = primitive (6,8,7) (audit: p2, rank E8, scalaron-7); brute-force census over the address box {0..5}^3: each column is the UNIQUE solution (1 of 216) - R4' shrinks from a 6^9 census (v121) to three 1-of-216 column problems: (d,n) => R. (2) HONESTY [I]: K is NOT pinned directly (d^T K = (1,1/2,1), n^T K = (14,1,-6)); det K = 4 follows via the diamond (mu_4 wall, v135). (3) SPECTRAL NORMAL [I]: the A0* zero mode v = (-sqrt2,3,-sqrt5)/3 has signed squares = -(2,-9,5) = -(|Z2|, -N_fam^2, g_car); NEW ATOMS: ||v||^2 = 16/9 (16 = dim S+), adj(A0*) = (2/9) P_v with 2/9 = the SdS entropy curvature. (4) SIGMA RELATIONS [I]: sigma.1 = -|Z2|, sigma.a = N_fam, n.sigma = 121 = ||Pl(K)||_1^2 (the v119 audit constant). (5) ORBIT CONTROL [I]: |W(A3)| = 24 exact; only real orbit images of sigma are its signed copies; NO image proportional to n - the naive cofactor/orbit lift FAILS as predicted; sigma -> n is a genuine mechanism beyond the monodromy group. (6) R4' RESTATED [P]: derive the PAIR (d,n); then R is forced columnwise (ledger GATE.UWALL.10)"),
    ("v137_qplus_cohomology", "THE Q+ GRADING IS COHOMOLOGY (R5/GATE.QGEO at the spectrum level; external review 2026-06-12 validated + sharpened): (1) BASIS + CHARACTERS [I]: b_1(P^1 minus mu_4) = 3 = N_fam with holomorphic basis omega_k = z^(k-1)dz/(z^4-1), k = 1,2,3 (regular at infinity); mu_4 character of omega_k = i^k - H^1 = chi_1 + chi_2 + chi_3, each nontrivial character exactly once, trivial absent; residue vector over the punctures = the character vector zeta^k/4 exactly. (2) THE GRADING IS Spec(Q+) [I]: character degrees (1,2,3) = Spec(Q+) (Q+ = 3*diag(cusp weights)+1, v69/v72); NEW: the cusp weights {0,1/3,2/3} are spec(A0*) (v115) - Mehta-Seshadri weights, cusp classes, cohomology characters and Q+ are ONE spectrum in four readouts. (3) A3 EXPONENTS [I]: (1,2,3) = exponents of A3 (W(A3) = S4, v117), h(A3) = 4 = |mu_4| - the Q+ generation grading IS the A3 exponent grading realised on the seam curve's cohomology: the R5 dictionary at spectrum level. (4) RESIDUE [P]: GATE.QGEO's remainder = the NATURALITY of the identification (canonical map H^1 character basis -> V-axis generation basis, rowsum(V) = (1,2,3) v135); spectrum equality [I], canonical map = the residue (ledger FLAV.QGEO.04)"),
    ("v138_vw_firewall", "THE VOLKOV-WIPF FIREWALL (R1 typed closure: external full-4d value pinned, the edge part = TWO COPIES of the reduced seam budget; external review 2026-06-12, values verified against arXiv:2506.02142 Table 4.1 = Volkov-Wipf hep-th/0003081): (1) EXTERNAL DATUM [I, typed external]: alpha_bulk = 22/45, alpha_edge = -8/3, alpha_PI = -98/45 for d = 3 (S^2 x S^2); review's arXiv number corrected (0204021 -> 0003081). (2) THE EDGE MATCH [I]: alpha_edge = -8/3 = 2 x (-4/3) - the external edge factor is TWO IDENTICAL COPIES (one per horizon) and the per-copy magnitude 4/3 = e1/p0 is EXACTLY the v133 reduced seam budget (= the seed gain); the TFPT reduced route lands on the EDGE sector of the external bulk/edge split, the bulk 22/45 = ideal graviton gas (not the clock); two copies = horizon pair = sheet doubling. (3) FIREWALL ARITHMETIC [I]: -98/45 + 60/45 = -38/45 (38 = 2*19); neither -98/45 nor -38/45 nor 22/45 is an anchor atom - consistent with v133's non-atomic naive route (different operator content, recorded). (4) TYPING DECISION [P]: R1 = the reduced zero-mode/RPA seam clock = an EDGE-sector object; the full 4d VW determinant is the gravity firewall (absorbed in mu_0/(Lambda G)^3 normalisation), not a TFPT atom (ledger HOR.CLOCK.11)"),
    ("v139_selector_triangle", "THE SELECTOR TRIANGLE (anchor + A0* zero mode + three atoms => R; the R4' residue shrinks to three pairings): (1) d IS ANCHOR DATA [I]: d = (3/2)a - 2*1 exactly - the dual anchor (v134) has a closed form that never mentions R; the first selector of the pair (d,n) is DERIVED, not residual. (2) THE FRAME [I]: (1, a, sigma) is a basis of Z^3 with det(1|a|sigma) = 11 = ||Pl(K)||_1 (the quark constant as the frame volume; sigma = the A0* zero-mode signature, v136). (3) n FROM THREE ATOMS [I]: n = (5,-9,6) is the UNIQUE solution of n.1 = 2 = |Z2|, n.a = 8 = rank E8, n.sigma = 121 = 11^2 - the cofactor definition (v95) is replaced by frame data plus three atoms. (4) THE SQUARE SELECTS [I]: on the line n.1 = 2, n.a = 8 the sigma-pairing is 11(11+t) - divisible by 11 for every t, a positive perfect square exactly at t = 0. (5) THE REVIEW LIFT EXACT (audit) [I]: n = reverse(sigma) + |mu_4| e_3 (generation flip + mu_4 lift at the third slot, as the review predicted); n - sigma = N_fam e_1 + e_3. (6) RESIDUE [P]: R4' = derive the three pairings (|Z2|, rank E8, ||Pl(K)||_1^2); everything else in anchor -> (d,n) -> R (v136) is exact (ledger GATE.UWALL.11)"),
    ("v140_canonical_map", "THE CANONICAL MAP EXISTS AND IS RIGID (GATE.QGEO naturality collapses to ONE Z_3 choice): (1) THREE mu_4 ACTIONS, ONE MATCH [I]: deck U = diag(1,i,-i) has characters (0,1,3) (invariant line, misses 2 - cannot match H^1); the sheet-twisted deck -U has (2,3,1) and the cusp exponential i^{Q+} has (1,2,3) - both with character SET {1,2,3} = the H^1 set (v137): only the SIGN-TWISTED actions match, the same sheet twist as the v118 hexagon. (2) RIGIDITY (Schur) [I]: both sides multiplicity-free with equal character sets => the equivariant isomorphism exists and is unique up to one scalar per character (commutant = diagonal); the explicit map is the character-matching permutation - 'the canonical map' is well-defined; existence and uniqueness are no longer open. (3) GRADING TRANSPORT [I]: under the i^{Q+}-map the H^1 Euler degree pulls back to Q+ itself; under the -U-map to Q+ o rho (rho = the (123) family rotation) - the two candidates differ by EXACTLY one Z_3 rotation. (4) RESIDUE [P]: GATE.QGEO collapses from 'prove naturality' to ONE discrete choice - which sign-twisted action is the geometric boundary deck (-U monodromy sheet twist vs i^{Q+} cusp exponential) (ledger FLAV.QGEO.05)"),
