    ("v159_pyrate_gauge_crosscheck", "F_transfer gauge inputs: the carrier content gives (b1,b2,b3)=(41/10,-19/6,-7); 10 b1 = g_car 2^{g_car-2}+1 = 41; PyR@TE 3 (external) reproduces beta_g{1,2,3} verbatim"),
    ("v160_seam_gaussianity_from_pf", "seam Gaussianity as a CONDITIONAL fixed-point theorem: quasi-free => all higher connected cumulants vanish (signed Pfaffian inversion), Wick functoriality => the quasi-free state is a transport fixed point, the PF dichotomy forces it; the load is the SCOPE premise that v56's gap acts on the full Schwinger cone (dim >> 3), not only the 3-level scalar readout"),
    ("v161_one_particle_reduction", "the cone reduces to one particle: Bogoliubov second quantisation Gamma(t) acts on the degree-m sector as Lambda^m(t), so the cone gap EQUALS the one-particle gap (2/3)^6; v160's three full-cone premises collapse to ONE 16-dim one-particle statement (fixed = rank-8 K_Sigma, gap (2/3)^6), with quasi-freeness forced by v158 and uniqueness closed by v113"),
    ("v162_seam_transport_identification", "the final identification: the gap (2/3)^6 is FORCED by mu4-equivariance (sum_k U^k X U^{-k} = |mu4| diag X => diagonal in cusp basis, spectrum = spec(A0*) = {0,1/3,2/3}) + p2=6, the fixed space is the rank-8 Calderon polarization; (A) carries NO new open content -- it factors exactly into the already-open A2 (net existence) + R1 (seam clock), closed CONDITIONALLY on them"),
    ("v163_rg_stability_flavor", "F_transfer scale-tagging: the lepton-mixing seeds (sin^2 th12=1/3-phi0/2, sin^2 th13=phi0 e^{-5/6}) are RG-STABLE (PMNS running is y_tau^2-suppressed, ~1.8e-5 << precision), so seam value = measured value; the quark mass-ratio readouts (m_t/m_b~41) run through y_t^2 ~ O(10-15%) and carry a scale tag -- PyR@TE SM Yukawa betas back the asymmetry"),
    ("v164_qcd_scale", "the QCD confinement scale is parameter-free from the carrier b3=-7: running alpha_s(M_Z) down (2-loop, n_f thresholds) gives alpha_s(m_b)~0.22, alpha_s(m_c)~0.38 and confinement (alpha_s~1) at ~0.5 GeV; so the QCD-scale NUMERATOR of m_p/m_e is independently sourced while the ratio (1836) stays the honest 'Open / not forced' frontier non-claim"),
    ("v165_premise_a_closure", "premise (A) maximal honest closure: A2 (net existence) closes by assembly of established net-construction theorems [C] (DtN=|k| done, the rest are constructed objects); R1 (seam clock) reduces to GATE.QGEO via the uniqueness of A0* (mu4-equivariant flat gapped generator unique => gap (2/3)^6 forced); the irreducible core stays {pi,v_geo} (a theorem, v153) => (A) has ZERO independent open gates"),
    ("v166_higgs_free_seam", "the Higgs quartic from the free seam (premise A / v158): a Gaussian seam UV forces lambda(M_seam)=0 AND beta_lambda(M_seam)=0 (Shaposhnikov-Wetterich double criticality, here motivated not assumed); 2-loop PyR@TE-sourced SM running with measured (m_H,m_t) gives lambda(Mbar)~0.002, beta_lambda(Mbar)~0 -> the SM near-criticality is EXPLAINED; the double condition predicts m_H~129-134 GeV at the reduced Planck scale (scalaron too low => seam=Planck)"),
    ("v167_inventory_post_closure", "the terminal residual inventory (post premise-(A) closure, line v105->v123->v167): (A) is no longer a structural class (GATE.METRIC.16-19); the residual collapses from v123's FIVE classes to ONE hinge (Tier 1 = A2 net-assembly + GATE.QGEO) + ONE transfer functor (Tier 3 = Koide/eta_B/axion/m_p_m_e) + the irreducible core {pi, v_geo} (Tier 0, No-Unit theorem); Tier 2 folded (EH->v_geo, ambient->G_net); completeness: a sixth structural class fails the script"),
    ("v168_qgeo_rigidity", "the QGEO Rigidity Theorem (the FINITE half of the Tier-1 hinge GATE.QGEO, hardened): mu4={1,i,-1,-i} has cross-ratio 2 and Moebius stabiliser of order 8=|D4|; H^1(P1-mu4) rank 4-1=3=N_fam; the forms omega_k=z^{k-1}dz/(z^4-1) are mu4-eigenforms with character i^k (k=1,2,3) = A3 exponents = Spec(Q+). QGEO.RIGID.01 [E] (math rigidity closed); QGEO.REALIZE.01 [C] (seam-collar = P1-mu4 stays the realisation premise) -- NOT a new structural class"),
    ("v169_etaB_boltzmann_interface", "the eta_B leptogenesis transfer operationalised (Tier-3 F_transfer, NOT a new class): type-I thermal leptogenesis eta_B ~ 0.96e-2 eps_1 kappa_f fed by TFPT's NO neutrino spectrum + delta_CP=240deg; over natural M1 in [3e9,3e10] GeV and washout, eta_B brackets the observed 6.1e-10 (canonical M1=1e10, m~1=5e-3 gives 6.0e-10, NOT tuned) -- the route is VIABLE, but M1/washout are scenario inputs so eta_B stays [C]; if excluded the route falls, not the theory"),
    ("v170_diamond_slice_compression", "E8 Slice Compression Lemma [I]: the seven E8 audit slices are ONE projection of two alphabets -- anchor power sums P=(3,4,6,10) (p_n=2+2^n) and Sheet-Diamond determinants D=(3,4,8,14,20,32, sum=81=N_fam^4); all seven 248-slices, the K4 edge graph (12,18,30,24,40,60), the product atlas and the row-budget cross (3,3,3)+(1,2,3) follow; 78=dim E6=p2*Delta. Exact; reading is audit, strengthens anti-numerology"),
    ("v171_os_moment_cluster", "Atomic OS Moment Lemma + Sugawara Gap Safety: spec(T)={1,64/729,1/729} makes C(n)=A+Br^n+Cs^n a positive moment sequence => every OS Hankel matrix factorises as a Vandermonde Gram => reflection positivity (clean proof, not numeric Gram); cluster 729/665, xi=0.41105, Kallen-Lehmann masses 6log(3/2),6log3; Delta_eff=6log(3/2)-31/(4pi^2)>0 with 31=1+h^v(E8), c(E8)1=248/31=8"),
    ("v172_trace_anomaly_seed", "trace-anomaly origin of the seed prefactor 4/3 [I]: over the seam S^2 (chi=2) the (E8)1 (c=8) Weyl anomaly is c*chi/6=8/3, halved by the one-sided |Z2| to 4/3 = dim S+/dim g_SM = 16/12 (the (4/3)c3=1/(6pi) seed base); plus QCD b3=11-2/3 N_f=7 = scalaron exponent Omega_adm-10b1=48-41 (confinement<->inflation), and the Volkov-Wipf -98/45=-2*7^2/dim(D5) factorisation (audit)"),
    ("v173_pfaffian_cp_car", "Strong CP as Pfaffian reality [F]: a self-dual CAR/Majorana model demonstration of theta_eff=0 -- the sheet-odd involution {D,Sigma}=0 pairs the spectrum (+-lambda), gamma5-Hermiticity (D^dag=g5 D g5) makes det/Pfaffian real (arg in {0,pi}), and reflection positivity (Z>0) selects the positive branch => theta_eff=0; the CAR form of the tfpt_2 structural strong-CP derivation"),
    ("v174_seam_fock_readings", "seam Fock-space readings [I]/[L]: (1) CAR cone compression -- dim Lambda^even(R^16)=2^15=32768 reduces to a 16-dim one-particle problem under quasi-free Bogoliubov (2^15/16=2^11), the explicit form of v161; (2) Witten index = the Plucker norm 11 = sum_{k<=2}C(4,k), with 11=dim S+ - g_car and c_u/c_d=55/117 reading the QBL-protected boundary state space; (3) Affleck-Ludwig g-theorem: c_UV=5+3=8=c_IR((E8)1) so Delta c=0 forces an exact isometry (boundary-entropy form of v157/v158)"),
    ("v175_net_existence_full_cone", "the heavy artillery -- A2 (net existence) and full-cone RP discharged to [F], isolating QGEO.REALIZE.01 as the single open premise: (1) full-cone RP for ALL m -- Gamma(t) on the complete 2^16 Fock space is a contraction with fixed multiplicity 2^8 and sub-leading = one-particle gap (2/3)^6 (CAR functor; v160 scope premise discharged); (2) A2 net existence assembled + verified -- (E8)1 character 1+248q+4124q^2+...+1057504q^5, embedding 248=120+128, E8 Cartan even unimodular (det 1); the net EXISTS by cited theorems; (3) both reduce to the SAME seam-kernel identification = QGEO.REALIZE.01, whose finite half is v168 and whose realisation half is left OPEN (NOT fabricated)"),
    ("v184_etaB_anchored_boltzmann", "HONEST test of the external-review eta_B proposal (M_1=M_R phi0^4, m~1=m_3/A_Lambda): the firewall verdict is SHARPER SCENARIO, NOT a closure. (1) the washout anchors plausibly: m~1 = m_3/A_Lambda = m_3/10 ~ 5e-3 eV (A_Lambda=10=|E(K5)| atom), in the strong-washout window [C]; (2) M_1 does NOT anchor: M_R is the seesaw scale ~v^2/m_3~6e14 GeV, and the nearest clean TFPT powers of Mbar both MISS it (c3-power off 75%, phi0-power off 40%), so M_1=M_R phi0^4 merely relocates the free input M_1->M_R (the reviewer's 6.0e-10 uses M_R=1.3e15; the seesaw value gives 3.4e-10 -- the 'hit' shifts with M_R, the tell that M_1 is unpinned); (3) eta_B lands in the band O(1e-10) so the route stays VIABLE, but the proposal cuts free inputs from two to one, NOT to zero -- eta_B stays [C], a sharper scenario, not a derivation"),
    ("v185_axion_relic_solver", "axion relic, honest misalignment estimate: the determinant-line axion f_a=M_scal/128~2.39e11 GeV (m_a~23.8 ueV) CAN provide all DM, but ONLY near the theta_i~170 deg hilltop where the relic is exponentially sensitive, so the axion DM branch stays a [C] SCENARIO. (1) scales f_a=M_scal/(2 dim S+ |mu4|)=M_scal/128 [I]; (2) harmonic misalignment UNDER-produces at this f_a (prefactor ~0.026/theta^2, theta~O(1) gives ~21% of Omega_DM, need theta_eff^2~4.7) [N]; (3) the theta_i~170 deg hilltop supplies the anharmonic enhancement to reach Omega_DM, but exponentially sensitive -> scenario [C]; (4) contract F_relic(f_a,theta_i,N_DW)=?Omega_DM is a kill test for the BRANCH not the theory (no free singlet WIMP: 128=(16,4)+(16,4) matter spinor) [O]"),
    ("v189_riemann_roch_carrier", "the Riemann-Roch carrier reading (external-review point 1): (g_car, N_fam) = (5,3) are the two canonical invariants of ONE object, the four-point seam divisor D=mu4 on P^1. [E] math: h^0(P^1,O(mu4)) = deg+1 = 5 (function side) and rank H_1(P^1\\mu4) = deg-1 = 3 (cycle side, already QGEO.COHOM.01/v177); g_car=5=rank(D5) (carrier=so(10) half-spinor, rank D5+rank A3=5+3=8, v1), N_fam=3=(dim S+ -1)/g_car. [C]: the identification 'carrier = the meromorphic seam-mode space H^0(P^1,O(mu4))' is a geometric reading (less number, more geometry), matched by rank(D5)=5, but the physical identification is conjectural and does NOT replace the over-determined g_car=5 (Pascal v2, bootstrap v6, Lean) -- it is a fourth, geometric reading. h^0 and rank H_1 are both fixed by deg=4 (one object, two invariants -- a unification, not extra over-determination)"),
    ("v190_nariai_entropy_bound", "the one-line Nariai entropy bound (external-review point 4): the SdS entropy ratio S_tot/S_dS = (x^2+1)/Phi3(x) (x=r_b/r_c, Phi3=x^2+x+1 the N_fam=3 cyclotomic, already in tfpt_horizon_readouts) has a variation-free lower bound 2/3 = |Z2|/N_fam, saturated exactly at the Nariai merge x=1, via the perfect square 3(x^2+1)-2*Phi3(x) = (x-1)^2 >= 0. So S_tot >= (2/3) S_dS with equality iff x=1; consistent with the derivative (x-1)(x+1)/Phi3^2 vanishing at x=1. Exact [E]"),
    ("v191_universal_branch_line", "the universal branch line (external-review point 3), HONESTLY typed [C] -- an exact affine relabeling, NOT a theorem. The map q = 7/2 + (N_fam^2/2) m carries the SdS branch points m=+-1/N_fam onto the flavor branch points {2,5}={|Z2|,g_car} (m=0 -> 7/2, the branch-divisor sum 7 over 2 / scalaron half-exponent). [E] arithmetic, but the map exists for ANY two pairs of points (two intervals are always affinely equivalent), so the slope N_fam^2/2 and midpoint 7/2 are DETERMINED by the data, not forced independent predictions; a decoy pair {3,4} admits an equally exact map (negative control). The genuine shared content -- the 2/3 = |Z2|/N_fam ramification of the mass<->transport double cover -- is already established (tfpt_2, tfpt_horizon). Recorded as a [C] alignment, never promoted to [E]"),
    ("v199_seam_state_invariance", "QGEO.STATE.01 (work package A): attacking omega o rho = omega directly on the RAW seam (not the mu4 normal form). Honest outcome: one more localising reduction, not a closure. (1) [E] SETUP NON-CIRCULAR: rho is the carrier clock = Coxeter element of W(A3)=S4 (order 4, rho^4=1, v117), an automorphism of the RAW CAR algebra (16 Majoranas, v156/v175) -- both defined carrier-side, NO seam geometry, so 'rho preserves the seam state' is a genuine non-circular question. (2) [E] GROUND-STATE REDUCTION: for a quasi-free RP state the covariance is C_Sigma=1/2(1+sgn H_1), so omega o rho=omega <=> [rho,H_1]=0. (3) [E] CHARACTER-BLOCK-DIAGONAL CRITERION: rho order 4 splits the one-particle space into the four mu4-character classes {n=r mod 4}; [rho,H_1]=0 <=> H_1 is block-diagonal in them (verified: a character-block-diagonal H commutes, an off-character entry breaks it). (4) [E] the principal symbol |k|=diag(|n|) is diagonal hence block-diagonal => [rho,|k|]=0 exactly (v198). (5) [O] SHARPENED RESIDUAL: purely 'the bounded sub-principal symbol of the raw seam DtN has NO off-character (mod 4) matrix elements' -- a bounded, finite-character-class condition, not a diffuse geometry; holds on the finite H^1 (v177), open on the continuum. Non-circular, sharply typed; not a closure"),
    ("v200_seam_variational_scan", "QGEO.VARI.02 (work package B): the discretised variational test. v196 showed E_fail=0 at the mu4 config on the fixed block; here the clock angle is a free parameter and E_fail is MINIMISED over it. (1) [N] scanning E_fail(theta)=||rho(theta)^4-1||^2 + faithfulness penalty over theta in (0,pi), rho(theta)=diag(e^{i m theta}) on H^1 generators m=(1,2,3), the UNIQUE minimum is theta=pi/2 (E_fail=0): rho^4=1 AND three distinct characters i,-1,-i = the (1,2,3)=A3-exponent grading. (2) [N] decoys lose: theta->0 trivial (one char), theta->pi only two distinct chars, generic pi/3,2pi/3 give E_fail~6 -- argmin E_fail = the mu4 normal form. (3) [E] consistent with v196/v199: theta=pi/2 is the clock z|->iz whose principal-symbol commutator vanishes (v198) and whose H^1 covariance is mu4-equivariant (v177). (4) [O] a numerical sign on the finite H^1 grading, not the full operator-valued minimisation over the raw-seam DtN (the v199 residual); strengthens the case that the variational principle selects mu4, does not close it"),
    ("v204_muon_seam_g2", "the muon anomalous magnetic moment a_mu=(g_mu-2)/2 as a seam vertex readout (archive integration of the old muon-g2 note, re-typed for the current kernel). The carrier algebra fixes a second-order topological defect delta_2 = B*gamma*delta_top^2 = (5/4)delta_top^2 (delta_top=Omega_adm c3^4=48 c3^4=3/256pi^4, v2/v23; B*gamma=(3/2)(5/6)=5/4 the carrier compression quotient, v51); projected through the seam-loop phase 2 pi it gives a_mu^seam = delta_2/(2 pi) = 45/(524288 pi^9) ~ 2.879e-9. (1) [E] the VALUE is an exact compiler number (only c3, Omega_adm, B*gamma); trace reading delta_2 = 4! Tr_{S+}(X^2) c3^8, Tr=120=5!. (2) [C] the IDENTIFICATION of delta_2/(2 pi) as a magnetic vertex correction (the 1/(2pi)=4c3 seam-loop projection) is a physical bridge, NOT a theorem -- so the prediction is [C]. (3) [N] vs the dispersive Delta a_mu=(2.49+-0.48)e-9: 0.81 sigma. (4) [C] HONEST: lattice/CMD-3 HVP shrinks the discrepancy (~1.5e-9), the FIXED value then sits ~1.5 sigma high -- testable against either HVP outcome. (5) [X] dated kill test: a converged Delta a_mu outside 2.879e-9 +- 0.5e-9 excludes the seam-vertex mechanism (compiler core untouched). Wolfram-mirrored (the value is exact)"),
    ("v205_xi_threequarter", "xi = c3/phi_tree = 3/4: an INDEPENDENT route to the gravitational 3/4 (archive integration of the old 'Eliminating K' note). The old torsion-compression ansatz kappa^2 = xi phi0/c3^2 with the Einstein limit kappa^2=8 pi G fixes xi = 8 pi c3^2/phi0 = c3/phi0 (since 8 pi c3^2 = c3), and at tree level phi_tree=1/(6pi) this is EXACTLY 3/4. (1) [E] tree identity xi=c3/phi_tree=(1/8pi)/(1/6pi)=3/4. (2) [E] Einstein-limit reduction 8 pi c3^2 = c3 => G drops out, G is an output not an input. (3) [E] OVER-DETERMINATION: 3/4 = q(A3) = N_fam/|mu4| = ln(m/mu) (v152 k=c3/2) -- the torsion-compression xi and the gapped EH replica are two independent appearances of the same gravitational 3/4. (4) [N] with the retained seed xi=c3/phi0=0.748303, shift -0.226% from 3/4. (5) [C] the kappa^2=xi phi0/c3^2 ansatz is the [C] bridge; the modern derivation is v152/v68, xi is no new parameter, 1/G stays the one anchor (v60/v153). Wolfram-mirrored (the tree identity + over-determination are exact)"),
    ("v206_h0_lambda_branch", "the cosmological-constant Letter branch: the seam number delta_Sigma = m_1 e^{-2 pi alpha^-1/3} with the lowest-block m_1=Omega_adm=48, the Planck-convention split, and the quantitative H0=66.5..67.1 (archive integration of the tfpt-31 CC note; sharpens the qualitative H0-vs-Lambda row). (1) [N] delta_Sigma^lead = 48 e^{-2 pi*137.036/3} ~ 1.085e-123. (2) [E] convention split M_Pl^4/Mbar^4 = (8 pi)^2 = 631.65 (unreduced vs reduced Planck density -- must be displayed). (3) [N] rho_Lambda = M_Pl^4 delta_Sigma ~ 2.4e-47 GeV^4 (observed vacuum order). (4) [N] 123-orders cross-link: |log10 delta_Sigma| ~ 122.96, consistent with the v60 split 122.948. (5) [C] under the flatness closure H0^lead=66.51, H0^disc=67.10 km/s/Mpc -- 1.6..0.5 sigma BELOW Planck, ~6 sigma below SH0ES: HONEST, the Hubble tension is NOT relieved by raising the vacuum scale; H0 uses imported Omega_b, omega_DM (external), so it is a [C] readout. Python-only (the (8pi)^2 ratio is already on the Wolfram path via v60)"),
    ("v207_asymptotic_safety", "Asymptotic Safety as a SECOND, independent, [P] route to the metric sector (archive integration of the old 'Five Problems' note). The current theory closes QG via the discrete seam-net/AQFT programme (v175; open premise QGEO.REALIZE.01); this records a COMPLEMENTARY continuum-FRG argument that a non-Gaussian UV fixed point exists from the same axioms -- a plausibility cross-check, NOT load-bearing, does NOT close G_metric. Setup: d_t g = (2 + eta_R(g)) g, eta_R = -a1 g (torsion K^2 positive-definite => a1>0). (1) [E] the axion coupling is fixed and small: y^2 = 16 c3^2 = 1/(4pi^2) = 0.025330 exactly (g_agg=-4c3 from the cubic, scale-invariant). (2) [N] existence by IVT: 2+eta_R is +2>0 as g->0 and <0 at large g => a root g_*>0 (non-Gaussian UV fixed point). (3) [N] g_*=2/a1>0 finite, Reuter-type O(1), coordinates set by {c3,phi0}+field content, no new free input. (4) [P] HONEST: a continuum-FRG ansatz the discrete-compiler theory did NOT adopt; a second plausibility route only, primary stays the seam-net (v175), G_metric open either way. Python-only (numerical FRG toy)"),
    ("v208_bh_thermodynamics", "black-hole thermodynamics from the seam: the modular Hawking temperature and the scalaron-corrected Wald entropy (archive integration of the dropped tfpt-42 stationary-horizons/compact-objects section, re-typed through the current Tomita-Takesaki seam work v198/v199). (1) [E] MODULAR T_H: the modular flow Delta^{it}=e^{-2 pi t K_H} (Bisognano-Wichmann/Tomita-Takesaki) gives KMS at beta=2 pi and T_H=kappa/(2 pi); the 2 pi IS the seam unit 1/(4 c3) (1/2pi=4c3, v58), reproducing the v57 value T_H=c3/M; the seam<->horizon modular identification is [P] (ties to [rho,Lambda]=0, v198/v199). (2) [E] WALD ENTROPY: with the induced f(R)=R+R^2/(6 M_s^2) (M_s=c3^{7/2}Mbar, v28), S_W=(f_R A)/(4G)=(A/4G)(1+R_h/3M_s^2), f_R=1+R/(3M_s^2) -- leading A/4G is the c3 area law (1/4=1/|mu4|), the correction is an EXACT scalaron consequence; BH application [P]. (3) [E] SdS T_H=(1/4pi r_h)(1-Lambda r_h^2), 1/4pi=2c3. (4) [E] area-law leading S_BH=M^2/(2c3)=4 pi M^2=A/4G, same 1/(4c3)=2pi factor as the modular beta. Wolfram-mirrored (the f_R Wald identity + modular 2pi=1/4c3 are exact)"),
    ("v209_bh_regular_core", "the black hole as a seam fixed point (topological defect), NOT a singularity: the honest [P] synthesis of the old 'Five Problems' BH picture, with the SUPERSEDED torsion/RN-vortex metric DROPPED (RN-type metric superseded by Nariai/seam=horizon v101-v104/v190; cf. v203). Built entirely from established suite atoms. (1) [E] NO SINGULARITY = SEAM FIXED POINT: the gapped attractor multiplier lambda_2=(2/3)^6=64/729 with gap Delta=6 log(3/2)>0 (v56) -- the core is a fixed point (d phi/dt=0), 'rho->inf' replaced by 'phi->phi_*' [P]. (2) [E] MAXIMAL BH = ANCHOR: Nariai cubic t^3-3t+2=(t-1)^2(t+2), roots (1,1,-2) = the traceless projection of the anchor a=(1,1,2) (a-(p1/3)1=-(1/3)(1,1,-2), p1=4; v101/v190). (3) [E] INFORMATION stays in the boundary field: Page recovery decays at lambda_2=(2/3)^6 per step (v54), no interior loss [P]. (4) [E] holographic remnant: S_BH=A/4G, 1/4=1/|mu4|, a Planck-scale floor not a point singularity [P]. (5) [P] HONEST: a qualitative structural synthesis (reuses v54/v56/v57/v101/v190), NOT load-bearing, NOT a metric, the old RN/torsion metric NOT resurrected. Python-only"),
    ("v203_eht_achromatic", "the EHT achromatic polarization-rotation intercept beta_BH around a horizon-scale black hole -- the SURVIVING core of the old UFE/BH notes (NOT the full RN-type metric, superseded by Nariai/seam=horizon v101-v104/v190; only the polarization signature). (1) [E] the coupling is a compiler number: beta_BH(r) = Q_e^eff Q_m^eff/(256 pi^4 r^2) = 16 c3^4 (Q_e Q_m/r^2), with 16 c3^4 = 1/(256 pi^4) EXACTLY (c3=1/8pi), no free coupling. (2) [E] alpha-kernel cross-link: 16 c3^4 = delta_top/3 with delta_top = 48 c3^4 = 3/(256 pi^4), the SAME top-form coefficient that fixes the alpha-kernel precision-zone correction (one row from beta_rad=phi0/4pi) -- EHT polarimetry probes the same admissibility data as the alpha row. (3) [C] TFPT fixes the 1/r^2 profile, achromaticity, and sign-flip under E.B reversal; the amplitude Q_e Q_m is an MHD/GR weight, not a compiler output. (4) [X] dated kill test: the residual intercept chi_0^res must pass three nulls (frequency/achromatic, spatial 1/r^2, sign-flip); a residual consistent with zero after honest GRMHD subtraction, or failing any null, falsifies THIS channel (not the compiler). Wolfram-mirrored (the coefficient identity is exact)"),
    ("v202_rare_kaon", "the rare kaon sector K -> pi nu nubar from the TFPT CKM point ([C] downstream flavor readout, NOT a compiler power). The kernel fixes the full CKM matrix (s12=lambda_C, s23=phi0/(1+lambda_C)=|V_cb|, s13=lambda_C^3/3, delta=pi/3+3 lambda_C^2=1.19823 rad, v18/v88) with no flavor fit; feeding the exact point into the standard Brod-Gorbahn-Stamou short-distance formulas gives BR(K+ -> pi+ nu nubar)=9.45e-11 and BR(K_L -> pi0 nu nubar)=3.33e-11. (1) [I] the CKM point + exact apex (rhobar,etabar)=(0.1374,0.3509) and lambda_t=V_ts* V_td. (2) [C] the branching ratios -- NOT parameter-free, the SD functions X_t=1.462, P_c, kappa_pm are external electroweak/QCD input (recomputed from the CURRENT CKM point; an earlier scaffold's BR(K_L)=3.47e-11 had an Im(lambda_t)/lambda^5 slip, corrected to 3.33e-11). (3) [N] BR(K+)=9.45e-11 lands ON the NA62 full 2016-2024 combination (9.6 +1.9/-1.8)e-11 (La Thuile 2026), +0.08 sigma (the 2016-2022 obs (13.0 +3.3/-3.0)e-11 was ~1.2 sigma above); a strong consistency hit, but an F_transfer bridge, NOT a unique TFPT-vs-SM discriminator (SM (8.6+-0.4)e-11 is also inside the NA62 error). (4) [I] Grossman-Nir ratio BR(K_L)/BR(K+)=0.352 << 4.3 (isospin corridor). (5) [X] dated kill test: a stable NA62 BR(K+) outside [7,12]e-11, or a KOTO-II BR(K_L) off the GN-plane point, breaks the TFPT flavor bridge for this sector (compiler core untouched); the ~2 sigma delta_CKM tension makes the corridor discriminating"),
    ("v201_seam_subprincipal_marks", "QGEO.SUBPRIN.01: the v199 bedrock residual reduced one genuine step further. v199 localised omega o rho=omega to 'the bounded sub-principal symbol of the raw seam DtN has no off-character (mod 4) matrix elements'. Here block-diagonality is shown NOT to be an independent postulate: (1) [E] the DtN is Lambda=|k|+M_f with M_f = multiplication by a curvature function f(theta) on the seam circle (standard Steklov sub-principal structure), so <n|M_f|n'>=f_{n-n'}. (2) [E] M_f is mu4-character-block-diagonal <=> f has Fourier support only on modes ≡0 (mod 4) <=> f is Z4-invariant; the principal |k| already commutes (v198). (3) [E] a mu4-MARK SUM f(theta)=sum_{j=0}^3 g(theta-2pi j/4) has f_m=4 g_m[m≡0 mod 4] for ANY profile g -- automatically Z4-invariant, hence block-diagonal; so (v195 marks=mu4 orbit) FORCES the sub-principal symbol block-diagonal. (4) [E] negative controls: 3 equally-spaced marks (Z3) and 4 generic unequal marks both break the commutator -- specific to mu4. (5) [O] NEW RESIDUAL: omega o rho=omega reduces to 'the DtN sub-principal symbol is MARK-LOCAL (seam flat away from the mu4 marks = the conformal-deck structure v177)' -- given it, v195 => Z4-invariant sub-principal => block-diagonal => [rho,H_1]=0 => omega o rho=omega. A genuine reduction; the residual is now structurally definitional (conformal-deck flatness), the narrowest form yet of QGEO.SYM.01"),
    ("v210_mark_local_dtn", "a numerical SHARPENING of v201/QGEO.SUBPRIN.01 on REALISTIC Steklov curvature profiles, carried to the quasi-free STATE level (the actual omega o rho = omega, not just [rho,Lambda]=0); NOT a closure of QGEO.SYM.01. v201 argued at the abstract mode level; here a real von-Mises curvature bump g(theta) localised at a puncture, summed over the four mu4 marks f(theta)=sum_{j=0}^3 g(theta-j pi/2), builds the Steklov DtN Lambda=|D_theta|+M_f. (1) [E] MARK-SUM FOURIER SUPPORT: every off-(mod 4) Fourier coefficient of the REAL f vanishes to <1e-16 (exact 4-fold cancellation), although g itself has all modes. (2) [N] OPERATOR COMMUTATOR: ||[rho,Lambda]||<1e-15. (3) [N] STATE INVARIANCE (new vs v201): the quasi-free covariance C=1/2(1+sgn H_1) satisfies rho C rho^dag = C to <1e-13 and [rho,C]<1e-13 -- the STATE, not just the operator, is clock-invariant. (4) [N] NEGATIVE CONTROLS (realistic profiles): a single off-centre bump, a Z3 (3-mark) source and 4 generic unequal marks each break BOTH the operator and the state invariance by O(1) -- specific to the mu4 orbit. (5) [N] CONVERGENCE: mark-local commutator stays <1e-10 for N in {16,32,64}; the Z3 control stays O(1) -- not a truncation artefact. (6) [O] VERDICT: numerically certifies 'mark-local DtN => omega o rho = omega' for concrete profiles AND at the state level (the operational content of QGEO.SUBPRIN.01); the PREMISE that the physical seam IS mark-local stays [O] -- the narrowest definitional form of QGEO.SYM.01, NOT its closure (net existence + full-cone RP remain the [E] of v175). Python-only (numerical; the exact mark-sum identity is Wolfram-mirrored via v201)"),
    ("v211_axion_spine_angle", "axion DM, the spine-angle branch theta_i = pi N_fam/g_car = 3 pi/5 (108 deg): an ALTERNATIVE, more ROBUST misalignment angle than the determinant-line hilltop theta_i~170 deg (v185, which over-produces Omega_a h^2~0.66). A [C] kill-test branch, NOT a closure. (1) [I] RATIONAL MOTIVE: theta_i = pi N_fam/g_car = 3 pi/5 = 108 deg exactly (spine quotient 3/5, no fit). (2) [N] ON TARGET: the v185 full finite-T solver (theta=1 -> 0.03) reaches Omega_DM at theta~106 deg; 108 deg is essentially there, harmonic estimate 0.03 theta^2 = 0.107 (right order), mild anharmonic lifts to ~0.12. (3) [C] ROBUST: 108 deg is 62 deg BELOW the 170 deg hilltop, in the MILD-anharmonic regime -- NOT exponentially sensitive, a far more robust landing than v185; if theta_i is the spine quotient the axion is all of DM without tuning. (4) [O] HONEST: theta_i=3 pi/5 (spine) and theta_i=pi(1-phi_seam)~170 deg (seam-value, v185) are MUTUALLY EXCLUSIVE; neither forced, the full solver decides (DM.AXION.SPINE.01) -- a sharper scenario, not a derivation. (5) [X] KILL TEST: full finite-T solve at theta_i=3 pi/5, f_a=M_scal/128, N_DW=1; Omega_a h^2 outside ~[0.08,0.16] demotes the spine branch. Python-only"),
    ("v212_leptogenesis_decuple", "leptogenesis, the scalaron-decuple branch: BOTH Boltzmann inputs share the decuple A_Lambda=10=|E(K5)| -- M_1 = M_scal phi0^2/A_Lambda ~ 8.65e9 GeV and m~_1 = m_3/A_Lambda ~ 5 meV. A cleaner [C] route than v184's M_1=M_R phi0^4 (which only RELOCATED the free input to the un-pinned seesaw M_R). (1) [I] SHARED DECUPLE: A_Lambda=10 divides both inputs (scalaron reheating dressed by two seed insertions phi0^2, over the pair sector). (2) [N] HEAVY MASS: M_1 = M_scal phi0^2/A_Lambda = 8.65e9 GeV (M_scal=c3^{7/2} Mbar~3.06e13, phi0~0.053172) -- inside the thermal window [3e9,3e10] (v169), above the Davidson-Ibarra floor. (3) [N] WASHOUT: m~_1 = m_3/A_Lambda ~ 5 meV (m_3~0.05 eV), K~4.6 strong washout, same A_Lambda. (4) [N] eta_B: Davidson-Ibarra eps_1=(3/16pi)M_1 m_3/v^2~8.5e-7, kappa_f~0.15, eta_B~0.96e-2 eps_1 kappa_f = 1.2e-9 -- O(1e-9) brackets the observed 6.1e-10 (v169 band), no tuning. (5) [C] HONEST: M_1 uses ONLY {M_scal,phi0,A_Lambda} (no hidden seesaw scale, both inputs share A_Lambda), but the coupling MECHANISM is posited not derived; eta_B stays [C], a sharper scenario. (6) [X] KILL TEST: a precise flavored-Boltzmann/RGE solve outside the observed band falls the ROUTE, not the theory (Route A / Omega_b independent, FR.ETAB.01). Python-only"),
    ("v213_ftransfer_functor", "the F_transfer FUNCTOR CONTRACT (CONTRACT.F.01): the four frontier transfers are ONE typed functor F_transfer = F_observable o F_threshold o F_RG with FOUR structural axioms, each instance a DISCRETE compiler kernel [E/I] composed with an EXTERNAL continuous solver [C/O]. Consolidates v183 (F_pole), v212 (F_Boltzmann), v211 (F_relic), v164/FR.MPME (F_QCD) under one contract; the structural complement of the v187 typing GUARD. (1) [I] AXIOM 1 mu4-DECK EQUIVARIANCE: the Koide multiplier lambda_2=(2/3)^6=64/729 IS the mu4-deck transfer eigenvalue (deck fixes the branch divisor, v82/v54); discrete kernels built from {|mu4|=4, N_fam=3, g_car=5, A_Lambda=10}. (2) [I] AXIOM 2 PLUCKER PRESERVATION: dimensionless readouts are Plucker readings -- Koide 53=a^T(R+Q)1 (F-corner Pl(F)=(1,22,30)), quark ratio ||Pl(K)||_1=11. (3) [I] AXIOM 3 POSITIVITY/STOCHASTICITY: spec(T)={1,(2/3)^6,(1/3)^6} positive (RP/OS), washout kappa_f in (0,1), Omega_a>0. (4) [I] AXIOM 4 EXTERNAL MODULES EXPLICIT: each instance's continuous content is a named external module (pole transfer, DNN Boltzmann, finite-T chi(T), lattice C_N), never a compiler number; b3=-7 a carrier output (|b3|=11-(2/3)(2 N_fam)=Omega_adm-10 b1=48-41=7). (5) [C] VERDICT: F_transfer is a typed functor with 4 axioms, NOT a bag of open topics; discrete kernels [E]/[I], external solvers [C]/[O]; an architectural consolidation guarded by v187, NOT a closure of any frontier number. Python-only (the exact discrete sub-parts 53/54, (2/3)^6, the F-corner Plucker are Wolfram-mirrored via v94/v183)"),
    ("v214_seam_pillowcase", "QGEO.PILLOW.01: the Pillowcase reduction of QGEO.SYM.01 -- the two separately-tracked open QGEO residuals (v180/QGEO.ISO.01 'the carrier clock is an order-4 ISOMETRY of the seam metric' and v201/QGEO.SUBPRIN.01 'the DtN sub-principal symbol is MARK-LOCAL, seam flat away from the mu4 marks') are ONE statement -- the seam carries the uniformising flat orbifold ('pillowcase') metric -- and the order-4 clock is DERIVED from cross-ratio 2 (v168), not assumed. A genuine reduction + unification, NOT a closure. (1) [E] EUCLIDEAN ORBIFOLD: chi_orb(S^2(2,2,2,2))=2-4(1-1/2)=0 => flat (Troyanov cone-metric uniformisation, unique up to scale); Gauss-Bonnet 4 cone deficits pi sum to 4pi=2pi chi(S^2) => int K_smooth=0 (flat away from marks = the v201 conformal-deck residual). (2) [E] NEW LINK cross-ratio 2 => j=1728: mu4 has cross-ratio 2 (v168); j(lambda)=256(l^2-l+1)^3/(l^2(l-1)^2), j(2)=1728, all six harmonic cross-ratios {2,-1,1/2} give 1728 => the square modulus (hence the order-4 clock) is a CONSEQUENCE of cross-ratio 2. (3) [E/L] j=1728 <=> tau=i square torus <=> CM by Z[i] <=> Aut=Z/4 (only other exceptional modulus j=0/tau=rho gives Z/6; generic Z/2). (4) [E] explicit order-4 CM: on y^2=x^3-x the map (x,y)->(-x,iy) negates the polynomial (same zero locus) and has order 4 = the z->iz isometry. (5) [E] NEG CONTROL: generic cross-ratio lambda=3 gives j=21952/9 not in {0,1728} => Aut=Z/2, no order-4 clock -- specific to mu4. (6) [I] UNIFICATION: 'seam = uniformising flat pillowcase metric' implies BOTH v201 mark-locality AND v180 QGEO.ISO.01 -- two residuals collapse to ONE canonical-metric statement. (7) [O] HONEST: does NOT close QGEO.SYM.01 -- the premise 'RP seam metric = the uniformising constant-curvature representative' stays open, milder/more canonical than the bare isometry premise; net existence + full-cone RP remain v175's [E]. Exact parts Wolfram-mirrored; Klein-J values mpmath-numerical"),
    ("v215_seam_deck_killtest", "QGEO.KILL.01: the bedrock QGEO.SYM.01 (omega o rho = omega) recast as a FALSIFIABLE structural kill-test, not a proof-promise (a foundational symmetry cannot be derived from nothing, v181/v153). The non-circular reduction (v198/v199/v201): for a quasi-free seam state omega o rho=omega <=> [rho,C]=0; the principal symbol |k|=diag(|n|) commutes with rho=diag(i^n) exactly (v198), so the residual sits in the bounded sub-principal M_f, and [rho,M_f]=0 <=> f has Fourier support only on modes ≡0 (mod 4); measure form: the raw Gaussian bulk form A is mu4-deck-invariant. Four falsifiable levers (carrier-side GREEN, seam-side DEFERRED): (1) [E] K1 EXACTLY FOUR MARKS -- order-4 clock (Coxeter of W(A3)=S4) free orbit mu4 + rank H^1 = #marks-1 = 3 = N_fam => #marks=4=|mu4|=e1(a); KILL if #marks!=4 (b1!=3). (2) [E] K2 SQUARE CONFIG -- cross-ratio 2 => j=1728 (square tau=i, Aut=Z/4); clock order h(A3)=4 selects Z/4 not the j=0 Z/6; generic marks (cross-ratio 3 -> j=21952/9) only Z/2; KILL if non-square. (3) [E] K3 MOD-4 SUPPORT -- a mu4-mark sum has f_m=4 g_m[m≡0 mod4], M_f block-diagonal, [rho,M_f]=0, off-character breaks it; KILL if a first-principles seam DtN has off-character sub-principal weight above noise. (4) [E] K4 TRANSFER GAP -- cusp weights {0,1/3,2/3}, transfer eigenvalues (1-w)^6={1,(2/3)^6,(1/3)^6}, gap (2/3)^6=64/729; KILL if gap!=64/729. (5) [E] FREEZE BINDING: freeze_file.csv row 'seam_deck_symmetry' names the four levers (prediction+test locked, v84/v100 discipline). (6) [E] NON-CIRCULAR: rho + CAR algebra carrier-defined, no seam geometry -- NOT Bisognano-Wichmann (which presupposes the covariance it should produce). (7) [O] DEFERRED EMERGENCE TEST (QGEO.REALIZE.01): the decisive kill = compute the raw P1 collar DtN WITHOUT inputting the marks and check 4 square marks EMERGE; no first-principles raw-seam construction yet, so deferred (like axion_DM 'no test until the scale is closed'); carrier-side K1-K4 are regression guards, seam-side stays [O]. A KILL-TEST, not a closure. Python-only (falsification layer like v65/v100; exact sub-parts already Wolfram-mirrored via v214/v54/v56)"),
    ("v216_marks_gauss_bonnet", "QGEO.MARKS.03: the FOUR marks EMERGE from Gauss-Bonnet, not by hand -- an independent (Euclidean-orbifold) derivation that EXECUTES the K1 lever of the v215 kill-test. (1) [E] MARK COUNT = 2 chi: Z2 branch points (cone angle pi, deficit pi) on a flat sphere (chi=2) give n*pi = 2pi*chi = 4pi => n = 2 chi = 4 = |mu4| = e1(a) = N_fam+1 (the SAME chi=2 as the 8 in c3=1/(|Z2| 2pi chi)=1/(8pi)). (2) [E] exactly FOUR Euclidean sphere orbifolds chi_orb=0: (2,3,6),(2,4,4),(3,3,3),(2,2,2,2) (n<=4). (3) [E] ALL-ORDER-2 (the |Z2| sheet branch) selects (2,2,2,2) uniquely. (4) [E] N_fam=3 selects it: rank H^1=#marks-1=3 only for (2,2,2,2); the 3-mark orbifolds give 2 families -- the 3 generations pick the 4-mark square over the 3-mark hexagonal (3,3,3); family count and mark count are ONE fact. (5) [E] the free order-4 deck selects it: only (2,2,2,2) admits a free order-4 rotation of the marks ((2,4,4) order-4 fixes its cone points, (3,3,3)=Z3, (2,3,6)=Z6) -- three independent criteria converge. (6) [O] residual: (2,2,2,2) has a 1-param modulus; the SQUARE (cross-ratio 2 => j=1728, v214) needs the one order-4 carrier input. So the mark COUNT + EQUALITY are now DERIVED (K1 executed); only the square modulus stays input -- does NOT close QGEO.REALIZE.01. Exact (sympy enumeration + Gauss-Bonnet solve); Wolfram-mirrored"),
    ("v217_marks_emergence_scan", "QGEO.EMERGE.01: the NUMERICAL emergence scan (sibling of v216, as v210 is to v201) -- with the NUMBER of marks n AND their POSITIONS free, the 4-equally-spaced (square) configuration is the joint minimiser of {clock-invariance + 3-family cohomology + transfer gap (2/3)^6} on the actual seam DtN/state. (1) [N] CLOCK-INVARIANCE: n=4 equally-spaced marks give ||rho_4 C rho_4^dag - C|| ~ 1e-14 (the quasi-free state is clock-invariant). (2) [N] FAMILY COUNT selects n=4: scanning n in {2..8}, only n-1=3=N_fam (n=3->2 families = hexagonal, excluded; n=5->4) -- the number is not input. (3) [N] GAP: a mu4-equivariant operator is forced diagonal in the cusp basis (deck-average off-diagonal ~1e-16 for V=diag(i,-1,-i)), cusp weights {0,1/3,2/3} => transfer (1-w)^6={1,(2/3)^6,(1/3)^6}, gap (2/3)^6=64/729 (only the 3-dim n=4 block carries the three weights). (4) [N] POSITION SCAN: among 4-mark configs the square minimises the defect (square ~1e-14 vs off-square ~0.4). (5) [N] NEGATIVE CONTROLS: n=3 (Z3/hexagonal) -> 2 families + breaks the order-4 clock; n=5,6 wrong count -- 4-square is the unique joint winner. (6) [O] numerically confirms the emergence on the real DtN (number scanned, positions free), selector = 3-family/gap structure (carrier input); executes K1 numerically but does NOT close QGEO.REALIZE.01 (order-4/N_fam stays irreducible, v153/v181); complements v216. Python-only"),
    ("v218_diamond_axis_geometry", "the DIAMOND AXIS GEOMETRY: the Sheet Diamond (v94) is a discrete geometry with TWO axes around the centered cross (v95: C center, U winding, V sheet), and the missing corner F is the transfer completion. Three exact [I] lemmas + honest audit/heuristic typing, NO new numbers. (1) [I] AXIS CURVATURE: det(C+xU)=14+6x LINEAR (winding flat, slope 6=|R^+(A3)|); det(C+yV)=14+14y+4y^2 QUADRATIC, 2nd diff=8=rank E8; det B(C+xU)=28+12x=2 det(C+xU); anchor-block sheet 2nd diff=6=|R^+(A3)| -- two curvatures (8 det, 6 anchor)=(rank E8, |R^+(A3)|). (2) [I] PLUECKER TRANSFER LADDER: Pl(K)=(-1,6,4)->Pl(C)=(0,14,14)->Pl(F)=(1,22,30); C-K=(1,8,10)=(N_Phi,rank E8,A_Lambda), F-C=(1,8,16)=(N_Phi,rank E8,dim S+) -- each step adds (1,8), the third the decuple 10 then the full generation 16 (identity [I], source->pole reading [C]). (3) [I] SPECTRAL RAMIFICATION: for Q,K,C,F the cubic discriminant = q(r)^2 Disc(q); squares |q(r)|=(1,3,4,6)=(N_Phi,N_fam,|mu4|,|R^+(A3)|), kernels Disc(q)=(13,48,65,105)=(Delta_Q,Omega_adm,g_car Delta_Q,N_fam g_car 7), Delta_Q=13=|R(A3)|+1 (v14); F carries 105=3*5*7=family*carrier*scalaron. (4) [I] AUDIT anchor-defect spectrum Delta_a(Q,K,R,C,L,F)=(8,16,18,21,24,26) monotone in the det ordering (26=2*13 spectral Delta_Q, NOT Delta_a(Q)=8; cleaned notation); spine only if the six operators are canonical/complete. (5) [I] AUDIT pair-sum atlas {12,24,28,36,40,52} total 64=dim S+ |mu4|, det staircase sum 81=N_fam^4 steps (1,4,6,6,12) -- 28=2 dim G2 and 52=dim F4 are exotic AUDIT-only labels, NOT spine (same typing as v94/v95). (6) [C] HEURISTIC F=transfer completion corner (det F=32=2^g_car, a^T F 1=53=sum Pl(F)) -- a search principle ONLY, NOT a hard admissibility filter (cf. v94 firewall rejection). Python-only (exact identities mirrored in wolfram extension)"),
    ("v198_modular_commutator_reduction", "QGEO.MODULAR.01: cracking the bedrock one decisive level further. The v194 residual (the full-L^2 commutator [rho,Lambda_Sigma]=0, framed as Bisognano-Wichmann with a circularity worry) is (a) made EXACT at the principal-symbol level and (b) reduced via Tomita-Takesaki to a clean STATE-INVARIANCE, removing the circularity. (1) [E] the DtN principal symbol |k|=sqrt(-d^2/dtheta^2) (Lee-Uhlmann, v156) is diag(|n|) and rho:z|->iz is diag(i^n) in the Fourier basis -- both diagonal => [rho,|k|]=0 EXACTLY on ALL of L^2 (not just H^1); the leading-order commutation is FREE on the whole boundary. (2) [E] Tomita-Takesaki: the modular operator Delta_omega is intrinsic to (M,Omega), so a state-preserving symmetry (rho Omega=Omega) commutes with Delta hence with log Delta ~ Lambda_Sigma => [rho,Lambda_Sigma]=0 FOLLOWS from omega o rho = omega, needing ONLY the state+reflection (RP), NO conformal covariance -- the v194 BW circularity is REMOVED. (3) [E] on H^1 the covariance is mu4-equivariant (v177), so omega o rho = omega already holds on the finite block. (4) [O] the irreducible residual: the FULL raw quasi-free seam state is rho-invariant (omega o rho = omega) <= the Gaussian bulk measure is rho(deck)-invariant = the mu4 deck is a symmetry of the raw seam -- the maximally-operational, non-circular form of QGEO.SYM.01 (a STATE/MEASURE invariance, checkable). VERDICT [O]: bedrock cracked to omega o rho = omega; principal symbol exact, non-circular, finite block invariant; NOT a full closure (a foundational symmetry cannot be derived from nothing) but the sharpest falsifiable form, circularity gone"),
    ("v195_marks_lefschetz_character", "QGEO.MARKS.02: a Lefschetz/character derivation of the four seam marks (external-review path 2). Instead of POSITING D4 marks, they are FORCED to be a free mu4 orbit by orbit-counting + the H^1 character: (1) [E] rho:z|->iz (order 4) fixes exactly {0,infinity}, so points off it have free order-4 orbits; (2) [E] H^1=chi_1+chi_2+chi_3 (A3 exponents (1,2,3), v177) has NO trivial character => no puncture at a fixed point; (3) [E] rank H_1=n-1=3 => n=4 punctures => exactly ONE free orbit => marks = mu4 ~ {1,i,-1,-i} (cross-ratio 2); (4) [E] Lefschetz consistency Tr(rho|H^1)=i+i^2+i^3=-1, L(rho)=1+1=2=#fixed pts. RESIDUAL [O]: now 'H^1 carries the A3-exponent rep' (a carrier-algebra premise) instead of 'the seam is P^1\\mu4 (geometric)' -- less circular, still [O] at the carrier<->seam link"),
    ("v196_seam_energy_functional", "QGEO.VARI.01: the E_fail variational functional (external-review path 1), a concrete numerically-testable sharpening of the v194/ENERGY.02 target: E_fail = ||[rho,Lambda_Sigma]||^2_HS + ||rho^4-1||^2 + ||Theta rho Theta - rho^{-1}||^2, with E_fail=0 <=> the QGEO.SYM.01 conditions. (1) [E] on the finite H^1 block (rho=diag(i,-1,-i), Lambda diagonal, Theta=conj) all three terms vanish => E_fail=0; (2) [N] a mu4-breaking off-diagonal Lambda or a non-order-4 rho gives E_fail>0 (mu4 is a true minimiser); (3) [I] the zero locus = the seam-deck conditions (commutator + order-4 + RP twist); (4) [O] the FULL-operator minimisation (beyond H^1) is exactly the v194 Bisognano-Wichmann residual -- E_fail is a discretisable handle on the open bedrock, a target not a closure"),
    ("v197_rr_carrier_clifford_d5", "ARCH.RRCAR.02: hardening the Riemann-Roch carrier from g_car to D5 itself (external-review point 7). v189 read g_car=5=h^0(P^1,O(mu4)) and matched rank(D5); this goes further: the 5-dim carrier mode space C_car:=H^0(P^1,O(mu4)) generates the so(10)=D5 half-spinor by its even Clifford algebra, Lambda^even(C_car)=S^+, dim=C(5,0)+C(5,2)+C(5,4)=1+10+5=16=2^{g_car-1}=dim_Splus. (1)[I] even Clifford dim 16; (2)[I] so(10)=D5 half-spinor 2^4=16=S^+=Lambda^even(C_car); (3)[I] closes the chain mu4->g_car->D5 from one four-point divisor (cycle side rank H_1=3=N_fam(A3); function side h^0=5=g_car; Clifford spinor=16=D5 half-spinor=carrier); (4)[C] the identification 'carrier = Clifford spinor of the seam mode space' stays physical [C] (as v189), does not change the over-determined g_car=5"),
    ("v194_raw_seam_dtn_rp", "QGEO.DTN.01: subclaim 2 of QGEO.ENERGY.02 ('the raw RP-seam DtN is RP-definable') tackled -- a REDUCTION, not a closure. (1) [E] FINITE CORE: rho:z|->iz acts on H^1=<w1,w2,w3>, wk=z^{k-1}dz/(z^4-1), as rho* wk = i^k wk (characters i,-1,-i distinct; (iz)^4-1=z^4-1 invariant), so any operator commuting with rho is diagonal on H^1 and the harmonic structure is rho-equivariant there (v177) => [rho,Lambda_Sigma]=0 on H^1. (2) [I] HINGE MET: the DtN/transfer operator is RP-canonical (Osterwalder-Schrader gives T=e^{-H} from the RP state + reflection alone, v54/tfpt_2(4)) on a quasi-free seam state (v155: boundary marginal of a Gaussian bulk = compression P Gamma P, a contraction), so Lambda_Sigma is RP-definable WITHOUT choosing P^1\\mu4 -- subclaim 2's non-circularity hinge is essentially met. (3) [O] RESIDUAL RELOCATES: [rho,Lambda_Sigma]=0 on the FULL L^2 (beyond the 3-dim H^1) <=> the quasi-free seam state's modular flow is GEOMETRIC (Bisognano-Wichmann); BW must be established INTRINSICALLY (from RP+quasi-free alone) or it re-circulates (BW normally presupposes conformal covariance). VERDICT [O]: QGEO.SYM.01 REDUCES from a definitional postulate to 'intrinsic BW geometric modular covariance of the quasi-free seam state' -- one notch sharper, still [O]; the last fog point sharpens, does NOT close to [E]"),
    ("v193_qgeo_energy_commutator", "QGEO.ENERGY.02: the energy-COMMUTATOR contract (external-review proposal, the non-circular sharpening of QGEO.ENERGY.01): the operator identity [rho, Lambda_Sigma]=0 on the rank-8 Calderon polarisation, rho the carrier clock, Lambda_Sigma the DtN/Calderon energy form of the RAW RP seam. Strictly sharper than ENERGY.01 via three sub-claims: (1) [E] rho is carrier-defined (Coxeter element of W(A3)=S4, order 4=|mu4|, v117), NOT imported from the seam; (2) [O] THE NON-CIRCULARITY HINGE -- Lambda_Sigma must be the RAW RP-seam DtN (definable from RP data alone), not the mu4 normal form; if it needs P^1\\mu4 assumed it is circular, if from RP data alone the commutator is a genuine rigidity statement; (3) [E] [rho,Lambda_Sigma]=0 forces the mu4 character grading (1,2,3) on H^1, already established (QGEO.COHOM.01, v177). Plus an EXACT [I] EH-rigidity consistency: the induced k=(ln m)/(12 pi) (v150) reproduces c3/2=1/(16 pi) iff ln m=q(A3)=3/4 (FAMILY norm), NOT q(D5)=5/4 (carrier, off by g_car/N_fam=5/3) -- the energy form must reproduce the family norm. VERDICT [O]: a PROOF TARGET, not a proof; if proven, QGEO.SYM.01 becomes an energy-rigidity theorem; bedrock stays [O] until sub-claim 2 holds"),
    ("v192_qgeo_energy_clock", "the energy-conserving-clock reformulation (external-review point 7), HONESTLY typed: QGEO.ENERGY.01 (rho^* Lambda_Sigma rho = Lambda_Sigma, the carrier clock preserves the Calderon/DtN energy form) RELOCATES the bedrock postulate QGEO.SYM.01 to a more operationally checkable operator identity, but does NOT eliminate it. The downstream chain (conformality -> Moebius -> z|->iz -> mu4 -> QGEO.SYM.01) already exists (v180/v181); the new upstream link (energy invariance => conformality in 2D) is checkable on the DtN operator Lambda=|k|. But 'rho preserves Lambda' is plausibly EQUIVALENT to 'rho is the conformal deck', so it is a sharper RESTATEMENT, not a theorem, unless rho is independently defined and the invariance independently proven (open). The bedrock stays [O] -- same pattern as v179->v181 (each step sharpens but cannot remove the premise)"),
    ("v188_frontier_wording_guard", "the frontier-wording guard (a prose sentinel, no new physics): v187 protects the ledger typing, this guard protects the PROSE. It forbids stale sentences whose semantics an earlier round superseded -- 'leptogenesis interface (mE)' (v184 retyped Route B to [C]), 'closed branch also fixes the leptogenesis inputs' (M_R is the seesaw scale, not a compiler power), 'relic scale f_a,m_a open' (v185: the scales DEFINE the branch, the open item is the hilltop-sensitive relic abundance), 'computed Q=0.664 ... near, not exact' (v183 gave the 53/54 factor an exact operator origin), 'Suite now 187 modules' (the count is 187, highest ID v188; v186 skipped), and the old determinant-line axion mass '64.36' ueV (the superseded small-angle theta_i=phi0 reading; the current closed reading is theta_i=170.4 deg, f_a=M_scal/128, m_a~23.8 ueV). Scans the 10 active .tex documents; PASSES when none of the stale phrasings appear, so a frozen Zenodo release can never re-introduce wording that was true yesterday and is half-true today"),
    ("v187_ftransfer_laws", "the F_transfer discipline guard (CI-style firewall): the four continuous-transfer frontier observables (Koide FR.KOIDE.*, eta_B FR.ETAB.*, axion FR.DM.*, m_p/m_e FR.MPME.*/QCD.LAMBDA.*) must NEVER be typed as primitive [E]/[N] compiler predictions -- each must carry a [C]/[A]/[O] marker. Reads the ledger and enforces it (all 13 active frontier rows pass; exact algebraic sub-parts like Koide 53/54 or b3=-7 may be [I]/[E], the physical prediction never is). Records the four explicit interfaces F_pole/F_Boltzmann/F_relic/F_QCD and that the raster rule + frozen registry + null model bind. Prevents any future edit from quietly promoting a 'pretty frontier number' to a closed compiler output"),
    ("v183_koide_f_corner_transfer", "the Koide source->pole factor 53/54 has an OPERATOR origin (external-review proposal, validated; upgrades FR.KOIDE.03 from '1-1/(2 N_fam^3)' to an operator identity on the carrier): u_pole/u_source = a^T(R+Q)1 / (2*1^T R a) = 53/(2*27) = 53/54. (1) 1^T R a = 27 is the E6xA2 cubic family block (248 = dim E6 78 + det R 8 + 2*27*N_fam); (2) F = R+Q is the MISSING Sheet-Diamond corner M(1,1) with det B_F = 52 = dim F4 (v80) and anchor response a^T(R+Q)1 = 53 = 52+1; (3) the ratio 53/54 matches 1-1/(2 N_fam^3) exactly (54=2*27=2 N_fam^3); (4) NEGATIVE CONTROL: only F gives 53 (R/Q/K/L give 32/21/35/56). [I] the factor is exact; [C] the physical mechanism (leptonic source->pole reads the F corner) stays an F_transfer conjecture. Cross-ref HOR.TRISECT.01 (same double-cover grammar, gravity clock)"),
    ("v182_reviewer_residual_map", "the four external-review concerns (A mapping 2D->4D, B UV-gravity abstractness, C grammar-tuning/meta-look-elsewhere, D Koide Mobius flow) do NOT add four independent open gaps: three reduce, by the same honest-reduction discipline, onto the two ALREADY-named residuals {QGEO.SYM.01 (seam realisation), F_transfer (transfer functor)}, and the fourth is the single experiment-only item. A [I]/[C]: the Plucker-11 readout is the QBL boundary count (11=sum_{k<=2}C(4,k)=dim S+ - g_car=16-5, v174); the 2D->4D step is the holographic reduction -> A = QGEO.SYM.01 + F_transfer. B [I]: 'gravity = geometric boundary readout' IS QGEO.SYM.01 itself. C [N]/[C]: frozen (v84) + minimal + over-determined (the anchor a=(1,1,2) lands in >=6 independent not-selected-for structures: Nariai (1,1,-2), Coxeter-30, spine, EM 41, seed 4/3, c3) -> look-elsewhere-resistant, but residual falls only to data (JUNO/CMB-S4). D [I]/[C]: the Mobius nature is forced by Aut(P^1)=PSL(2,C) on the deck P^1\\mu4, t~2.84 just locates the point, the missing RG generator IS F_transfer -> D = QGEO.SYM.01 + F_transfer. NET: three reduce, one waits for data; a unification of the concern structure, NOT a closure (premises stay [O]/[C])"),
    ("v181_clock_is_conformal_symmetry", "the FINAL honest reduction + the explicit identification of BEDROCK: the isometry premise QGEO.ISO.01 (v180) is weakened one more genuine step -- to a CONFORMAL-symmetry premise QGEO.SYM.01 -- via equivariant uniformisation (Nielsen realisation, finite cyclic on genus-0): a CONFORMAL automorphism (strictly weaker than an isometry: every isometry is conformal, conformal allows any positive scale) already suffices to put the order-4 clock in the form z->iz. The clock is the Coxeter element of W(A3)=S4 (v117), order h(A3)=4=|mu4|, i.e. the mu4 deck, and a deck transformation preserves the pulled-back conformal structure by definition. So below QGEO.SYM.01 the residual is DEFINITIONAL, not a missing theorem: 'the seam's conformal structure IS the mu4-deck structure of the carrier clock' (the carrier mu4 glue is the conformal monodromy of the seam) -- a physical/definitional identification tying P2 to the seam's conformal geometry, NOT reducible further without relabeling. The reduction chain REALIZE(v175)->theorem(v176)->MARKS+KERNEL(v177)->finite cores(v178)->CONF.01(v179)->ISO.01(v180)->SYM.01(v181) has reached bedrock; we stop here honestly"),
    ("v180_clock_is_mobius", "cracking QGEO.CONF.01 one level further: the conformal-realisation premise is REPLACED, via three classical theorems, by a strictly MILDER, non-circular premise QGEO.ISO.01 -- 'the carrier clock is an order-4 orientation-preserving ISOMETRY of the RP seam metric'. (1) UNIFORMISATION (Poincare-Koebe): a genus-0 Riemann surface is conformally P^1, so the genus-0 seam double (P1, v179) with its RP-metric conformal structure IS P^1 -- the target is PRODUCED, not assumed; (2) KEREKJARTO (1919; Constantin-Kolev 2003): a finite-order orientation-preserving homeo of S^2 is conjugate to a rotation, so the order-4 clock (h(A3)=4) is topologically z->iz; (3) ISOMETRY=>CONFORMAL=>MOEBIUS: an orientation-preserving isometry of a Riemannian surface is holomorphic, Aut(P^1)=PSL(2,C); (4) ORDER-4 MOEBIUS = z->iz (verified: projective order 4, fixed {0,inf}, multiplier i, free orbit mu4). So QGEO.CONF.01 is IMPLIED by the milder isometry premise; the new residual QGEO.ISO.01 (the seam transport is a metric-compatible holonomy preserving the RP inner product) does NOT name P^1/mu4 and is milder, but its surface realisation from the raw seam stays OPEN"),
    ("v179_conformal_realisation", "the two residual premises (MARKS-residual + KERNEL-residual) collapse to ONE geometric premise QGEO.CONF.01 (honest unification, the conformal realisation stays OPEN): MARKS's residual decomposes and is NOT three independent assumptions -- (1) genus-0 IS P1 (c3=1/(|Z2|*2pi*chi(S^2))=1/(8pi) with chi(S^2)=2 => g=0, the same chi=2 that supplies the '8'; v58/v73), (2) the order-4 clock IS the carrier (Coxeter element of W(A3)=S4, order h(A3)=4=|mu4|; v117), (3) marks=one orbit is FORCED (parabolic marks != the 2 elliptic fixed points {0,inf}; a free order-4 orbit has exactly 4=e1(a) points) -- so MARKS reduces to 'the carrier clock acts conformally (Moebius) on the genus-0 double'. KERNEL's residual then FOLLOWS from that same geometry: DtN principal symbol |k| (Lee-Uhlmann, v156) => rank-8 c=8 fixed polarisation; no drift (v158); the cusped-surface residual/cusp-form data is H^1=C^3=N_fam = the 3-dim gapped transfer block (Schur, v162/v178). So both residuals = ONE premise QGEO.CONF.01: 'the raw RP seam normal double is conformally (P^1,mu4) with the carrier clock as the order-4 Moebius automorphism'. The two doors of v177/v178 are one geometric realisation; it is the SINGLE structural residual of the whole theory, left honestly OPEN"),
    ("v178_marks_kernel_attempt", "an honest ATTEMPT at the two open obligations QGEO.MARKS.01 + QGEO.KERNEL.01 -- NOT a closure (they are genuine constructive-geometry/AQFT statements, not finite computations), but a deeper reduction: each finite/algebraic CORE is closed [E] and each obligation is reduced to ONE sharper irreducible [O] premise. MARKS finite core [E]: given a genus-0 double with an order-4 clock rho (~z->iz, fixed points {0,inf}) and sheet reflection tau, the marks are a generic rho-orbit {1,i,-1,-i}=mu4 (NOT the fixed points), distinct iff b1=4-1=3=N_fam (collision drops b1, excluded), tau.rho.tau=rho^{-1} => faithful D4 order 8 -- so MARKS reduces to the single topological/clock premise 'the seam double is genus-0 with an order-4 clock whose marks form one orbit'. KERNEL finite core [E]: on the 3-dim multiplicity-free H^1 the mu4 characters (1,2,3) are distinct, so by Schur a mu4-equivariant operator is forced DIAGONAL and completely determined by its eigenvalue per character -- two such with the same forced transfer spectrum {1,(2/3)^6,(1/3)^6} (v162) and the unique residue-normalised basis (v177) are EQUAL as operators (the 'spectrum vs operator' worry vanishes on the finite block); KERNEL reduces to the single full-operator-reduction premise 'the full DtN reduces to this transfer block + the rank-8 fixed polarisation' (principal symbol |k| Lee-Uhlmann v156, no drift v158). NET honest: neither obligation closed; both sharpened to milder premises"),
    ("v177_seam_marking_kernel", "the QGEO proof TREE -- the single 'realisation premise' of v176 is split into its honest constituents: REALIZE = MARKS . UNIFORM . COHOM . MODULE . KERNEL . NET, four nodes now closed CONSTRUCTIVELY as [E] and the open residual sharpened into exactly TWO named obligations. [E] QGEO.UNIFORM.01 (Lemma 2, constructive): an order-4 Moebius map conjugates to z->iz, a non-fixed orbit scales to mu4, the reflection z->1/z gives sigma.rho.sigma=rho^{-1} (D4 order 8) -- a genus-0 4-marked faithful-D4 boundary IS (P^1,mu4); [E] QGEO.COHOM.01: rho* wk = i^k wk so the H^1 character grading is (1,2,3)=A3 exponents=Spec(Q+); [E] QGEO.MODULE.01: the H^1->generation iso is UNIQUE (multiplicity-free + residue normalisation; reflection w1<->w3, w2 fixed); [E] QGEO.NET.01 (v154/v175): index-4 mu4 extension of (D5)1(x)(A3)1 = (E8)1. The TWO genuine open obligations [O]: QGEO.MARKS.01 (raw seam -> genus-0 four-marked D4 boundary) and QGEO.KERNEL.01 (raw seam Calderon kernel = the mu4-equivariant free gapped contraction as an OPERATOR). Removes the near-circular v176 framing (which took MARKS as a hypothesis); the whole structural residual is now exactly these two doors"),
    ("v176_seam_collar_realisation", "the Seam Collar Realisation Theorem assembled as ONE central statement and machine-checked as a REDUCTION certificate (not a fabricated proof): the theorem 'the seam collar's conformal boundary is P^1 minus mu4 with H^1 grading (1,2,3), Calderon contraction = rank-8 K_Sigma, index-4 extension = (E8)1' decomposes into six steps, FIVE of which are already [E] -- geometry/uniformisation (v168: cross-ratio 2, |D4|=8, b1=N_fam=3), Calderon DtN symbol |k| (v156), H^1 character = generation grading (1,2,3)=A3 exponents (v137/v168), mu4-equivariant one-particle contraction diagonal with gap (2/3)^6 (v162), AQFT closure (D5)1(x)(A3)1|x mu4=(E8)1 + full-cone RP all m (v154/v175) -- so the WHOLE structural residual reduces to EXACTLY one open premise: that the physical seam collar's conformal boundary IS this P^1 minus mu4 (QGEO.REALIZE.01), a constructive-geometry statement left honestly OPEN"),

    ("v219_icosahedral_mckay", "MCKAY.E8.01: the McKay BEDROCK lemma -- WHY the three atoms are {2,3,5}. A backward certificate of the already-closed E8 (NOT a P2 proof). E8 is the exceptional TOP of the McKay tower of finite SU(2) subgroups: 2T->affine E6 (h=12), 2O->affine E7 (h=18), 2I (binary icosahedral, order 120)->affine E8 (h=30=2*3*5). The McKay graph is BUILT FROM THE GROUP: (1) [E] the 120 icosians (unit quaternions) close to 2I, element orders {1,2,3,4,5,6,10} -- it CONTAINS the 2,3,5 rotation-axis orders; (2) [E] 9 conjugacy classes = 9 irreps; the irreducible character DEGREES (Dixon, from the class algebra) = {1,2,2,3,3,4,4,5,6}, sum=30=h(E8), sum^2=120=|R^+(E8)|; (3) [E] A_ij=<chiV chi_j,chi_i> from the natural 2-dim rep is the affine E8 adjacency (tree, top eigenvalue 2), Perron marks = the irrep degrees (the McKay correspondence executed numerically); (4) [E] negative controls 2T->E6, 2O->E7 -- only the icosahedral (2,3,5) gives E8. Status: [E] identities, [C] 'explains (2,3,5) as the E8 top', [O] 'raw seam without E8 first' (P2 interface)"),
    ("v220_cp_hexagonal_modulus", "CP.MOD.01: CP lives in the HEXAGONAL phase fiber, not the (square) seam deck -- a geometric sharpening of red-team Target D (the magnitude bijection misses the CP phases). (1) [E] the seam deck is the SQUARE modulus j(i)=1728, automorphism Z/4 (the mu4 clock, v214); (2) [E] its exceptional partner is the HEX modulus j(rho)=0, rho=e^{i pi/3}, automorphism Z/6, CM by Z[omega]; arg(rho)=pi/3 -- a genuine complex phase; (3) [E] the frozen leading CKM reading delta=pi/3+3 lambda_C^2=68.654 deg (v88, registry untouched) has leading term pi/3=arg(rho), the hexagonal CM phase, with 3 lambda_C^2 the seam-misalignment correction; (4) [E] NEG the |Z2| alternative pi/3+2 lambda_C^2 is the frozen look-elsewhere trap (v88). CRITICAL: the seam deck stays Z/4 (v215 kill-test); CP is the Z/6 phase FIBER over it. Status: [E] modular geometry, [C] CP bridge (not a physical CP derivation, does NOT re-select the deck)"),
    ("v221_seam_qecc", "QEC.SEAM.01: the seam as a FINITE recoverability code (recovery rate (2/3)^6=64/729). 'Finite recoverability code' FIRST, 'holographic code' second. (1) [E] code dimension = dim S^+ = 16 = 2^(g_car-1); (2) [E] the gapped transport T on the cusp-weight 3-space (deviation directions (1,-1,0) and the Nariai anchor (1,1,-2)) is symmetric, doubly stochastic (CPTP), spectrum {1,(2/3)^6,(1/3)^6}; (3) [E] CONTRACTION: on the trace-zero deviation subspace ||T delta||/||delta|| <= (2/3)^6, hence ||T^n delta|| <= (2/3)^{6n} ||delta|| (Knill-Laflamme-type per-step recovery bound); (4) [E] NEG a free ratio r!=(2/3)^6 gives r^n (rate not generic); breaking mu4-equivariance destroys it. Status: [E] finite code+spectrum+bound; [C] holographic/Petz identification (gated on the Seam-Horizon theorem). Python-only (numerical contraction bound)"),
    ("v222_cm_norm_duality", "CMNORM.DUAL.01: CM-norm duality -- the two exceptional moduli give 41 (square) and 7 (hex). (1) [E] SQUARE (Gaussian Z[i], j=1728): N(g_car+i|mu4|)=5^2+4^2=41=10 b1 (the EM index IS the Gaussian norm of the carrier-glue vector on the square seam); N(3+2i)=13=Delta_Q; (2) [E] HEX (Eisenstein Z[omega], j=0): N(3+2 omega)=3^2-3*2+2^2=7=scalaron exponent; (3) [E] the (3,2)=(colour,weak) split generates (5,6,7,13)=(g_car,|R^+(A3)|,scalaron,Delta_Q) by sum/product/Eisenstein-norm/Gaussian-norm; (4) [E] NEG the rings are rigid -- Eisenstein norm of (5,4)=21!=41, Gaussian norm of (3,2)=13!=7, only the {2,3} split gives (7,13). Status: [E] ring arithmetic; [C] the architecture bridge 'square<->EM/mu4-clock, hex<->scalaron/CP-phase'"),
    ("v223_coxeter_totative_clock", "COX.CLOCK.01: the mu4 clock is the order-4 character of the E8 Coxeter cycle. (1) [E] (Z/30)^x = {1,7,11,13,17,19,23,29} = the E8 exponents = the live Coxeter phases; phi(30)=8=rank E8, 30=|Z2|*N_fam*g_car=2*3*5; (2) [E] (Z/30)^x ~ Z/4 x Z/2 with order-4 generator 7 (7^2=19, 7^4=1 mod 30): a literal mu4 clock <7>={1,7,13,19} on the exponents; (3) [E] the conjugate pairs m+(30-m)=30 split the 8 phases into |mu4|=4 invariant 2-planes which the order-4 clock permutes; (4) [E] NEG only E8 has phi(h)=rank AND h=2*3*5 (E6: phi(12)=4; E7: 18!=2*3*5). Complements v219 (McKay gives (2,3,5) from the finite group; this gives mu4 from the Coxeter cycle). Status: [E] cycle/character arithmetic, [C] the seam-clock identification"),
    ("v224_diamond_ftransfer_path", "FTR.PATH.01: F_transfer as ONE path on the Sheet Diamond, not four external interfaces. Family M(s,t)=R+Q diag(s,t,t): the transfer corners K=M(1,-1),C=M(1,0),F=M(1,1) sit on the SHEET axis (s=1). (1) [E] the sheet axis is CURVED det M(1,t)=4t^2+14t+14, dets(K,C,F)=(4,14,32), 2nd diff=8=rank E8; the winding axis det M(s,0)=6s+8 is FLAT (slope 6=|R^+(A3)|); (2) [E] PLUECKER LADDER Pl(C)-Pl(K)=(1,8,10)=(N_Phi,rank E8,A_Lambda), Pl(F)-Pl(C)=(1,8,16)=(N_Phi,rank E8,dim S^+) (v218); (3) [C] F_transfer = the K->C->F sheet geodesic, Koide source->pole its 1-D Moebius projection (v37/v183), the external solver evaluates ALONG the known discrete path; (4) [E] NEG the diagonal cut t=s mixes the axes (not branch-preserving). Status: [E] diamond geometry+Plucker ladder, [C] F_transfer identification"),
    ("v225_dual_normal_frame", "DUAL.FRAME.01: the dual normal frame (d,n) -- one boundary compass for flavor + horizon, with CP as orientation. (1) [E] d=a^T R^{-1}=a^T L^{-1}=(-1/2,-1/2,1)=-1/2*(1,1,-2) (frame-independent; the Nariai/horizon normal); d.1=0, d.a=1; (2) [E] n=(5,-9,6): n^T R=(det R,0,0)=(8,0,0), n^T L=(det L,0,0)=(20,0,0) -- n annihilates the stable columns 2,3 (first-generation/torsion selector, v136); (3) [E] oriented volume det(1,d,n)=21=N_fam*scalaron=3*7; (4) [C] CP AS ORIENTATION: Im det(1,d,rho*n)=21 sin(pi/3) for rho=e^{i pi/3} (the hexagonal CM unit, v220) -- CP sits in the orientation of the normal frame, exactly where the magnitude bijection (Target D) fails. Status: [E] normal frame, [C] CP-orientation candidate (not a CP derivation)"),
    ("v227_degree_exponent_channel_split", "E8.CHAN.01: 248=120+128 as a magnitude/phase channel typing (replaces the over-strong 'S^- is dark matter'). (1) [E] E8 exponents {1,7,11,13,17,19,23,29} sum=120=|R^+(E8)| (MAGNITUDE channel: positive roots/root transitions); (2) [E] E8 degrees {2,8,12,14,18,20,24,30} sum=128=2^(rank-1) (PHASE/GLUE channel: the SO(16) half-spinor; =rank E8*dim S^+=8*16); (3) [E] 248=120+128=adj(D8)+spinor(D8); sum(deg)-sum(exp)=rank=8; (4) [C] TYPING: ratios+products (Target D bijection) live in the 120 channel, the un-covered CP phases in the 128 phase/glue channel; (5) [O] whether the 128 channel hosts a dark sector is Frontier, NOT asserted. Status: [E] split, [C] channel typing, [O] dark physics"),
    ("v228_rr_index_gate", "QGEO.RR.01: P2 as the mode space of a degree-4 seam divisor (a Riemann-Roch INDEX GATE; bedrock LANGUAGE for P2, NOT a proof from nothing). (1) [E] deg D=4=|mu4| on P^1 => h0(O(D))=deg+1=5=g_car (Riemann-Roch, genus 0); (2) [E] rank H1(P^1 minus 4 marks)=4-1=3=N_fam (A3 cycles); (3) [E] h0+rank H1=8=rank E8, h0-rank H1=2=|Z2|, (h0+H1)/2=4=|mu4|; (4) [E] Lambda^even(C^5)=1+10+5=16=dim S^+ (the D5 half-spinor, v197); (5) [E] NEG deg 3->(4,2), deg 5->(6,4), colliding marks lower H1 and break N_fam. Relocates P2 from '5 slots' to 'the genus-0 mode count of a 4-mark divisor'; conditional on the raw seam producing the degree-4 divisor (=QGEO.SYM.01). Status: [E] index arithmetic, [C] mode-space reading, [O] the seam->divisor step"),
    ("v229_lepton_frobenius_algebra", "LEP.FROB.01: the charged leptons as an etale Frobenius algebra over the mu6 resolvent. (1) [E] exact coefficients (c_e,c_mu,c_tau)=(16/7,4/3,7/6), ring closure c_e c_tau=8/3=|Z2| c_mu, product=32/9=2^g_car/N_fam^2; (2) [E] FROBENIUS: A=Q[t]/(m), m=(t-c_e)(t-c_mu)(t-c_tau), the trace-form Gram G_ij=Tr(t^i t^j) is nondegenerate (det G=discriminant(m)!=0, A etale) -- a commutative Frobenius algebra with nondegenerate trace pairing; (3) [E] mu6 RESOLVENT: the C6 shift has charpoly t^6-1 (spectrum mu6=mu3 family x mu2 sheet, the v17 hexagonal backbone); (4) [C] PMNS extension: Aut(A) permutes {e,mu,tau} (real part), the hexagonal CM point j=0 (v220) supplies the phase. Status: [E] coefficient algebra+Frobenius+mu6 spectrum, [C] PMNS extension"),
    ("v230_center_budget_norms", "CENTER.NORM.01: the Sheet-Diamond center budget (7,11,13) is the three LOCAL NORMS of the theory. C=R+Q diag(1,0,0), row sums (7,11,13) (v95/v218). (1) [E] 7=N_Z[omega](3+2 omega) (Eisenstein/hexagonal CM norm = scalaron exponent); (2) [E] 13=N_Z[i](3+2i) (Gaussian/square CM norm = Delta_Q); (3) [E] 11=C(4,0)+C(4,1)+C(4,2)=1+4+6 (QBL boundary Fock count on the 4 mu4 corners = dim S^+-g_car=16-5, v174); (4) [E] NEG the ring assignment is rigid (N_i(3,2)=13!=7, N_omega(3,2)=7!=13). So C = (hex norm, boundary Fock count, square norm): the two CM rings (v222) and the seam boundary count meet in one operator center. Status: [E] arithmetic, [C] the 'center = three local norms' reading"),
    ("v231_cp_mu6_phases", "CP.MU6.01: both CP phases are mu6 powers of ONE hexagonal CM unit, split by the sheet -- a structural reduction of red-team Target D (sharper than v220/v225). With rho=e^{i pi/3} (the j=0 Eisenstein CM unit, v220): (1) [E] rho is a primitive 6th root, rho^6=1, rho^3=-1 (the Z2 sheet half-turn); (2) [E] delta_CKM leading = arg(rho^1)=pi/3 (quark), delta_PMNS = arg(rho^4)=4 pi/3 (lepton, the tfpt_2 phase lattice); (3) [E] rho^4=-rho => delta_PMNS = delta_CKM,lead + pi = (CM unit)x(Z2 sheet) -- the two CP phases are ONE hexagonal unit on the two sheets, not two independent inputs; (4) [E] the C6/mu6 monodromy U6 has charpoly t^6-1 (spectrum mu6 carries rho); (5) [E] ORIENTATION (v225): Im det(1,d,rho^1 n)=+21 sin(pi/3) (quark), Im det(1,d,rho^4 n)=-21 sin(pi/3) (lepton) -- sheet-flipped Jarlskog orientations; (6) [E] NEG mu3 (cube roots) has no -1, so it cannot relate the two phases by a half-turn (mu6=mu3 family x mu2 sheet required). REDUCTION: 2 CP phase inputs -> 1 hexagonal unit + the sheet; the quark seam correction 3 lambda_C^2 stays the v88 misalignment, the deck stays Z/4 (v215). [E] arithmetic; [C] physical CP derivation; does NOT close Target D, removes one of its two phase inputs"),
    ("v232_e8_kleinian_seam", "TOPO.E8.01: the seam as the E8 Kleinian singularity -- a canonical algebraic-geometric MODEL for the open seam-realisation premise QGEO.REALIZE.01. The du Val side of the McKay correspondence (v219): (1) [E] the McKay graph of 2I is affine E8 (9 nodes); dropping the unique trivial-rep node (the single Kac mark=1) leaves the FINITE E8 Dynkin on 8 nodes = the dual intersection graph of the 8 exceptional P^1's of the minimal resolution of C^2/2I (trivalent node, arms 1,2,4). (2) [E] EIGHT exceptional P^1's = rank E8 = g_car+N_fam = #nontrivial 2I irreps (9-1) -- a fourth reading of the '8' in c3=1/(8 pi). (3) [E] the negated resolution intersection form is the E8 CARTAN: even, det 1 (unimodular), positive definite -- each P^1 a (-2)-curve, adjacent curves meet once; the seam P^1's carry the E8 lattice. (4) [E] exactly ONE degree-1 irrep => 2I perfect => H_1(S^3/2I)=0: the link is the Poincare homology 3-sphere, pi_1=2I order 120=|R^+(E8)|. (5) [C] SEAM REALISATION: the raw RP seam (P^1 with marks) is canonically a component of the E8 du Val exceptional locus -- QGEO.REALIZE.01 gets a geometric model, NOT a derivation of P2 ([O] stays: presupposes E8). [E] resolution/lattice/link arithmetic; [C] seam reading; bedrock [O]"),
    ("v233_cp_triality_phase", "CP.TRIALITY.01: the CP phase is the UNIVERSAL family/triality phase, only sheet-split -- one step past v231 in the mu6 = mu3 (family/triality) x mu2 (sheet) factorisation. (1) [E] mu6=mu3 x mu2 (gcd(3,2)=1): the Z3 triality centre {1,omega,omega^2} = the cusp weights {0,1/3,2/3} x 2pi, the sheet is mu2={1,-1}; rho = omega^2 * (-1). (2) [E] SAME FAMILY CLASS: rho^4 = rho^1 * rho^3 with rho^3 in mu2, so the quark (rho^1) and lepton (rho^4) CP phases have the SAME image in mu6/mu2 ~ mu3 (the same triality centre element) and OPPOSITE sheet ((-1)^1 vs (-1)^4). (3) [E] so the CP phase IS the universal triality phase omega^2 (the 2/3 cusp-weight Z3 centre), read on the two sheets -- NOT a free choice of power. (4) [E] omega is the mu3 factor of the order-30 (2,3,5) Milnor/Coxeter monodromy (omega^3=1, 30/3=10=A_Lambda), so CP lives inside the same cycle that builds E8 (v232). (5) [E] NEG: mu2-only carries no triality, mu3-only carries no sheet; only mu6 gives 'one triality phase, two sheets'. Reduces Target D from 'one hexagonal unit + sheet' (v231) to 'the universal triality phase + sheet'; physical CP derivation stays [C], quark 3 lambda_C^2 stays the v88 misalignment"),
    ("v234_seam_holomorphy_selection", "GATE.HOLO.01: the Seam-Holomorphy selection certificate -- the entire structural residual is ONE condition with THREE equivalent faces, all forcing E8. THE CONDITION: 'the seam carries no nontrivial abelian sector.' (i) AQFT: the boundary net is HOLOMORPHIC (mu-index 1, single sector); (ii) geometry: the seam link is a HOMOLOGY 3-sphere <=> the binary group is PERFECT <=> 2I; (iii) rep theory: exactly ONE 1-dim irrep. (1) [E] #(mark-1 affine-Dynkin nodes) = |Gamma^ab| = |H_1(S^3/Gamma)| = #(1-dim irreps): A_n->n+1, D_n->4, E6->3, E7->2, E8->1 -- ONLY E8 gives 1, so 2I is the unique nontrivial perfect finite SU(2) subgroup (the Poincare sphere is the unique homology-sphere space form). (2) [E] holomorphic c=8=g_car+N_fam: a holomorphic chiral CFT has c in 8Z, and at c=8 the unique even unimodular rank-8 lattice is E8 (Gram even, det 1) -> (E8)_1. (3) [E] CONVERGENCE: face (i)=v83/v154, (ii)=v232, (iii)=v219 are the SAME E8-selector, so Target A, G_net, the carrier P2 and the Kleinian seam are ONE gate, not four. (4) [O] the CLOSING THEOREM (stated, not proved): RP+gap+chirality => quasi-free bulk (v160) => invertible bulk => holomorphic boundary net => E8; the single residual analytic step is 'free bulk => holomorphic boundary', then P2/QGEO/G_net follow. [E] selection arithmetic; [O] the analytic theorem"),
    ("v235_seam_chern_simons", "GATE.HOLO.02: the closing step in abelian Chern-Simons language -- holomorphic <=> det K = 1, a genuine reduction (NOT a closure) of GATE.HOLO.01's analytic step into standard anyon-condensation physics. A free gapped bosonic 2+1d bulk = an even integer K-matrix with #anyons = |det K|, edge c = signature(K), and the edge net holomorphic <=> |det K| = 1 (standard CS/quantum-Hall bulk-boundary correspondence). So 'no nontrivial abelian sector' (v234) is exactly |det K| = 1. (1) [E] the TFPT extension tower (v92) IS the anyon-condensation tower read by det: carrier D5(+)A3 (even, det 16, c=8, 16 anyons) -> SO(16)_1=D8 (det 4, 4 anyons) -> (E8)_1 (det 1, 1 anyon, HOLOMORPHIC); all rank 8, c=signature=8=g_car+N_fam. (2) [E] holomorphic <=> det 1 <=> E8 = the unique even unimodular rank-8 K-matrix = the Kitaev E8 quantum-Hall state (edge (E8)_1). (3) [E] CONDENSATION: a Lagrangian (maximal isotropic) glue of order sqrt(16)=|mu4|=4 takes det 16->16/4^2=1 (carrier->E8); an order-2 isotropic only ->4 (D8). So holomorphic <=> condense the order-|mu4| Lagrangian glue, not a partial. (4) [E] NEG: D8 (det 4) is free+bosonic but has 4 anyons (not holomorphic); an odd K is fermionic -- 'free+bosonic' does NOT imply holomorphic, det=1 is the extra condition. (5) [O] RESIDUAL: the closing step = 'the free RP seam condenses the order-|mu4| Lagrangian glue (det->1)' = the same sheet/mu4 selection as GATE.QGEO, now with holomorphy<=>det1 a theorem. [E] CS/lattice dictionary + det tower; [O] the Lagrangian-condensation input"),
    ("v236_brieskorn_capstone", "TOPO.BRIESKORN.01: the (2,3,5) Brieskorn singularity x^2+y^3+z^5 is the ONE generator of the discrete skeleton -- the capstone of the icosahedral round (v55/v219/v223/v232/v233). Its three exponents ARE the atoms (|Z2|,N_fam,g_car)=(2,3,5). (1) [E] MILNOR NUMBER = the '8': mu=(2-1)(3-1)(5-1)=(|Z2|-1)(N_fam-1)(g_car-1)=1*2*4=8=rank E8=#exceptional P^1 = the '8' in c3=1/(8 pi) (a FIFTH independent origin after geometry/lattice/gravity/phi(30)). (2) [E] MONODROMY = the order-30 Coxeter cycle: the Milnor monodromy eigenvalues lambda=zeta_2^j1 zeta_3^j2 zeta_5^j3 are the eight primitive 30th roots e^{2pi i m/30}, m in {1,7,11,13,17,19,23,29} = the E8 exponents; charpoly = Phi_30 (deg phi(30)=8=mu) -> the Milnor monodromy IS the E8 Coxeter element of order 30=h(E8) (v55). (3) [E] BOTH CLOCKS: the monodromy GROUP <h>=Z/30=Z/2(sheet)xZ/3(family)xZ/5(carrier) carries the mu3 triality (CP omega, v233) as h^10; the GALOIS group Gal(Q(zeta_30)/Q)=(Z/30)^x=Z/2xZ/4 carries the order-4 mu4 clock (x7) on the spectrum (v223). (4) [E] Milnor lattice=E8, link=Poincare sphere S^3/2I (v232/v234). (5) [I] SYNTHESIS: one singularity generates atoms+8+E8+order30+both clocks+seam. Unifies, does not close a gate"),
    ("v237_seam_sre_closure", "GATE.HOLO.03: the closing step as a PHYSICAL condition -- no topological ground-state degeneracy <=> det K=1 <=> the seam bulk is short-range-entangled (SRE/invertible). Sharpens GATE.HOLO.02's residual from definitional ('condense the Lagrangian glue') to physical/falsifiable. (1) [E] the K-matrix ground-state degeneracy on a genus-g surface is |det K|^g: carrier D5(+)A3->16, D8->4, E8->1 (torus); so 'no degeneracy on any closed surface' <=> |det K|=1. (2) [E] SRE <=> det 1 <=> E8: among rank-8 even positive-definite K (c=signature=8=g_car+N_fam) only E8 has det 1 -- THE unique nontrivial bosonic SRE 2+1d phase (Kitaev E8), edge (E8)_1 holomorphic; D8/carrier are long-range-entangled. (3) [E] PLANE vs TORUS: a unique vacuum on the plane (RP+gap+cluster, established) is necessary but not sufficient -- the plane cannot see |det K|, the torus does; the residual is exactly 'the seam unique-vacuum extends to the torus' = SRE. (4) [E] NEG: an LRE bulk (D8, det 4) has 4-fold torus degeneracy + non-holomorphic boundary. (5) [O] SHARPENED RESIDUAL: 'the free RP gapped seam bulk is short-range-entangled (no topological ground-state degeneracy)' = det K=1 = the Kitaev E8 phase -- a yes/no statement about topological order, sharper than v235 or QGEO.SYM.01. [E] degeneracy=|det K|^g dictionary + SRE<=>det1<=>E8; [O] the physical SRE premise. NOT a closure"),

    ("v238_modular_lindblad_dynamics", "DYN.SEMIGROUP.01: the STATIC->DYNAMIC flip -- the seam's modular flow (reversible) and its recovery channel read as a Markov/Lindblad generator (irreversible), with the dissipative gap EQUAL to the OS mass gap. Companion to v196/v198 (modular) and v221/v64 (recovery): those state the structure STATICALLY (a commutator, a contraction bound, a mass-gap number); this reads the SAME objects DYNAMICALLY. (1) [E] MODULAR FLOW = REVERSIBLE GENERATOR: sigma_t = e^{i t Lambda_Sigma} is a unitary one-parameter group (Tomita-Takesaki), and the mu4 clock is CONSERVED -- rho sigma_t rho^{-1} = sigma_t for all t <=> [rho,Lambda_Sigma]=0 (the v198 state-invariance), so the static v198 commutator IS the conservation law of modular time; NEG a mu4-breaking off-diagonal Lambda breaks it. (2) [E] RECOVERY = DISSIPATIVE GENERATOR: L = log T is real-symmetric with off-diagonals >= 0 and zero row/column sums (a doubly-stochastic / CPTP-classical Markov generator), e^{L*1} = T reproduces the v221 channel, and e^{L tau} -> the rank-1 projector onto the democratic mode (the arrow of time, matching v64's T^n -> projector). (3) [E] KEYSTONE: the dissipative spectral gap = -log((2/3)^6) = 6 log(3/2) = the OS/RP mass gap Delta (v64) -- the STATIC recovery bound (2/3)^6 (v221) and the DYNAMICAL mass gap (v64) are ONE number, one exponentiated; NEG a free rate r != (2/3)^6 breaks it. (4) [E] GKSL SPLIT: G = i Lambda_Sigma + L has reversible (imaginary) + dissipative (real <= 0, gapped) spectrum -- the canonical Hamiltonian + Lindbladian split. (5) [O] residual: geometric modular flow on the FULL seam algebra (Connes-Rovelli 'thermal time = physical time' = QGEO.SYM.01, v198) and the continuum embedding -- a target, not a closure. Python-only (finite-block linear algebra, numpy)."),

    ("v239_kms_thermal_time", "DYN.KMS.01: KMS / thermal time -- the modular flow of v238 makes the seam state a KMS (thermal) state at beta=1, and the geometric normalisation fixes the seam temperature via 2 pi = 1/(4 c3). (1) [E] KMS at beta=1: omega(A sigma_i(B)) = omega(B A) for all A,B (omega(X)=Tr(rho X), rho=e^{-Lambda_Sigma}/Z), so modular time (v238) is a thermal time (Connes-Rovelli) and the seam state is the Gibbs state of the modular Hamiltonian. (2) [E] NEG: beta != 1 (e.g. 1/2) fails -- Tomita-Takesaki pins beta=1, no tunable knob. (3) [E] the seam unit: beta_phys = 2 pi = 1/(4 c3) exactly (v58; 1/4=1/|mu4|), so the modular KMS temperature is T_H = kappa/(2 pi) = c3/M (v57/v208) -- thermal time = horizon time. (4) [E] one object with v238: the same Lambda_Sigma generates sigma_t and rho=e^{-Lambda_Sigma}/Z; the recovery generator L's stationary state is the beta->0 democratic point. (5) [O] residual: that this is the GEOMETRIC boost (T_H physical) is the QGEO.SYM.01/BW premise (HOR.BHTHERMO.01 [P]) -- a target, not a closure. Python-only."),

    ("v240_gns_os_reconstruction", "DYN.GNS.01: GNS / OS reconstruction (finite toy) -- the Hilbert space and a POSITIVE Hamiltonian are OUTPUTS of the seam data (M, omega), not inputs. (1) [E] GNS: <A,B>=Tr(rho A^dag B) is Hermitian positive-definite (rho>0), dim n^2, identity cyclic+separating -- the Hilbert space is reconstructed from (M,omega). (2) [E] modular flow sigma_t(x)=rho^{it} x rho^{-it} is a state-preserving *-automorphism with generator i[log rho,.] = Lambda_Sigma (v238); modular operator Delta:X|->rho X rho^{-1} positive. (3) [E] OS Hamiltonian H_OS = -log T (T the v221 recovery transfer) is POSITIVE: eigenvalues {0, 6 log(3/2), 6 log 3} >= 0, ground state the stationary mode, gap = 6 log(3/2) = the v64 mass gap -- OS reconstruction delivers v64's 'H>=0 + mass gap'. (4) [E] H_OS = -L: the OS Hamiltonian is MINUS the v238 dissipative generator -- the recovery semigroup IS Euclidean time; two Hamiltonians from one seam (modular thermal-time + OS positive-energy). (5) [O] residual: the geometric/operator-level identification = QGEO.SYM.01/BW + the standard OS theorem under RP/gap (Layer 2). Python-only."),

    ("v241_dhr_sectors", "DHR.SECTORS.01: particles = DHR superselection sectors -- the carrier discriminant/anyon content and the v235/v237 condensation tower as an abelian MTC. The carrier discriminant form is the Lean-verified glue form (FORM.GLUE.01): on Z4 x Z4, q(x,y)=(5x^2+3y^2)/8 mod 1, B((x,y),(x',y'))=(5xx'+3yy')/4 mod 1, theta(a)=e^{2 pi i q(a)}. (1) [E] 16 sectors = Z4 x Z4 (= det K_carrier = dim S^+), fusion = abelian group law (closed, associative, vacuum, inverses). (2) [E] spin/condensability: bosonic <=> theta=1 <=> isotropic <=> 5x^2+3y^2=0 mod 8 -- exactly the six elements {(0,0),(1,1),(1,3),(2,2),(3,1),(3,3)}. (3) [E] condensation tower = v235/v237: condensing the Lagrangian H1=<(1,1)> (order 4, self-dual) leaves |H^perp/H|=1 sector = (E8)_1 (det 1); the order-2 isotropic <(2,2)> leaves 4 = D8 (det 4); so carrier 16 -> D8 4 -> E8 1. (4) [E] NEG: a non-isotropic anyon (1,0) is confined, and <(1,0)> cannot be a condensation algebra -- forced by isotropy. (5) [C] identifying sectors with SM multiplets is the interpretation; the MTC data is exact. 'Particles = stable defect sectors of the seam code' made precise. Python-only."),

    ("v242_spin_statistics_modular", "DHR.MODULAR.01: spin-statistics and the modular (S,T) data of the carrier MTC -- statistics + the fusion ring recovered from modular data, and the anyon central charge c = 8. Same MTC as v241 (Z4 x Z4, q=(5x^2+3y^2)/8, theta=e^{2 pi i q}). (1) [E] spin-statistics: T = diag(theta_a) splits the 16 anyons into 6 bosons (theta=1), 2 fermions (theta=-1) = {(0,2),(2,0)}, 8 anyons. (2) [E] modular S_ab = (1/sqrt 16) e^{-2 pi i B(a,b)} is unitary, symmetric, S^2 = C (charge conjugation), S^4 = I. (3) [E] Verlinde N_ab^c = sum_x S_ax S_bx conj(S_cx)/S_0x = delta(c,a+b) -- the fusion ring is recovered from modular data. (4) [E] Gauss-Milgram (1/sqrt 16) sum theta_a = e^{2 pi i c/8} with c = 8 = g_car + N_fam = the (E8)_1 central charge (v156/v175) -- statistics and c=8 are one fact. (5) [C] the boson/fermion split is the kinematic skeleton; sector<->multiplet map is the interpretation. Python-only."),

    ("v243_haag_ruelle_braiding", "DHR.SMATRIX.01: scattering -- the Haag-Ruelle skeleton + the braiding S-matrix. The seam net has a mass gap (v64/v238) so Haag-Ruelle constructs asymptotic states; for the abelian anyon MTC (v241/v242) the 2-particle S-matrix is the monodromy M(a,b)=theta(a+b)/(theta(a)theta(b))=e^{2 pi i B(a,b)}. (1) [E] mass gap Delta=6 log(3/2)>0 (v64/v238) -> HR asymptotic in/out states (standard gapped-net theorem). (2) [E] 2-particle S = monodromy: |M|=1, diagonal in the conserved anyon labels -> no particle production, factorised (integrable) scattering. (3) [E] Yang-Baxter: M is a bicharacter (M(a+a',b)=M(a,b)M(a',b)) -> multi-particle factorisation. (4) [E] crossing+symmetry: M(a,b)=M(b,a), M(a,-b)=conj(M(a,b)). (5) [E] holomorphic point: on the condensed (E8)_1 (single deconfined sector) M=1 -- trivial braiding, a closed anomaly-free bulk (det 1/SRE); scattering only in the matter sectors. (6) [O] the 4d S-matrix / cross-sections are the open holographic uplift (Phase 3) -- this exhibits the exact 2d topological scattering data. Python-only."),

    ("v244_spectral_action_contract", "CONTRACT.QFT4D.01: the 4d Lagrangian via Connes' spectral action -- the honest CONTRACT for the Phase-3 structural gap (2d seam net -> 4d physics). The natural TFPT bridge is the spectral action: a SINGLE Dirac operator whose Tr f(D/Lambda) yields gravity AND matter. (1) [E] carrier spinor = one generation: SO(10) half-spinor = dim S^+ = 2^(g_car-1) = 16 = one SM generation (15 + nu_R), N_fam = 3 -- the carrier carries the SM matter rep. (2) [E] SM gauge group inside the carrier: SU(3)xSU(2)xU(1) (dim 12) in SU(5) (24) in SO(10)=D5 (45); color SU(3) in A3=SU(4) (Pati-Salam); rank(D5)+rank(A3)=8=rank E8. (3) [E] one Dirac operator -> gravity (a2~R, a4~R^2, v36) + matter (a4 ~ F^2 Yang-Mills + |D phi|^2 Higgs, Gilkey). (4) [X] falsifiable hooks: spectral-action boundary relations g3=g2=sqrt(5/3)g1 and a Higgs-quartic relation (Chamseddine-Connes-Marcolli). (5) [O] CONTRACT.QFT4D.01: obligations (seam -> Dirac D; finite geometry = carrier; spectral action reproduces SM couplings) -> the 4d SM+gravity Lagrangian is an OUTPUT. The genuine Phase-3 target, NOT closed (complement of U_wall/G_metric). Python-only."),

    ("v245_spectral_matter_content", "QFT4D.MATTER.01: the computable core of CONTRACT.QFT4D.01 -- the spectral-action / NCG MATTER content, discharging the representation-theory + tree-relation core to [E]. The carrier half-spinor is the SO(10) 16. (1) [E] 16 = one generation: SO(10) 16 = SU(5) (10+5bar+1); SM multiplet dims 6+3+1+2+3+1 = 16 = dim S^+, N_fam=3 (15 Weyl fermions + nu_R). (2) [E] electric charges Q = T3 + Y are exactly the SM values (quarks +2/3,-1/3; leptons 0,-1; e^c +1; nu^c 0) -- hypercharges forced by the embedding. (3) [E] anomaly-free: sum Y = 0, sum Y^3 = 0, [SU(2)]^2 U(1) = 0, [SU(3)]^2 U(1) = 0 (exact). (4) [E] spectral-action unification: sin^2 th_W = (sum T3^2)/(sum Q^2) = 3/8, i.e. g3=g2=sqrt(5/3)g1 (Chamseddine-Connes-Marcolli). (5) [E] Higgs = the (1,2)_{1/2} off-diagonal inner fluctuation of the finite Dirac operator (one doublet). (6) [O] residual: the seam->Dirac realisation + reproducing measured couplings after RG running -- still a contract, now with its rep-theory core verified. Python-only (exact rational arithmetic)."),

    ("v246_unification_data_crosscheck", "QFT4D.RGTEST.01: the HONEST data cross-check for the spectral-action prediction (v244/v245) -- does g1=g2=g3, sin^2 th_W=3/8 at Lambda survive the MEASURED SM couplings? Answer: NOT in the plain SM. Inputs (PDG, GUT-normalised, M_Z): alpha_i^-1 = (59.01, 29.59, 8.47), SM 1-loop b=(41/10,-19/6,-7) (v159). (1) [E] the prediction: alpha1=alpha2=alpha3 and sin^2 th_W=3/8 at the unification scale. (2) [X] tension: the pairwise crossings are NOT coincident (a1=a2 ~1e13, a1=a3 ~2.4e14, a2=a3 ~1e17 GeV; ~4 decades spread) and the residual spread at 2e16 is Delta(alpha^-1) ~ 8.8 -- g1=g2=g3 is not realised by the plain SM. (3) [X] sin^2 th_W: 3/8 predicted vs 0.23122 measured (the known non-SUSY shortfall). (4) [X] two-loop also misses: RK4 2-loop run gives minimal spread Delta(alpha^-1) ~ 3.2 at ~1.7e14 GeV (never a common point), ~8.7 at 2e16. (5) [O] NO rescue: TFPT has SM gauge content and no new states (tfpt_3 'no new state'), and the E8 cascade is an arithmetic spine (v5), not a threshold tower -- there is no admissible threshold source; closing it needs new gauge-charged matter (vs 'no new state') or a non-GUT/boundary reading. The spectral-action 4d-GUT route is in genuine tension (same status as NCG-SM), likely falsified unless extended. A kill-test typed [X]/[O], NEVER [E]-as-success. Python-only (1+2-loop running)."),

    ("v247_e8_branching_no126", "PS.E8BRANCH.01: the E8 audit hull forbids the 126 and supplies exactly {1,10,16,45} for SO(10). The carrier D5(+)A3 = SO(10)xSU(4) is a rank-8 subalgebra of E8 (via SO(16)); the 248 branches as (45,1)+(1,15)+(10,6)+(16,4)+(16bar,4bar) = 45+15+60+64+64 = 248 (SO(16): 120 adjoint + 128 spinor). (1) [E] ranks 5+3=8=rank E8. (2) [E] dims sum to 248. (3) [E] SO(10) content = {1,10,16,45}; the 126 is ABSENT -> the renormalisable 126_H is algebraically forbidden if fields are E8-hull reps; 10+16+45 is E8-supplied, not fitted (makes the scalaron-match 16-over-126 selection algebraic). (4) [E] CAVEAT: only ONE (45,1) and ONE (1,15) in the 248 -> minimal content is proton-MARGINAL. (5) [O] the field-content principle + the NCG inner-fluctuation complement (v250). Python-only (rep theory)."),

    ("v248_ps_algebra", "PS.ALGEBRA.01: the Pati-Salam NCG algebra A_F = H_L (+) H_R (+) M_4(C) and its exact SM matching. (1) [E] unimodular group SU(2)_L x SU(2)_R x SU(4)_c (ranks 1+1+3=5=rank SO(10), dims 3+3+15=21). (2) [E] one generation 16 = (4,2,1)+(4bar,1,2) = 8+8. (3) [E] Y = T_3R + (B-L)/2 gives the EXACT SM hypercharges for all 6 multiplets and Q=T_3L+Y the exact electric charges (B-L = SU(4)_c generator, lepton = 4th colour). (4) [E] matching a1^-1=(3/5)a2R^-1+(2/5)a4^-1 (coeffs sum to 1 -> a1=a_GUT at the SO(10) point), sin^2 thetaW=3/8. (5) [O] that A_F is UNIQUELY reconstructed from seam+sheet+mu4 (carrier gauged as a theorem). (6) [O] CAVEAT: PS colour SU(4)_c sits inside SO(10)=D5; it is NOT the carrier A3=SU(4) (= family, N_fam=3) -- a precision the reviews blur. Python-only (exact rational rep theory)."),

    ("v249_ps_unification", "PS.RGTEST.01: carrier-native Pati-Salam/SO(10) two-step unification kill-test with the mandated negative controls (the suite claim-check of experiments/gauge-unification). (1) [E] matching + a valid 1-loop unification solution exists (M_PS < M_GUT < M_Pl). (2) [X] NEG SM-only fails (residual spread ~8.8 at 2e16). (3) [C] scale coincidence: M_PS/M_s = 1.0-1.7 (1-loop; 2-loop ~1.0-1.2) -- the gauge-unification and gravitational-scalaron scales coincide. (4) [X] NEG 126 breaks the match (b2R>0 -> no scalaron-matched solution; 2-loop ~33x; 126 also E8-forbidden, v247). (5) [X] NEG proton decay selects content: minimal 16-Higgs M_GUT~2e15 -> tau_p < Super-K EXCLUDED; +(15,1,1) [E8 45] raises M_GUT, proton-safer. (6) [O] residuals: the gauging fork, exact kappa, the one-45 E8 marginality. Python-only (1-loop analytic two-step; full 1+2-loop in experiments/gauge-unification)."),

    ("v250_dirac_triple_contract", "CONTRACT.QFT4D.DIRAC.01: the spectral-triple contract that would make 'carrier gauged' a theorem (Reviewer-A Theorem 3 + sigma=scalaron). Target: (A,H,D,J,gamma) almost-commutative, A_F = PS (v248), H_F = 3x16, D_F from (R,L,phi0,Majorana). (1) [E] H_F = N_fam x dim S^+ = 3x16 = 48. (2) [E] the Yukawas are already fixed (FLAV.QUARK.01/v18) so the open test is NCG consistency, not 'nice Yukawas'. (3) [O] the 7 NCG obligations (J, gamma, KO-dim 6 mod 8, first-order condition [the historic SO(10) obstruction], orientability, Poincare duality, no-junk). (4) [O] sigma=scalaron hypothesis (rescues first-order + nu_R Majorana; supported by M_PS=kappa M_s) -- CAVEAT: scalaron<->nu_R nu_R coupling not automatic, must be proven. (5) [O] inner fluctuations Omega^1_D -> 10+16+45 not 126 (NCG complement of v247). (6) [C] verdict: reduces '4d QFT' to ONE object (the triple) + finite NCG checks; gauge group/matter/Yukawa/unification already in place. Python-only (typing/bookkeeping)."),

    ("v251_first_order_sigma", "PS.DIRAC.01: the FIRST-ORDER CONDITION is violated EXACTLY by the Majorana/sigma term -- the Chamseddine-Connes-van Suijlekom 'beyond first order' mechanism that makes non-commutative geometry produce Pati-Salam + a sigma field. Advances CONTRACT.QFT4D.DIRAC.01 (v250) from contract to exhibited mechanism on a faithful minimal model (the lepton/neutrino block, doubled particle (+) antiparticle). HONEST CORRECTION to the review: sigma does NOT 'rescue' first order -- one DROPS first order and the inner fluctuations THEN generate Pati-Salam + sigma. (1) [E] order-zero [pi(a),J pi(b) J^-1]=0. (2) [E] real-even: J^2=+1, gamma^2=1, D gamma=-gamma D (KO-dim 6 signs; physical SM triple is KO-6). (3) [E] first order HOLDS for the Yukawa block (M=0). (4) [E] first order VIOLATED with M!=0, supported EXACTLY on the Majorana (nu_R nu_R^c) blocks -- the sigma is the unique violator; the controlled violation IS the Pati-Salam mechanism. (5) [C] sigma=scalaron (M_PS=kappa M_s, v249), physical identification [O]. (6) [O] the full 96-dim SM/PS triple + spectral-action expansion stay open (v250). Python-only (numpy)."),

    ("v252_full_finite_triple", "PS.DIRAC.02: the FULL 96-dim finite spectral triple (A_F, H_F, D_F, J, gamma) of the carrier, built explicitly, with the NCG axioms verified by direct computation. Advances CONTRACT.QFT4D.DIRAC.01 (v250) from a contract listing 7 open obligations to a concrete object discharging 5 to [E]. H_F = particle (+) antiparticle doubling of three SO(10) 16-plets (dim 96). D_F = [[S,T],[T^dag,conj S]] (S=Yukawa, T=Majorana/sigma). (1) [E] dim 96 = 2 x Omega_adm. (2) [E] D_F Hermitian + odd (D gamma=-gamma D). (3) [E] reality J: J^2=+1, JD=DJ. (4) [E] grading: gamma^2=1, [gamma,a]=0, J gamma=-gamma J. (5) [E] KO-dimension 6. (6) [E] order-zero [pi(a),J pi(b) J^-1]=0 for the SM algebra. (7) [E] first order HOLDS for the SM algebra C(+)H(+)M3 INCLUDING the Majorana. (8) [E] first order VIOLATED for the Pati-Salam (SU(2)_R) algebra exactly by the Majorana, localized to the right-handed lepton doublet {nu_R,e_R} -- the CCvS beyond-first-order PS+sigma mechanism on the full triple. (9) [E] spectrum of D_F = fermion masses + type-I seesaw m_light=m_D^2/M_R. (10) [C] Poincare duality: intersection form non-degenerate. (11) [O] orientability + no-junk + spectral-action expansion. Python-only (numpy)."),

    ("v253_kappa_scalaron_ps", "PS.KAPPA.01: pinning kappa in M_PS = kappa M_s, discharging residual 6(b) of v249. M_s = c3^{7/2} Mbar ~ 3.06e13 GeV (exact). kappa := M_PS/M_s. (1) [E] scalaron scale exact from {c3,Mbar}. (2) [E] kappa PINNED by RG: scanning PDG coupling errors x the two E8-allowed contents gives kappa in a tight O(1) interval (~1.3, consistent with the 1-loop [1.0,1.7] / 2-loop [1.0,1.2] band) -- pinned, not free. (3) [C] HEAT-KERNEL ORIGIN: kappa = sqrt((f2/f0) c_PS/c_grav) is a ratio of heat-kernel coefficients over H_F (the 96-dim triple, v252); Lambda cancels so kappa is scale-free and O(1) for O(1) cutoff moments. (4) [X] NEG control: 126-content drives kappa out of the O(1) window (content-selective). (5) [O] the exact scheme-independent decimal needs the cutoff moments f2/f0 fixed. Python-only (numpy)."),

    ("v254_inner_fluctuations", "PS.NCG.FLUCT.01: the inner fluctuations Omega^1_D(A_F) of the finite Dirac operator computed explicitly (reusing the v252 triple), closing v250 #5 (Higgs content, NOT 126) and the NO-JUNK obligation, and fixing the sigma quantum numbers. (1) [E] Omega^1_{D_F} is purely chirality-odd -> the finite fluctuations are SCALARS (gauge bosons come from the continuum [D_M,a]). (2) [E] NO JUNK, NO 126: for the SM algebra every 1-form sits exactly in the Higgs-doublet pattern (chirality-odd, colour-diagonal, no quark<->lepton mixing) = the one SM Higgs doublet (1,2)_{1/2}; no triplet, no (10,1,3)/126-type scalar. (3) [E] sigma NEEDS BEYOND FIRST ORDER: with the SM algebra the sigma (nu_R Majorana) direction is NOT generated (first order holds) but with the Pati-Salam algebra it IS -- sigma is the CCvS beyond-first-order scalar. (4) [E] sigma quantum numbers: SM singlet (1,1,0), B-L=2 (nu_R has B-L=-1), giving the nu_R Majorana mass. (5) [C] sigma=scalaron consistency. Python-only (numpy)."),

    ("v255_spectral_action_expansion", "PS.SPECACT.01: the spectral-action heat-kernel (Seeley-DeWitt) expansion S = 2 f4 L^4 a0 + 2 f2 L^2 a2 + f0 a4 over the finite triple, closing v252 #11 (spectral-action expansion) and making the kappa-dependence on the cutoff moments explicit (v253 #5). (1) [E] expansion structure: a0=cosmological, a2=Einstein-Hilbert+Higgs-mass, a4=Yang-Mills+Weyl^2+R^2+Higgs-quartic, with N=dim H_F=96. (2) [E] trace inputs a=Tr(Y+Y), b=Tr((Y+Y)^2), b/a^2=1/3 (top-dominated, the Chamseddine-Connes value). (3) [E] gauge: sin^2 thetaW=3/8 (cross-check v245). (4) [C] Higgs quartic lambda(L)~g^2 b/a^2 -> the famous ~125 GeV (vs ~170 without sigma) after running. (5) [E] scalaron from R^2: gravitational a4 ~ f0 N gives Weyl^2+R^2, the R^2 spin-0 mode = the Starobinsky scalaron. (6) [C] kappa = sqrt((f2/f0) c_PS/c_grav) made explicit (a2 carries f2, a4 carries f0); RG kappa~1.3 fixes f2/f0 to O(1). (7) [O] exact kappa/lambda need the cutoff function f fixed. Python-only."),

    ("v256_orientability_poincare", "PS.NCG.ORIENT.01: orientability and Poincare duality treated HONESTLY -- the two NCG obligations that do NOT close to a clean [E] on the simplified v252 rep. KO-dim 6 forces the intersection form cap(p,q)=Tr(gamma pi(p) J pi(q) J^-1) to be ANTISYMMETRIC. (1) [E] skew form forced by J gamma=-gamma J + order-zero + reality (verified). (2) [E] on the SM K-theory Z^3 the skew form has rank 2, corank 1, null ~ (1,1,-1) -- the structural obstruction (skew form on odd-rank lattice is degenerate). (3) [E] orientability local condition [gamma_F,pi(a)]=0; orientability proper is a degree-4 Hochschild cycle on the product M x F, not a finite-only check. (4) [C] the canonical hypercharge-faithful SM/PS triple satisfies both (van Suijlekom; Chamseddine-Connes-Marcolli) -- literature, not re-derived. (5) [O] a self-contained machine proof needs the complete canonical bimodule; the v252 rep verifies the five substantive axioms but not these two. NO faked closure. Python-only (numpy)."),

    ("v257_quasiorient_modpd", "PS.NCG.ORIENT.02: the HONEST, literature-confirmed resolution of orientability + Poincare duality, correcting the too-generous v256 typing. Published result (Cacic-Stephan arXiv:0902.2068; CCM07; SM-vacuum arXiv:hep-th/0601192): the CCM Standard-Model finite triple (KO-6, three nu_R) GENUINELY FAILS strict orientability and strict Poincare duality, and satisfies the weakened versions instead. (1) [E] strict orientability FAILS: gamma not in span{lambda(a) rho(b)} (non-orientable). (2) [E] QUASI-orientability HOLDS: the (left,right) A-irrep boxes are disjoint by chirality (L = H weak-doublet, R = C singlet) -> L^LR(H^even,H^odd)={0} -- the weakened orientability the CCM SM satisfies. (3) [E] strict Poincare duality FAILS: KO-6 skew intersection form, corank 1, exactly the equal-L/R-neutrino case (TFPT has 3 nu_R for seesaw). (4) [C] modified Poincare duality holds (CCM); Stephan's alternative triple (St06) restores strict PD with identical physics. (5) [E] correction of v256. A known property of the NCG-SM model class, NOT a TFPT defect; no faked closure. Python-only (numpy)."),
    ("v258_dirac_covariance_induction", "PS.DIRAC.03: the finite Dirac operator D_F is the MODULAR/COVARIANCE INDUCTION of the boundary seam state, not an independent posit -- closing the 'posited Yukawa vs derived operator' gap of v250/v252 (proposal Q2, Dirac as Kasparov product + covariance formula). The quasi-free/modular dictionary: a Gaussian state is fixed by its covariance C (contraction, spec in (0,1)) with one-particle modular Hamiltonian H=log((1-C)C^-1) (Araki/Casini-Huerta), inverse to the KMS occupation C=(1+e^H)^-1 (beta=1, v239). (1) [E] INVERSION IDENTITY: log((1-C)C^-1)=H exactly for C=(1+e^H)^-1 (random Hermitian + a chirality-graded Yukawa block). (2) [E] COVARIANCE IS A LEGAL STATE: C_F=(1+e^{D/mu})^-1 a positive contraction. (3) [E] CHIRALITY-ODD: the induced operator anticommutes with gamma_F -- a Dirac-type operator. (4) [E] UNITARY EQUIVALENCE to v252: inducing C_F built from the 9 Yukawas returns the same spectrum (D_F^ind ~_U D_F). (5) [E] MAJORANA = off-diagonal covariance: the seesaw block induces m_light=m_D^2/M_R. (6) [C] C_F = P_F C_Sigma P_F: the carrier covariance is the compression of the seam KMS two-point function; D_F is the KK shadow [D_Sigma](x)_{(E8)_1}[K_car], the v18 Yukawas the readout of C_Sigma. Python-only (numpy)."),
    ("v259_modular_cutoff_kappa", "PS.SPECACT.02: the spectral-action CUTOFF is the seam KMS weight, fixing f_2/f_0=1 EXACTLY and reducing the last open scheme freedom (v253 #5, v255 #7) from a free function to a finite-triple trace ratio (proposal Q4, the cutoff is modular not chosen). By Tomita-Takesaki/BW the seam state is KMS at beta=1 (v239) and 2pi=1/(4c3) (v58) fixes beta, so the heat-kernel cutoff f(u)=e^{-u} is DERIVED. (1) [E] KMS CUTOFF MOMENTS: f_0=f(0)=1, f_2=int f=1, f_4=int u f=1, so f_2/f_0=f_4/f_2=1 (sympy). (2) [E] SEAM-FIXED beta=1 (no new parameter beyond c3). (3) [E] NON-VACUOUS neg control: a Gaussian cutoff e^{-u^2} gives f_2/f_0=sqrt(pi)/2 != 1 -- the KMS choice is a genuine selection. (4) [E] kappa=sqrt((f_2/f_0)c_PS/c_grav)=sqrt(c_PS/c_grav), no cutoff function left. (5) [C] RG kappa~1.3 pins c_PS/c_grav~1.7 (O(1), band [0.3,3]); the [O] free scheme becomes [C] a finite computation over the built triple. (6) [C] same logic fixes lambda(Lambda) (the ~125 GeV readout). Python-only (sympy)."),
    ("v260_k3_kummer_unification", "ARCH.K3.01: one Kummer/K3 surface carries the SEAM, the CARRIER-16 and the E8 lattice as facets of a single smooth object -- the geometric unification of the v1 'glue D5(+)A3 + mu4 => E8' step (the K3/Kummer proposal). The seam square torus tau=i (j=1728, v214) under the elliptic involution z->-z squares to the Kummer K3. (1) [E] E8 CARTAN: even, det 1, positive-definite (the unique even unimodular pos-def rank-8 lattice). (2) [E] K3 LATTICE L_K3=U^3(+)E8(-1)^2: rank 22=b_2, det -1 (unimodular), even, signature (3,19), E8(-1)^2 an orthogonal summand. (3) [E] SEAM = T^2/(z->-z): 4=|(Z/2)^2| fixed points, pillowcase S^2(2,2,2,2), orbifold Euler char 0 (the v214/v216 four marks). (4) [E] CARRIER-16 = Kummer nodes: |A[2]|=2^4=16 nodes -> 16 exceptional P^1 = dim S+ = Lambda^even(C^5) = 16 (v197), 16=4x4=(seam marks)^2. (5) [E] HONESTY: the 16 node classes span the rank-16 Kummer lattice, NOT literally E8(-1)^2; both are exact but DISTINCT sublattices of H^2(K3) (no '16 nodes = E8(+)E8' conflation). (6) [C] two faces of E8 in K3 (local du Val C^2/2I = v232/v236; global H^2 summand). (7) [C] UNIFICATION: one surface carries seam+carrier-16+E8; v1's glue is its lattice shadow. A unification, not a closure. sympy (exact lattice) + numpy (signature)."),
    ("v261_modular_spectral_closure", "QFT.MSC.01: the MODULAR SPECTRAL CLOSURE -- the assembly/reduction certificate that turns the whole QFT layer (v238-v260) into ONE relative object reduced to ONE open premise (like v176/v234, an assembly cert, not new physics). Master object TFPT_QFT=(A_Sigma,omega_Sigma,Delta_Sigma,rho,A_F,H_F,D_F,J,gamma,S_rel). (1) [E] ONE INDEX=MARKS=FIXED POINTS=GLUE ORDER: Jones [B:A]=4 (v89) = |mu4|=4 (v92) = seam marks 2chi=4 (v216) = pillowcase/Kummer fixed points |(Z/2)^2|=4 (v260). (2) [E] ONE CARRIER-16: dim S+=2^(g_car-1)=Lambda^even(C^5)=Kummer nodes 2^4=16, H_F=2 N_fam 16=96. (3) [E] ONE GAP: Delta=-log((2/3)^6)=6log(3/2)>0 = OS mass gap (v240) = recovery rate (v221) = Lindblad gap (v238). (4) [E] THREE CLOSURES RE-DERIVED: Kasparov log((1-C)C^-1)=H (v258), KMS cutoff f2/f0=1 (v259), K3 lattice signature (3,19)/det-1/even + E8 det 1 (v260). (5) [E] RELATIVE-OBJECT MANIFEST: the ten components each realised by a built script (10/10 present). (6) [O] THE SINGLE RESIDUAL: the whole QFT layer reduces to ONE open premise QGEO.SYM.01 (seam realisation); ambient QG QG.AMB.01 kept separate. (7) [C] MASTER STATEMENT (Modular Spectral Universality) holds modulo QGEO.SYM.01. Python-only (assembly certificate; sympy+numpy)."),
    ("v262_fqcd_mp_me", "FR.MPME.02: the F_QCD transfer pipeline for m_p/m_e, implemented as a real solver (the one F_transfer pipeline that was contract-only). NOT a compiler power -- a [C] standard-physics transfer reproduction. (1) [E] b3=-7=-(11-2 n_f/3) at n_f=6, the SM/SU(3) one-loop coefficient (the only TFPT number in the run). (2) [N] 2-loop alpha_s(M_Z)=0.1179 run down with thresholds gives alpha_s(2 GeV)~0.30 (real ODE solve). (3) [C] Lambda^(3)_MSbar~0.33 GeV x lattice C_p=m_p/Lambda (external O(1)) over the closed m_e gives m_p/m_e~1824 vs measured 1836.15 within ~7% external budget. (4) [X] firewall: m_p/m_e is NOT an admissible compiler integer (SU(9) absent from D5(+)A3); stays [C], only b3=-7 is [E]. Advances FR.MPME.01 [O] -> FR.MPME.02 [C]. Python-only (numpy 2-loop RG)."),
    ("v263_mnu_from_df", "FLAV.PMNS.02: the light neutrino matrix M_nu as the type-I seesaw of D_F, advancing the solar-angle texture (v9) from a posited matrix to a seesaw OBJECT from D_F's blocks. (1) [E] M_nu=-m_D M_R^{-1} m_D^T symmetric + seesaw-suppressed (light masses an OUTPUT of D_F). (2) [E] mu-tau-symmetric (m_D,M_R) give mu-tau-symmetric M_nu (the v9 texture is in the seesaw image). (3) [C] diagonalising gives theta23=45deg and sin^2 theta12=1/3-phi0/2=0.30675 under the seam misalignment, reproducing v9. (4) [O] theta13=0 in this leading texture (physical sin^2 th13~phi0 e^{-5/6} a separate readout). (5) [O] CP magnitude delta_PMNS=240deg from mu6/triality (v231/v233) not from M_nu; M_R the free seesaw scale. An operator advance, NOT a closure of full PMNS dynamics. Python-only (numpy)."),
    ("v264_raw_seam_marklocal", "QGEO.ENERGY.03: the raw-seam => mark-locality REDUCTION (NOT a closure of QGEO.SYM.01). Composes v216+v201+v198 on the canonical pillowcase: (1) [E] Gauss-Bonnet -- 4 cone points, deficit pi each, sum 4pi=2pi chi(S^2), curvature ONLY at the 4 marks. (2) [N] curvature sourced at the mu4 orbit {0,pi/2,pi,3pi/2} has Fourier support ONLY on 4Z (FFT) -- mark-locality automatic for the pillowcase. (3) [E] M_f then commutes with the clock rho=diag(i^n): [rho,M_f]=0. (4) [E] with |k| already commuting (v198), [rho,Lambda]=0 => omega o rho=omega ON THIS METRIC. (5) [O] the residual IS the metric: the chain assumes the raw seam carries the uniformising flat pillowcase metric (= QGEO.SYM.01); NEG control (curvature off the mu4 orbit) breaks it. A reduction/sharpening, NOT a closure. Python-only (numpy FFT+commutator)."),
    ("v265_qft4d_fork_freeze", "QFT4D.FORK.01: freeze the 4D-QFT fork as a Branch Policy (not an open ambiguity); writes qft4d_fork_freeze.json + a prose guard, no new physics. (1) [X] BRANCH A / SM-only GUT killed: 1-loop SM running -- at the alpha1=alpha2 scale alpha3^-1 off by ~5.6, spread ~8.8 at 2e16 (v246); canonical expectation (E8 = audit hull, not a 4D gauge group). (2) [E] BRANCH B / E8 content: 248=(45,1)+(1,15)+(10,6)+(16,4)+(16bar,4bar), SO(10) {1,10,16,45}, 126 absent (v247). (3) [E] sin^2 thetaW=3/8 (v248). (4) [C] kappa=M_PS/M_s in [1.0,1.7] O(1) band (v249/v253). (5) [X] proton safety rule (no fake tau_p window). (6) [E] WORDING GUARD: bare 4D over-claims absent + scoped policy phrases present. (7) [C] decision freeze -> qft4d_fork_freeze.json (canonical=boundary_only, sm_only_gut=killed, uv_branch=PS conditional). A=default, B=falsifiable UV branch, C removed. Python-only (numpy + text guard)."),
    ("v266_ps_threshold_proton", "PS.PROTON.02: the explicit PS threshold model + proton-decay window that DECIDES branch B of the v265 fork; writes ps_threshold_proton.json. Two-step PS solve + d=6 tau_p(p->e+pi0)~1e36(M_GUT/1e16)^4(aGUT^-1/40)^2 yr with an O(3) hadronic band. (1) [E] explicit threshold model: minimal 16H -> M_PS~4.2e13 (=scalaron), M_GUT~2.4e15; +(15,1,1) -> M_GUT~5.9e15. (2) [X] minimal content KILLED: tau_p~4.4e33 yr < Super-K 2.4e34 even at the high band. (3) [C] +(15,1,1) survives now: tau_p~1.6e35 > Super-K. (4) [X] HYPER-K DECISIVE: tau_p~1.6e35 sits at the Hyper-K reach ~1.4e35 (p->e+pi0) -- a dated kill test within the decade. (5) [O] marginal (only ONE 45 in the hull, v247) + O(3) tau_p uncertainty. (6) [C] verdict: B promoted to content-selected (must be +(15,1,1)), Hyper-K-decisive UV branch; A stays canonical. Python-only (numpy)."),
    ("v267_qgeo_rigidity_minimal_axiom", "QGEO.SYM.02: the rigidity / minimal-axiom form of the bedrock QGEO.SYM.01 -- proves the ONE bare statement ('the raw RP seam admits the carrier mu4 clock as a conformal symmetry permuting its 4 marks' = omega o rho = omega) FORCES everything downstream; does NOT close the axiom. (1) [E] order-4 Moebius orbit {a,ia,-a,-ia} has cross-ratio 2 independent of a. (2) [E] cross-ratio 2 <=> j=1728 (only lambda in {-1,1/2,2}) <=> the order-4 CM auto (x,y)->(-x,iy) on y^2=x^3-x. (3) [E] DOWNSTREAM FORCED: square config => unique flat pillowcase (Troyanov, v214) => curvature only at 4 marks => Z4-Fourier DtN (v201/v264) => [rho,Lambda]=0 => omega o rho=omega (v198). (4) [E] NEG: generic config j!=1728 (only Z2), hexagonal j=0 (Z6, order 6 != 4) -- only the square realises mu4. (5) [C] arithmetic rigidity: {1,i,-1,-i} over Q, j=1728 CM by Z[i]; clock order 4 selects j=1728 (Belyi/dessins Galois rigidity). (6) [O] the bare order-4 symmetry stays the one foundational postulate (like c=const). Closes the REDUCTION (axiom=>everything), not the axiom. Python-only (sympy+numpy)."),
    ("v268_theta13_carrier_trace", "FLAV.TH13.01: the reactor angle theta_13 exponent is the carrier hypercharge trace. The VALUE sin^2 theta_13 = phi0 e^{-5/6} = 0.0231 is already checked (v16); here the EXPONENT origin is closed exactly. (1) [E] carrier hypercharge Y = roots of 6Y^2-Y-1=0 = {-1/3,1/2}, diag(-1/3,-1/3,-1/3,1/2,1/2); tr_E Y^2 = 3(1/3)^2+2(1/2)^2 = 5/6, complement 1/6 (the neutrino ratio). (2) [E] exponent gamma=5/6 IS tr_E Y^2, so sin^2 th13 = phi0 e^{-tr_E Y^2}. (3) [C] value 0.02311 vs PDG ~0.0222. (4) [E] OWN CHANNEL: the mu-tau-breaking eps=3phi0/4 induces only ~1.6e-3 << 0.023, so theta_13 is a separate carrier-trace channel, NOT the seesaw mu-tau breaking (corrects the tempting 'theta_13 from M_nu' route). (5) [O] CP magnitude + absolute nu scale remain open. Closes the theta_13 exponent origin, not full PMNS. Python-only (sympy+mpmath)."),
    ("v269_spert_paqft_skeleton", "QFT4D.SPERT.01: the perturbative 4D S-matrix (S_pert) as an Epstein-Glaser / pAQFT skeleton -- the honest middle layer of the three-layer S-matrix, NOT a nonperturbative closure. (1) [E] THREE-LAYER TYPING: S_top = 2d DHR braiding |M|=1 (statistics, v243), S_pert = 4d EG/BV S-matrix of the spectral action, S_phys = LSZ[OS Wightman] (v240) -- three distinct objects (the 2d braiding is NOT the 4d cross-section S-matrix). (2) [E] POWER-COUNTING RENORMALIZABLE: every spectral-action a_4 operator has mass dim <= 4 in 4D. (3) [E] FINITE COUNTERTERM BASIS: 7 marginal (dim-4) + 3 relevant (dim<4), no infinite tower. (4) [C] EPSTEIN-GLASER EXISTENCE: a renormalizable interaction has an order-by-order S(g)=T exp(i int g L_int) by causal factorisation + finite local extension (no path integral, no UV divergences); the spectral action qualifies. (5) [C] ADIABATIC/GAP: Delta=6log(3/2)>0 gives an IR-safe adiabatic limit + asymptotic states, S_pert -> S_phys via LSZ. (6) [O] nonperturbative residual: S_pert is perturbative; ambient measure QG.AMB.01 stays open. A contract/skeleton (like v244), explicitly perturbative. Python-only (sympy)."),
    ("v270_pmns_jarlskog_assembly", "FLAV.PMNS.03: the complete complex PMNS matrix + the leptonic Jarlskog J_PMNS (CP strength), assembled from the four TFPT channels (sin^2 th12 = 1/3 - phi0/2 v9/v263, sin^2 th23 = 1/2 v9/v263, sin^2 th13 = phi0 e^{-5/6} v16/v268, delta = 4 pi/3 v231/v233) into one unitary object. (1) [E] the three angle channels; (2) [E] U = R23.U13(delta).R12 is exactly unitary; (3) [C] J_PMNS = Im(U_e1 U_mu2 U*_e2 U*_mu1) = s12 c12 s23 c23 s13 c13^2 sin(delta) = -0.02965 (formula and full matrix agree), J_max = 0.03424 -- a DERIVED CP strength, the leptonic analogue of the CKM J (v88); (4) [C] data: J_max vs NuFIT 0.0332 (~3%), J vs best fit -0.026, negative sign reproduced; (5) [O] delta is the mu6/triality phase (assembled input, NOT from M_nu/D_F) and the absolute scale (Sigma m_nu, M_R) stays open. Assembles PMNS + CP strength; does not derive delta from D_F nor fix the scale. Python-only (mpmath+numpy; like v88, no Wolfram)."),
    ("v271_eg_oneloop_quartic", "QFT4D.SPERT.02: a concrete Epstein-Glaser order-2 (one-loop) calculation taking the v269 S_pert skeleton from 'exists' to an actual EG renormalization number. (1) [E] order structure: T_1 = :L_int: needs no extension, the first EG extension is the order-2 product T_2. (2) [E] scaling degree: sd(D_F)=2 in d=4, the one-loop bubble (two propagators) has sd=4=d so the UV singular order omega=sd-d=0. (3) [E] one logarithmic counterterm: omega=0 => C(omega+d,d)=1 local constant (renormalizable, finite, no infinite tower). (4) [E] loop factor Omega_3/(2(2pi)^4)=1/(16 pi^2) exactly -- the same factor that normalises the spectral-action a_4. (5) [C] one-loop beta_lambda = 3 lambda^2/(16 pi^2) (symmetry 3 = s,t,u channels), EG initial condition lambda_Phi(UV)=1/(16 pi^2). (6) [O] order-2/one-loop only; all-order EG + nonperturbative measure QG.AMB.01 stay open. Exact core mirrored in Wolfram. Python (sympy+math)."),
    ("v272_nu_mass_scale", "FLAV.NUSCALE.01: the absolute neutrino-mass scale, typed honestly (does NOT fabricate a Sigma m_nu number -- would contradict the v184 firewall). (1) [E] the absolute scale reduces to ONE seesaw ratio m_3 = (y_nu v_EW)^2/M_R -- one irreducible UV input like v_geo (v153); the ratios (m2/m3, ordering, PMNS angles v270) are pinned. (2) [N] the observed m_3 = 0.050 eV with the TFPT PS->GUT window M_R in [4.2e13, 2.4e15] GeV (v249) requires y_nu in [0.26, 2.0] -- O(1), no tuning. (3) [O] M_R(y=1) = 6.1e14 has log_c3(M_R/Mbar) = 2.57 (non-integer), not a TFPT power, so the absolute value stays open. (4) [C] NO floor Sigma m_nu = 0.0586 eV consistent with cosmology (<0.072-0.12 eV). (5) [X] kill test: a cosmological Sigma < 0.0586 eV excludes the NO m1~0 spectrum. Closes the PMNS bookkeeping (last [O] = one seesaw ratio), not the number. Python-only (mpmath)."),
    ("v273_eg_gauge_running", "QFT4D.SPERT.03: the gauge sector of the EG one-loop (v271's quartic mechanism applied to the gauge self-energy). (1) [E] the one-loop gauge 2-point has scaling degree sd=4=d so omega=0 -> one counterterm per coupling (same marginal mechanism + loop factor 1/(16 pi^2) as v271). (2-4) [E] the one-loop b_i from the explicit carrier/SM content: b3 = -(11/3)(3)+(2/3)(6) = -7; b2 = -(11/3)(2)+(2/3)(6)+(1/3)(1/2) = -19/6; b1 = (3/5)[(2/3)(10)+(1/3)(1/2)] = 41/10 (the same 41 as the carrier algebra, v159/CAR.SM.01). (5) [C] physical RG directions b3<0 (asymptotic freedom), b1>0 (U(1) Landau). (6) [O] two-loop (v159 PyR@TE) + all-order stay open. Shows the gauge running is an EG order-2 result. Exact b_i mirrored in Wolfram. Python (sympy)."),
    ("v274_scale_overdetermination", "SCALE.OVERDET.01: the single mass anchor is OVER-DETERMINED, and the absence of a derivable absolute scale is a THEOREM. (1) [E] one anchor (No-Unit v153): every dimensionful output = pure number x M_bar^d (rho_Lambda/M_bar^4, M_scal/M_bar=c3^{7/2}, the spectrum). (2) [N] two independent routes to M_bar agree: gravity (8 pi G)^{-1/2}=2.4353e18 GeV and cosmology (invert rho_Lambda/M_bar^4=(3/4pi^2)e^{-2 alpha^-1} with rho_L^{1/4}=2.24 meV)=2.438e18 GeV, to 0.11%. (3) [E] the anchor is the gravitational unit (G), the one measured dimensionful input of all physics. (4) [E] theorem not gap: the seam is a conformal c=8 CFT (v157/v158), scale-invariant by construction -> no intrinsic scale. (5) [A] scale-complete up to one over-determined anchor = maximal predictivity. Sharpens v153/v78. Python-only (mpmath)."),
    ("v275_qgamb_roadmap", "QGAMB.ROADMAP.01: the obligation roadmap for QG.AMB.01 (the ambient nonperturbative QG measure), consolidated into one module (the gate had no script). (1) [E] Tier A gap decoupling: Delta_eff = 6log(3/2) - 2*248 c3^2 = 1.648 > 0 (v36/v76), so every low-energy readout is independent of the un-built measure -- not a blocker. (2) [E]/[P] Tier B: the bulk measure reduces to identifying the seam-Calderon boundary with the holomorphic (E8)_1 net (c=248/31=8; v77/GATE.METRIC.03), reduced not closed (REDTEAM.A.01). (3) [C] perturbative layer in hand (v269/v271/v273). (4) [O] the nonperturbative ambient measure is NOT constructed -- the one genuine structural frontier. (5) [X] closes IFF seam net = (E8)_1 AND bulk reconstruction proved. A roadmap, not a closure. Python-only (sympy)."),
    ("v276_qgeo_flat_closes_commutator", "QGEO.SYM.03: the flat tau=i pillowcase premise CLOSES the modular-commutator chain to all orders, collapsing the bedrock QGEO.SYM.01 to ONE geometric postulate. Reduction: for a quasi-free seam state, QGEO.SYM.01 = (omega o rho = omega) <=> [rho,C]=0 <=> [rho,H]=0 (C=(1+e^H)^-1, v258). (1) [E] ISOMETRY=>COMMUTATOR: if H=f(Delta_flat) and rho (z->iz) is a flat-tau=i isometry then [rho,Delta]=0 => [rho,H]=[rho,f(Delta)]=0 EXACTLY (all orders); verified on the discretised square torus (rho^4=I, [rho,Delta]=0, [rho,sqrt(-Delta)]=0); generic non-isometry fails (control). (2) [E] ALL-ORDERS UPGRADE: rho commutes with every spectral function of Delta, upgrading v198 (principal) + v201 (subprincipal) to the full H -- flatness removes curvature terms. (3) [C] tau=i forced by order-4 (j=1728; hexagonal j=0 is order-6, excluded; v214/v267). (4) [O] QGEO.SYM.01 collapses to ONE geometric statement 'the raw seam IS the flat tau=i pillowcase quasi-free state' -- needs a human constructive-QFT proof or stays axiom. Narrows, does not close. Python (numpy+scipy+sympy)."),
    ("v277_seam_calderon_e8_match", "QGAMB.TIERB.01: the seam-Calderon -> (E8)_1 matching certificate -- the concrete Tier-B step of QG.AMB.01 (v275). Computes the FULL (E8)_1 matching target and pins the residual to ONE bit. (1) [E] c=8 (Sugawara, 248/31=g_car+N_fam); c=8 alone does NOT pin the net. (2) [E] DISCRIMINATOR=HOLOMORPHY: det Cartan(E8)=1 (1 primary, holomorphic) vs the c=8 counterexample det Cartan(D8=SO(16))=4 (4 primaries, non-holomorphic) -> single discriminator |det K|=1. (3) [E] the (E8)_1 character E4/eta^8 = j^{1/3} = q^{-1/3}(1+248q+...) has a single primary + exactly 248=dim E8 weight-1 currents (240 roots). (4) [E] equivalence chain: holomorphic <=> det Cartan 1 <=> unique even unimodular rank-8 (v83) <=> homology-sphere link <=> |det K|=1 (v235). (5) [C] seam-side match via v276 (flat tau=i) + v260 (K3). (6) [O] residual = the single holomorphy bit; reduced to one bit, NOT closed. Exact core mirrored in Wolfram. Python (numpy+sympy)."),
    ("v278_lsz_bridge_unitarity", "QFT4D.SPERT.04: the S_pert -> S_phys LSZ bridge + one-loop unitarity. Connects the EG perturbative S-matrix (v269/v271/v273) to the physical asymptotic S-matrix (S_phys = LSZ on the OS Wightman functions, v240) and verifies perturbative unitarity at one loop. (1) [E] LSZ bridge: S_phys = amputate+on-shell-residue of the connected T-products, and the EG T-products of S_pert ARE those correlators (OS Wick-rotation, v240) -> S_pert --LSZ--> S_phys. (2) [C] gap Delta=6log(3/2)>0 -> Haag-Ruelle asymptotic states -> LSZ valid. (3) [E] ONE-LOOP UNITARITY (optical theorem): the bubble discontinuity Im B(s)/pi = x_+ - x_- = sqrt(1-4m^2/s) EXACTLY = the two-body phase space, so 2 Im M = sum_int dPi |M|^2 (cutting rule) holds -> matter+gauge unitary. (4) [E] threshold: Im B=0 below s=4m^2, turns on at the physical 2-particle threshold. (5) [O] gravity caveat: the Stelle ghost makes the gravity perturbative S-matrix non-unitary -> QG.AMB.01. (6) [C] finite Z from the EG scheme. Exact core (cut=phase space) mirrored in Wolfram. Python (sympy)."),
    ("v279_qgeo_obligation_lemma", "QGEO.OBLIG.01: the QGEO.SYM.01 bedrock written as ONE precise constructive-QFT lemma + a proof-tree completeness check. Lemma: given the premise 'the raw seam carries the flat tau=i pillowcase metric g_flat (Troyanov-unique, cone angles pi), so Lambda_Sigma = sqrt(-Delta_flat)', then omega_Sigma o rho = omega_Sigma (the carrier clock is a symmetry of the seam STATE) -> mark-locality -> E8. (1) [E] PROOF-TREE COMPLETENESS: the reduction DAG from 'free RP seam' has 8 closed nodes and EXACTLY ONE open leaf ('raw seam state IS the flat state'). (2) [E] the geometric side is fixed (flat DtN diagonal, rho commutes to all orders, Lean FORM.QGEO.03) -> the obligation is STATE-IDENTIFICATION, not geometric ambiguity. (3) [C] two proof routes: RP-state uniqueness on the flat orbifold, or Troyanov + OS. (4) [F] the all-orders step is a Lean theorem (SeamDeckClosure.flat_all_orders_clock, only standard axioms, no sorry). (5) [O] one constructive-QFT statement closes QGEO.SYM.01. The formal obligation write-up; does NOT close it. Python (graph completeness)."),
    ("v280_pillowcase_steklov", "QGEO.STEKLOV.01: a direct numerical experiment on the flat tau=i pillowcase orbifold (the seam geometry), realising the QGEO chain on the geometric side. (1) [E] pillowcase = Z2-even sector of the flat torus; 4 cone points (2-torsion), deficit pi each, sum 4pi=2pi*2 (Gauss-Bonnet). (2) [E] the order-4 deck rho (z->iz) descends ([rho,Z2]=[rho,P_even]=0) and permutes the 4 cone points as 2 fixed + 1 swapped pair. (3) [E] geometric chain exact: [rho,Delta]=0 => [rho,H]=0 (H=sqrt(-Delta)) => [rho,C]=0 (C=(1+e^H)^-1) => omega o rho = omega, all numerical -- the v276/v279 all-orders closure on the real orbifold. (4) [C] RP-state determined: the Steklov DtN is positive self-adjoint, fixed by the flat metric (route-(i) evidence). (5) [O] confirms the conclusion given flat; the premise stays open. A self-investigable experiment. Python (numpy+scipy)."),
    ("v281_holomorphy_modular_data", "QGAMB.MODULAR.01: the modular-data / anyon-condensation layer of the QG.AMB.01 Tier-B holomorphy bit. (1) [E] #anyons=|det Gram|: E8->1 (holomorphic), D8=SO(16)->4, carrier D5(+)A3->16. (2) [E] anyon-condensation tower D5(+)A3 (16) -> D8 (4) -> E8 (1), each step condensing a Lagrangian Z2 boson (|det|/4=2^2), the Kitaev E8 endpoint. (3) [E] Gauss-Milgram (D8 spins 0,1/2,1,1) recovers c=8. (4) [E] E8 unique holomorphic c=8 (det 1); SO(16) same c=8 but 4 anyons -> holomorphy is THE discriminator. (5) [O] the open bit: does the seam net condense to det K=1? Reduced to one bit. Exact core mirrored in Wolfram. Python (numpy+sympy)."),
    ("v282_e8_tau_i_unification", "QGAMB.UNIFY.01: the E8-at-tau=i unification -- the candidate SIMPLIFICATION reducing the two open obligations to ONE object. chi_E8(tau)=Theta_E8/eta^8=j^{1/3}. (1) [E] tau=i is the order-4 CM point (j=1728, QGEO side). (2) [E] chi_E8=j^{1/3} (chi^3=q*j as q-series), so chi_E8(i)=1728^{1/3}=12 (QG.AMB side, the (E8)_1 character at the same tau=i). (3) [E] one object two faces: tau=i is both the order-4 CM point (flat geometry, QGEO.SYM.01) and the (E8)_1 partition-function modulus (holomorphy, QG.AMB.01). (4) [C] obligation count 2->1: 'the raw seam is (E8)_1 at tau=i' implies BOTH. (5) [O] the unified premise stays open but is now ONE object. Exact core mirrored in Wolfram. Python (sympy)."),
    ("v283_live_killtest_scorecard", "PRED.LIVE.01: a live kill-test scorecard of the recent round's computable predictions vs current data, each tagged with the decisive experiment. (1) [N] PMNS angles: sin^2 th12=0.30675 (+0.31 sigma), sin^2 th13=0.02311 (+1.45 sigma), th23 maximal. (2) [C] leptonic CP: J_PMNS=-0.0297 (J_max ~3% from NuFIT), delta=240 vs ~232(30). (3) [X] Sigma m_nu NO floor=0.0586 eV (consistent, edge; DESI/CMB-S4 decisive). (4) [X] proton decay tau_p=1.55e35 yr for +(15,1,1) (safe; minimal excluded; Hyper-K decisive). (5) [N] closed readouts alpha^-1, Omega_b, beta. (6) [N] all rows consistent < 2 sigma; 2 sharp near-term kill tests. A consolidation, not new physics. Python (mpmath)."),
    ("v284_route_i_rp_uniqueness", "QGEO.ROUTEI.01: Route (i) (RP-state uniqueness) decomposed into a 6-lemma chain with every dischargeable lemma discharged and the one irreducible lemma isolated (does NOT prove the open premise). [E] 5/6 lemmas are existing [E]/[F] results: L1 RP->DtN (v194), L2 four marks force the pillowcase class (v195/v216/v214), L3 flat orbifold Steklov = sqrt(-Delta_flat) (verified here: flat-strip DtN(k)/k->1, principal symbol |xi| no curvature term), L4 covariance C=(1+e^H)^-1 from DtN (v258), L5 mu4-invariance (v276/Lean/v280). [C] Troyanov reduction: 4 cone points angle pi => chi_orb=0 => unique flat (tau=i) representative, so L_open reduces to 'the raw seam is the constant-curvature geometric state'. [O] the ONE open lemma: the raw RP seam state is the constant-curvature/geometric state (the state-identification step). Python (numpy+sympy)."),
    ("v285_route_ii_seam_condensation", "QGAMB.ROUTEII.01: Route (ii) (seam-net condensation) decomposed into a 4-lemma chain, with the key result that its open lemma COINCIDES with Route (i)'s (v282 at lemma level). [E] 3/4 lemmas discharged: M1 no abelian sector <=> |det K|=1 <=> holomorphic (v234/v235), M2 holomorphic c=8 <=> (E8)_1, SO(16) det 4 counterexample (v277/v281), M3 the tower 16->4->1 = unique mu4-Lagrangian glue (v92/v281/v235). [E] discriminator det 1 vs det 4. [E] Routes (i) and (ii) SHARE one open lemma -- both say 'the raw seam IS the (E8)_1-at-tau=i object' (v282), so proving either closes both. [O] the unified open lemma (the reviewer's exact demand): construct a canonical equivalence between the raw seam KMS/DtN state and the holomorphic (E8)_1 net at tau=i. M_open = QGEO.SYM.01. Python."),
    ("v286_seam_equivalence_contract", "SEAM.EQUIV.01: the Seam Equivalence contract -- concentrates the whole open structure on ONE named arrow (does NOT prove it). Theorem: the raw RP seam state reconstructs canonically the holomorphic (E8)_1 boundary net at the tau=i pillowcase ('the raw seam is (E8)_1 at tau=i'). (1) [E] four objects typed (RawRPSeam, FlatTauIPillowcaseDtN, HolomorphicE8Net, SREKitaevE8Phase); (2) [E] six arrows: 2 closed (Route i v276/v280/v284, Route ii v281/v277/v235), 1 conditional (v282), 2 open premises (the same lemma, v284/v285), 1 Gral; (3) [E] IMPORT FIREWALL: no Route-i module imports any Route-ii module or vice versa -- the routes converge only through SEAM.EQUIV.01 (no E8-into-geometry-and-back circularity); (4) [E] exact-label taxonomy (Formal/Numerical/Conditional Exact, Open Selection); (5) [O] the one open arrow 'free Gaussian RP bulk => holomorphic single-sector boundary'. Writes seam_equivalence.json. Python (stdlib)."),
    ("v287_free_rp_bulk_to_holomorphic_boundary", "SEAM.EQUIV.A01: Route A (AQFT) theorem-dependency checker for the open Gral arrow 'free Gaussian RP bulk => holomorphic single-sector boundary net'. Types the 5-lemma chain and isolates the ONE missing standard theorem. [E] L1 RawRPSeam --OS--> CAR/quasi-free boundary (v155/v160/v240/v175); [E] L2 gap+chirality => gapped chiral bulk (v64/v156); [O] L3 invertible/SRE Gaussian bulk => single-sector boundary (mu-index 1) -- THE ONE MISSING STANDARD THEOREM (AQFT form of det K=1); [E] L4 mu=1+c=8 => holomorphic (v234); [E] L5 holomorphic c=8 => (E8)_1 (v83/v277/v281). Verdict: 4/5 discharged, Route A reduces SEAM.EQUIV.01 to one cited theorem (invertibility => single-sector). Python (structural)."),
    ("v288_full_l2_subprincipal_z4", "SEAM.EQUIV.B01: Route B (DtN) -- the full-L^2 lift of the sub-principal Z4 block-diagonality, PROVING (numerically, on the full Toeplitz operator) the 'probably provable' step and lifting v201/v284 from the finite block to L^2. (1) [E] character orthogonality: a mark-sourced curvature f=sum_{j<4} g(theta-j pi/2) has Fourier support only on m==0 mod 4 (nonzero modes {0,+-4,+-8,+-12}); (2) [E] full-L^2 block-diagonality: Lambda=|n|+M_f commutes with rho=diag(i^n), ||[rho,Lambda]||~2e-15 on -50..50; (3) [E] negative control: a generic curvature gives ||[rho,Lambda]||=4.44>0; (4) [E] Lean consistency (geom_sum_fourth_root + markLocal_blockDiagonal); (5) [O] the sharper residual: why is the raw seam sub-principal term mark-local?; (6) [E] SCOPE FIREWALL: does NOT prove 'full-L^2 QGEO' -- Fourier lemma = Formal/Exact, numerical test = Numerical Exact, transfer to raw conic DtN = Conditional (v264), mark-locality from RP seam = Open Selection (v289). Python (numpy FFT + Toeplitz)."),
    ("v289_marklocal_raw", "MARKLOCAL.RAW.01: decompose the ONE remaining Route-B residual ('why is the raw seam sub-principal term mark-local?') into a 5-lemma chain and isolate the single open analytic lemma (Flat-Away). L1 [C] conic parametrix: conic Steklov DtN = |D_theta| + M_f + cone sources (b-calculus/Melrose, imported); L2 [O] FLAT-AWAY -- the one open analytic lemma: RP+gap+4 marks => curvature vanishes away from the marks (the flat-pillowcase realisation); L3 [E] orbit-source: the 4 marks form one mu4 orbit (v195/v216); L4 [E] Fourier-support: mu4-orbit curvature => support only on 4Z (v264/v288, FFT, with a non-orbit negative control); L5 [E] full-operator: => [rho,Lambda]=0 on full L^2 (v288). 4/5 discharged; Route B reduces to exactly L2 (if it falls, Route B closes). Python (numpy FFT)."),
    ("v290_z4_smooth_curvature_adversary", "SEAM.ADVERSARY.01: the Route-B red-team that Z4 block-diagonality is NOT mark-locality. Constructs the strongest adversary -- a SMOOTH Z4-symmetric off-mark curvature f=eps*cos(4 theta) -- and shows honestly: (1) [E] it is Z4-symmetric (Fourier support {+-4} subset 4Z) but NOT mark-local (f(pi/4)=-eps != 0); (2) [E] it PASSES the v288 commutator ||[rho,Lambda]||=0 (same as mark-local; i^n-i^(n+-4)=0) -- so [rho,Lambda]=0 is necessary but NOT sufficient; (3) [E] BUT it shifts the DtN spectrum off the flat ladder (max|dlambda|=0.155 at eps=0.3); (4) [E] and the heat trace Tr(e^{-tL}) (delta=0.019) -- the KMS weight + (E8)_1 character shift; (5) [O] verdict: a genuine candidate modulus the commutator misses but the spectral data excludes -- so Flat-Away must use spectral/energy/heat input, not Z4-invariance. Honest red-team, no manufactured pass. Python (numpy)."),
    ("v291_flataway_contract", "FLATAWAY.RP.01: the Flat-Away lemma as its own named mini-theorem with three proof routes opened by v290. LEMMA [O]: given RawRPSeam with gap, chirality and the four mu4 marks, the smooth curvature density in the DtN sub-principal symbol vanishes away from the branch divisor. [E] SPECTRAL-RIGIDITY route: scanning f=eps*cos(4 theta), the spectrum deviation from the flat ladder is 0 ONLY at eps=0 and grows with |eps| -- flat is the unique spectral match. [E] HEAT-KERNEL route: the heat-trace deviation is 0 ONLY at eps=0 -- smooth off-mark curvature adds heat coefficients. [C] RP-ENERGY route: RP+gap = Dirichlet-energy minimisation in the Troyanov conformal class => constant-curvature minimiser (Troyanov; cf. v284). [O] verdict: 3 independent routes to ONE lemma; closing any one closes Route B. Python (numpy)."),
    ("v292_flataway_heat_reduction", "FLATAWAY.HEAT.01: the Heat-Kernel route made precise -- reduces Flat-Away to ONE named spectral invariant. (1) [E] QUADRATIC: Delta Tr(e^{-tL}) = c(t) eps^2 + O(eps^4) (Delta Tr/eps^2 constant ~0.208), no first-order term; (2) [E] POSITIVE-DEFINITE PER MODE: c_k(t)>0 for every Z4 mode 4k (k=1,2,3: 0.066,0.047,0.033); (3) [E] POSITIVE-DEFINITE ON COMBINATIONS: random Z4 combos give Delta Tr>0, no cancellation, so Delta Tr=0 <=> f=0; (4) [E] leading invariant is ||f||_L^2 (Parseval); (5) [O] reduction: Flat-Away <= 'the seam fixes the a_2 heat coefficient to its flat value' (then int f^2=0 => f=0 off marks). One external invariant. Python (numpy)."),
    ("v293_flataway_spectral_hessian", "FLATAWAY.SPEC.01: the Spectral-Rigidity route upgraded from one direction (v291) to the FULL smooth-Z4 space. (1) [E] SPLITTING MECHANISM: the degenerate flat level |n| is split by mode 4k at |n|=2k by +-eps/2 (modes 4,8,12 split levels 2,4,6); (2) [E] QUADRATIC: S=sum(dlambda)^2 ~ 0.50 eps^2; (3) [E] HESSIAN POSITIVE-DEFINITE: H over modes {4,8,12} has eigenvalues ~{0.497,0.500,0.503}>0, so flat is a STRICT isolated minimum over the whole Z4 space (answers 'only one direction'); (4) [E] clock-filter contrast: a non-Z4 mode (cos2theta) breaks the commutator outright; (5) [O] consequence: pinning the seam's Steklov spectrum excludes every smooth Z4 deformation => Flat-Away. Python (numpy)."),
    ("v294_flataway_rp_energy", "FLATAWAY.ENERGY.01: the RP-energy / Troyanov route -- flat is the unique constant-curvature minimiser at the fixed mark divisor. (1) [E] PRESCRIBED DIVISOR + GAUSS-BONNET: S^2 with 4 cone angles pi, sum(2pi-theta)=4pi=2pi*chi; (2) [C] TROYANOV/Euclidean-cone uniqueness: the prescribed cone divisor has a UNIQUE constant-curvature (flat) metric (Troyanov 1991), excluding smooth off-mark curvature; (3) [E] STRICTLY CONVEX curvature energy E[f]=int f^2, Hessian 2pi*I (PD) => unique minimiser; (4) [E] no zero-cost deformation (E[eps cos4ktheta]=pi eps^2>0); (5) [O] premise: 'RP+gap realises the energy-minimiser', converging with v292 (a_2) and v293 (spectrum) on ONE selection principle. Python (numpy)."),
    ("v295_flataway_a2_exact", "FLATAWAY.A2.01: the EXACT analytic a_2 coefficient, upgrading the v292 positive-definiteness from numerical to a proof. (1) [E] FIRST VARIATION VANISHES: d/deps Tr e^{-tL(eps)}|_0 = -t f_hat(0) sum e^{-t|n|} = 0 since the smooth off-mark curvature has zero mean (Gauss-Bonnet); (2) [E] CONVEXITY => GLOBAL MINIMUM: phi(x)=e^{-tx} strictly convex => L|->Tr e^{-tL} convex (Klein/Peierls), so with zero first variation eps=0 is the GLOBAL minimum and Delta Tr>=0 for ALL eps (verified even in eps over [-1,2]), =0 iff f=0 -- the exact positive-definiteness; (3) [E] EXACT a_2 KERNEL: Delta Tr^(2) = (1/4) sum_n [Phi(|n|,|n+4k|)+Phi(|n|,|n-4k|)] g^2 with the divided-difference kernel Phi(a,b)=[(b-a)t e^{bt}+e^{at}-e^{bt}]e^{-t(a+b)}/(a-b)^2 (Phi(a,a)=(t^2/2)e^{-ta}), derived by Duhamel and matched to numerics to rel.err<1e-6; (4) [E] DEGENERATE-SPLIT closed form 2 e^{-2kt}(cosh(tg/2)-1)>=0; (5) [O] reduction now analytic: Flat-Away <= 'the seam fixes a_2'. Lean-mirrored (FORM.FLATAWAY.01). Python (sympy + numpy)."),
    ("v296_flataway_a2_closed", "FLATAWAY.A2.CLOSED.01: the exact a_2 coefficient in CLOSED FORM (replacing v295's validated-numeric sum). (1) [E] the operator tails telescope to a geometric series: Phi(n,n+4k)=e^{-nt} C_k/(16k^2) for n>=0, and C_k + D_k e^{-4kt} = 4kt(1-e^{-4kt}), giving the closed tail W_k^tail = t(1-e^{-4kt})/(8k(1-e^{-t})); (2) [E] the middle is finite (4k-1 terms incl. the degenerate diagonal Phi(2k,2k)=(t^2/2)e^{-2kt}); (3) [E] closed form W_k(t)=t(1-e^{-4kt})/(8k(1-e^{-t}))+(1/2)sum_{m=1}^{4k-1}Phi(m,4k-m), W_1(t)=t(2t e^t+e^{3t}+3e^{2t}+e^t-1)e^{-3t}/8, reproduces v295 to machine precision; (4) [E] positivity manifest term by term; (5) [E] small-t W_k=t/2+O(t^3) (mode-independent leading 1/2, the t^2 term cancels). Python (sympy + numpy)."),
    ("v297_route_a_literature_stack", "SEAM.EQUIV.A.LIT.01: Route A's 'one standard import' written out as a precise CITABLE theorem stack. [E] LIT-A invertible/SRE bulk => trivial bulk topological order (Kitaev Ann.Phys.321 2006; Freed-Hopkins Geom.Topol.25 2021); [E] LIT-B bulk MTC=Drinfeld center, trivial center => holomorphic boundary net (Mueger JPAA 180 2003; Kawahigashi-Longo-Mueger CMP 219 2001); [E] LIT-C holomorphic c=8 net => (E8)_1 (Conway-Sloane lattice uniqueness; Dong-Xu/Kawahigashi-Longo). [E] the three COMPOSE (out=in matches) into 'invertible bulk => (E8)_1', all three legs established; [O] the ONE open hypothesis is the input of LIT-A, 'the raw quasi-free seam bulk is invertible (SRE)' = Route B's Flat-Away. [E] non-circular with Route B (no DtN/Steklov; the v286 firewall holds). Python (stdlib)."),
    ("v298_e8_network_attractor", "E8 as a network attractor -- a computational-substrate (Wolfram-program) reading of the (2,3,5)/McKay hull, on the v219 bedrock; an HONEST audit of the 'TFPT as hypergraph' idea, not a derivation. [E] E8 MARKS ARE A GRAPH ATTRACTOR: the minimal lazy update m<-(A+2I)/4 m on the affine-E8/(2,3,5) McKay graph converges from ANY positive start to the Kac marks (1,2,3,4,5,6,4,2,3) (unique stationary state, A·m=2m, top eigenvalue 2). [E] SPHERICAL TOWER TERMINATES AT E8 (2T->E6 h12, 2O->E7 h18, 2I->E8 h30=2*3*5). [E] CASCADE = nested-subgraph coarse-graining (240->126->72->40->20). [C] WOLFRAM-BRIDGE READING: E8 = universal attractor of a minimal (2,3,5) network, at the Coxeter-skeleton level. [O] HONEST SCOPE: a minimal hypergraph REWRITE whose attractor is the FULL TFPT structure stays open; NEG controls: phi0=(4/3)c3=1/(6pi) is the analytic seed NOT an edge fraction, recovery is a 1-D Mobius fixed point not a rewrite. Python (numpy)."),
    ("v299_hypergraph_0d_autonomous", "the hypergraph/Wolfram bridge, hardened: P2 is the MINIMAL (2,3,*) seed on which a LOCAL witness-based spectral growth is forced through E6->E7->E8 and stops at the affine boundary E8-hat (E8 = maximal FINITE point). NOT 'P2 derived'. [E] HYP.ICO.01 icosahedron = 3-uniform hypergraph (12 V, 20 hyperedges, 30 edges=h(E8)), |Aut|=120=|2I image|; [E] HYP.REWRITE.01 the 1->4 subdivision rewrite preserves all 120 symmetries at every scale (12->42->162); [E] HYP.FUSION.01 the 2I fusion tensor is a nonneg-integer weighted 3-uniform hypergraph, 2-dim slice = affine E8 McKay graph; [E] HYP.SMITH.01 rho<=2 selects (affine) ADE (Smith); [E] HYP.CW.01 Collatz-Wielandt: rho<=2 <=> a positive witness m with A m<=2m (local per-node); [E*] HYP.AUTO.01 self-generated witness (projectively-normalised diffusion) + LOCAL gate A m<=2m runs E6->E7->E8->E8-hat, critical witness = Kac marks (under the (2,3,*) seed + grow-longest-leg policy); [E] HYP.NEG.AN.01 path A_n control never reaches E8; [E] HYP.NEG.DN.01 D_n control never reaches E8; [O] HYP.SEED.01 the (2,3,*) seed is the single irreducible input = P2. A second network reading of the (2,3,5)/E8 core. Python (numpy; imports v219)."),
    ("v300_flataway_rigid", "FLATAWAY.RIGID.01: the attack on Flat-Away -- (I) HARDEN the obstruction from a soft minimum (v291/v293) to a DISCRETE one, and (II) DERIVE the external pin from the (E8)_1 data. [E] FLAT FINGERPRINT: spec(|D_theta|) is the integer ladder, every level n>=1 of multiplicity exactly 2 (a discrete fingerprint, not a norm). [E] EXACT DEGENERATE SPLIT: the resonant mode 4k splits level 2k by gap = g_k (sympy 2x2 [[2k,g/2],[g/2,2k]] -> 2k+-g/2; + O(g^2) common shift), validated vs the full Toeplitz operator. [E] HARD OBSTRUCTION: any g_k!=0 lifts the resonant degeneracy (mult 2->1+1) and changes the spectral MULTISET, so preserving the flat ladder *with its mult-2 degeneracies* forces every g_k=0 => f=0 (a degeneracy obstruction, strictly stronger than the v291/v293 'deviation grows' scan). [E] TWO-METRIC ISOLATION: with the v295 convexity (Delta Tr>=0, =0 iff f=0), flat is isolated analytically AND discretely. [C] THE PIN DERIVED: the (E8)_1 vacuum character E4/eta^8 = q^{-1/3}(1+248q+4124q^2+...) has integer q-coefficients with 248 at level 1 (E8 even unimodular => integer weights); by 2d Steklov conformal rigidity the integer ladder <=> flat seam, so (E8)_1 rationality => f=0 (conditional on Route A). [O] VERDICT: Flat-Away carries ZERO new open content beyond Route A; the convexity side is unconditional, the discrete obstruction exact; the two SEAM.EQUIV.01 routes converge on one rationality fact. Python (numpy + sympy)."),
    ("v301_route_a_invertible", "SEAM.EQUIV.A.INV.01: discharge Route A's single open hypothesis (v297 LIT-A: 'the raw quasi-free seam bulk is invertible/SRE') via the free-fermion classification -- since v300 collapsed Route B into Route A, this is the LAST unconditional gap of SEAM.EQUIV.01. [E] CARRIER=16 MAJORANAS, c=8: g_car+N_fam=5+3=8=16/2 (v148 NS/R census). [E] SO(16)_1 ⊃ (E8)_1: dim so(16)=120 currents + 128 spinor = 248 = dim E8 (v154 simple-current extension). [C] FREE-FERMION INVERTIBILITY (Kitaev periodic table): a gapped Gaussian/quasi-free 2+1D fermion phase (class D) is Z-classified by the chiral Majorana number and is ALWAYS invertible (no intrinsic anyons; topological order needs interactions) -- so a gapped quasi-free bulk is invertible automatically. [E] INVARIANT |det K|=#anyons: E8 Cartan det=1 (one primary => invertible) vs the gauged contrast D8=SO(16) det=4 (anyons), which free fermions cannot produce. [O] REDUCTION: LIT-A's 'invertible bulk' now FOLLOWS from 'gapped 16-Majorana quasi-free bulk' (v148+v160+the gap); the residual changes from a topological-order statement to the spectral input 'is the quasi-free bulk gapped?'. [O] VERDICT: with v300 (Route B = Route A rationality) the WHOLE open content of SEAM.EQUIV.01 reduces to the single spectral statement 'the quasi-free seam bulk is gapped'. Python (numpy + sympy)."),
    ("v302_seam_gap", "SEAM.EQUIV.GAP.01: the LAST lever -- after v300/v301 the whole open content of SEAM.EQUIV.01 was 'the quasi-free seam bulk is gapped'; here that gap is shown NOT to be a free input but the established RECOVERY GAP of the seam transfer operator. [E] TRANSFER SPECTRUM: spec(T)={1,(2/3)^6,(1/3)^6}={1,64/729,1/729} (v160/v162), simple leading Perron eigenvalue 1, rest <1. [E] THE GAP IS DERIVED: Delta=-ln((2/3)^6)=6 ln(3/2)=2 N_fam ln(3/2)~2.4328>0 (mult. gap 1-(2/3)^6=665/729); 6=2 N_fam, (2/3)^6 the mu4-deck transfer eigenvalue -- forced by the carrier, not assumed. [E] POSITIVITY MARGIN: Delta-31/(4pi^2)=1.6476>0 (the v76 decoupling margin), robust not marginal. [C] OS/QUASI-FREE CLUSTERING: for an RP quasi-free system a transfer gap Delta>0 <=> exponential clustering <=> a mass gap of the OS-reconstructed Hamiltonian (so the bulk mass gap = the transfer gap). [O] VERDICT: the last TFPT-internal input is realised by the derived Recovery gap 6 ln(3/2)>0, so SEAM.EQUIV.01's residual is a composition of cited theorems (OS/clustering + Kitaev v301 + the v297 AQFT stack) over established TFPT facts (16 quasi-free Majoranas; transfer gap 6 ln(3/2)) -- no undischarged TFPT-internal assumption remains; stays [O] (not machine-proved end-to-end). Python (sympy + mpmath)."),
    ("v303_ftransfer_dynamics", "FR.DYNAMICS.01: the discrete->dynamic lens on F_transfer -- is the main-branch mechanism (a gapped, positivity-preserving relaxation to a UNIQUE attractor; local-averaging update -> E8 marks, gap 6 log(3/2)) also the shape of the four F_transfer instances? [E] F_pole (Koide) IS the seam dynamics: the source->pole/branch relaxation is the Moebius map with fixed-point multiplier F'=(2/3)^6 = lambda_2 = the seam clock subleading eigenvalue (v82/v54), |F'|<1 => a unique attractor at the SEAM rate. [C] F_Boltzmann (eta_B): a gapped positive contraction (washout kappa_f in (0,1) -> the unique balance, H-theorem), compiler fixes A_Lambda=10, rate thermal. [C] F_relic (axion): the misalignment comoving number freezes to a constant (adiabatic fixed point), seed theta_i=3pi/5, rate cosmological. [I] F_QCD (m_p/m_e): the 1-loop RG flow with the carrier b3=-7 (asymptotic freedom) has the Gaussian UV fixed point as attractor, Lambda_QCD dynamically generated. [O] VERDICT: ONE shape (gapped relaxation/flow to a unique attractor: PF / H-theorem / RG fixed point) underlies all four = the main-branch principle; F_pole has the seam rate exactly, the other three share only the shape (external rates). F_transfer is the readout end of the one principle, NOT a bolt-on; simplicity is preserved by honest fencing (v187), not by reducing the external physics to the seam. Python (numpy)."),
    ("v304_idg_nonlocal_ghost", "QGAMB.IDG.01: the KMS spectral-action cutoff suggests a NONLOCAL (infinite-derivative) graviton form factor; under entire analyticity the Stelle ghost is a TRUNCATION ARTEFACT -- a CONDITIONAL narrowing of the rt_F perturbative-gravity attack, NOT a closure of QG.AMB.01 (no new parameter: the cutoff is the v259 seam KMS weight). [E] STELLE GHOST = TRUNCATION ARTEFACT: the local four-derivative propagator 1/(p^2(p^2+M^2))=(1/M^2)[1/p^2-1/(p^2+M^2)] has a healthy massless graviton (residue +1/M^2 at p^2=0) and a massive spin-2 mode with NEGATIVE residue -1/M^2 at p^2=-M^2 (reproduces rt_F/v278). [E] ENTIRE FORM FACTOR HAS NO EXTRA POLE: for an IDG kinetic operator p^2 a(p^2) with a(z)=e^{z/M^2} entire and nowhere zero (exp has no zeros), the dressed propagator 1/(p^2 a) has its ONLY pole at p^2=0 -- no ghost (Tomboulis 1997; Biswas-Mazumdar-Siegel 2006). [E] NEG CONTROL: a polynomial truncation a(z)=1+z/M^2 (R+R^2 order) has a real zero at z=-M^2 = the ghost pole, so 'entire vs polynomial' is the discriminator -- only the un-truncated factor is ghost-free. [C] the cutoff is the beta=1 seam KMS weight f(u)=e^{-u} (v259), not a choice; truncating Tr e^{-D^2/Lambda^2} at a_4 is what makes the local R+R^2 and the ghost. [C] CONDITIONAL NARROWING: IF the resummed form factor is entire (Biswas-Mazumdar-Siegel class) THEN the perturbative graviton is ghost-free and rt_F's attack is a truncation artefact. [O] OPEN: (i) the trace regulator f is NOT the kinetic form factor a(Box) -- entire analyticity of the resummation is unproven; (ii) a ghost-free perturbative graviton is not the nonperturbative ambient measure -- QGAMB.IDG.01 stays [C]/[O], NOT a QG.AMB.01 closure. Python (sympy)."),
    ("v305_witness_independence", "WITNESS.ECON.01: the STRUCTURAL firewall against 'one generator wearing many hats' (companion to the v100 phenomenological null test). [E] GENERATOR ECONOMY: every headline integer (|mu4|=4, g_car=5, |Z2|=2, N_fam=3, dim S+=16, rank E8=8, |R(E8)|=240, dim E8=248, |2I|=120, h(E8)=30, |W(D5)|=1920, Omega_adm=48, gap exponent 6) is a documented image of the single anchor a=(1,1,2) (e=(4,5,2), p_n=2+2^n; v23/v228), pi the only transcendental primitive (ARCH.CORE.01); 13 atoms / 2 free primitives = 6.5x compression made explicit (the recurring 2/3=|Z2|/N_fam and (2/3)^6 are ONE ratio). [E] WITNESS INDEPENDENCE: E8/g_car/anchor are overdetermined (>=3 structurally distinct derivations sharing only leaf inputs: v1/v15/v77+v92; v2/RR/reverse-glue), while the 5 pure-seed readouts (theta12/theta13/beta/Omega_b/lambda_C) are single-witness (multiplicity 1) -- correlated, NOT independent confirmations. [E] CORRELATION HONESTY: the 9 phi0-sharing scorecard observables must be scored JOINTLY (v100 fixes phi0), never as p^9. [E] NEG/POWER: alpha^-1's '137' is foreign to the anchor family (prime; no e_k/p_n/product) = an INDEPENDENT witness (F_U1 cubic, v3); foreign integers stay un-generated. Python-only (anti-numerology bookkeeping)."),
    ("v306_seed_crossval", "SEED.CROSSVAL.01: leave-one-out cross-validation of the shared seed phi0 -- turns the 'many observables, one seed' liability into a falsifiable out-of-sample test. [N] back-solving phi0 independently from each of the 5 seed-grammar observables (sin^2 theta12, sin^2 theta13, beta, Omega_b, lambda_C; repo-documented NuFIT 6.0 / ACT DR6 / Planck / PDG centrals) and taking the error-weighted mean reproduces the AXIOM seed phi0=1/(6pi)+48 c3^4=0.0531720 to 0.04% -- one real seed, not a per-observable fit. [N] the precise subset {lambda_C, Omega_b} clusters within 1.5% relative spread. [N] LEAVE-ONE-OUT: every held-out observable is predicted within 3 sigma out of sample; the most-tensioned hold-out is sin^2 theta13 (~2 sigma, the honest pressure point, cf. v62). [N] NEG/POWER: shuffling which datum feeds which inversion explodes the cross-validation chi^2 from 4.5 to ~1e5 (>100x). Python-only (out-of-sample statistic)."),
    ("v307_data_watchdog", "DATA.WATCHDOG.01: the operational DECISION pipeline over the frozen registry (v84) -- the machine-checked experimental-ledger / kill-test board. [N] reads predictions_frozen.json and classifies all 20 entries (16 predictions + 2 assigned textures + 2 conditional bands) PASS/WATCH/TENSION/KILL by live n_sigma vs the repo-documented current bests (CODATA 2022, NuFIT 6.0, ACT DR6, Planck 2018, PDG 2024, BK18); ratio observables judged against the conservative v18/v100 scheme window. [N] THEORY ALIVE: no decidable prediction in KILL (|n_sigma|<3). [N] POWER + PRESSURE POINT: the watch items are alpha^-1 (1.9 sigma), s23 (1.8 sigma), delta_CKM (1.0 sigma) and the most-tensioned CORE prediction sin^2 theta13 (2.0 sigma) -- the honest current pressure point (v62) the external analysis under-weighted. [N] JUNO #1 KILL TEST: the prediction-of-record sin^2 theta12=0.306747 is currently compatible (0.02 sigma). [N] FRONTS: r in [0.0033,0.0048] below BK18 0.036 and the kill 0.01 (allowed); w=-1 flagged WATCHDOG (DESI dynamical-DE = the most dangerous negative front). Python-only (decision harness)."),
    ("v308_seam_equiv_chain", "SEAM.EQUIV.CHAIN.01: TOE attack point 1 -- the SEAM.EQUIV.01 keystone as a machine-checked composition certificate. Assembles the v297 literature stack into ONE well-typed logical chain gap>0 -> invertible/SRE (Kitaev) -> holomorphic c=8 (Mueger/KLM) -> (E8)_1 (Conway-Sloane), out(i)=in(i+1). [E] arithmetic discriminators exact: |det Cartan(E8)|=1 (one anyon/primary/invertible/holomorphic) vs |det Cartan(D8=SO(16))|=4 (the same-c rival, NON-holomorphic); carrier |det D5|*|det A3|=4*4=16 => tower 16->4->1; c=g_car+N_fam=8. [E] the input gap is the derived recovery gap 6 ln(3/2)>0 with v76 margin >0. [O] the only undischarged premise is the cited OS step (OS-reconstructed bulk gap = transfer gap). An assembly/reduction certificate (like v261/v297), a Lean target, NOT a closure. Python-only (sympy)."),
    ("v309_modular_bedrock", "QGEO.MODHAM.01: TOE attack point 2 -- the bedrock omega o rho = omega via an EXPLICIT modular Hamiltonian, non-circular. [E] non-circular upstream: marks=2 chi=4 (Gauss-Bonnet, v216), clock z->iz order 4 from cross-ratio 2 (v214/v267), so mu4 is DERIVED not assumed; rho^4=I. [E] for the thermal quasi-free covariance C=1/(1+e^{H1}) the modular Hamiltonian K=log((1-C)/C) recovered from C round-trips to the seam operator H1. [E] rho C rho^dag=C AND [rho,K]=0 <=> omega o rho = omega (mu4 curvature couples only modes n-n' in 4Z, i^{n-n'}=1). [E] NEG: a Z2 (period-2) curvature breaks the invariance. [O] residual: the raw RP-collar C is intrinsically this clock-invariant state (Bisognano-Wichmann). NOT a closure of QGEO.SYM.01. Python-only (numpy)."),
    ("v310_carrier_sm_anomaly", "CAR.SM.ANOM.01: TOE attack point 3 -- the carrier half-spinor IS one anomaly-free SM generation with the SM RG (closes the spectrum+anomaly+beta sub-question exactly). [E] 16=Lambda^even(C^5)=1+10+5; SU(5)<SO(10): 10+5bar+1 = one generation (Q,u^c,d^c,L,e^c,nu^c), 16 Weyl states. [E] ANOMALY-FREE: sum Y=0, sum Y^3=0, [SU2]^2U1=0, [SU3]^2U1=0 (exact Fraction arithmetic). [E] one-loop RG from the carrier content (3 gen + Higgs): (b1,b2,b3)=(41/10,-19/6,-7), b1 numerator 41 = the EM-budget integer, b3=-(11-2 n_f/3) with n_f=2 N_fam. [E] NEG: dropping nu^c leaves an incomplete (15!=16) multiplet; a 4th family shifts b1 off 41/10. [C/O] the full Epstein-Glaser interacting S-matrix + Yukawa sector stay open. Python-only (exact Fraction)."),
    ("v311_gap_decoupled_measure", "QGAMB.CLUSTER.01: TOE attack point 4 -- the physical QG measure as a gap-decoupled, exponentially-clustering object (the honest statement in place of an over-claimed 4D measure). [E] the transfer spectrum {1,(2/3)^6,(1/3)^6} gives geometric clustering of the connected correlator at rate (2/3)^6, correlation length xi=1/Delta=1/(6 ln(3/2)). [E] finite susceptibility sum (2/3)^{6n}=1/(1-(2/3)^6)=729/665<inf => a well-defined admissible-sector thermodynamic limit. [E] gap-decoupling (v76): Delta-31/(4pi^2)~1.648>0, the gap survives metric dressing so the physical sector is decoupled from the un-built ambient. [E] NEG: an ungapped transfer (2nd eig->1) sends xi,chi->inf (no clustering). [C] spectral-action dictionary a2=EH, a4=R^2/72 (v36) + KMS beta=1 (v259). [O] the FULL ambient measure QG.AMB.01 is not built (gap-decoupled, inert). Python-only (numpy)."),
    ("v312_hypergraph_substrate", "HYP.INJECT.01: TOE attack point 5 -- the hypergraph substrate sharpened to exactly what a rewrite MUST inject. [E] the affine-E8 Kac marks (1,2,3,4,5,6,4,2,3) are the Perron eigenvector (A.marks=2 marks, top eigenvalue 2) -- the Coxeter skeleton is graph-spectral (v298/v299). [E] the subleading eigenvalue is exactly 2cos(pi/5)=golden ratio phi (the icosahedral (2,3,5)/5-fold signature; spectrum {+-2,+-phi,+-1,+-1/phi,0}). [E] HONEST NEGATIVE: the recovery rate (2/3)^6 is NOT any eigenvalue of A (the lazy-update rate (phi+2)/4=0.9045 != 2/3) -- the family-recovery dynamics is carried by the cusp weights, not the adjacency. [E] HONEST NEGATIVE: phi0=1/(6pi)+48c3^4 is analytic, not a rational edge fraction. [O] CONCLUSION: a full-structure rewrite must inject the cusp weight 2/3=|Z2|/N_fam (gap 6 ln(3/2)) AND the analytic seed phi0; the open question is now precisely delimited. Python-only (numpy)."),
    ("v313_golden_atoms_spectral", "GOLD.ATOMS.01: the golden ratio is the g_car=5 signature -- the (2,3,5) atoms ARE the affine-E8 network spectral angles (a v312 follow-up made exact). [E] EXACT: the affine-E8 charpoly factors x(x^2-4)(x^2-1)(x^2-x-1)(x^2+x-1); the golden minimal polynomial x^2-x-1 divides it, so phi=2cos(pi/5)=(1+sqrt5)/2 is an EXACT eigenvalue. [E] ATOMS = SPECTRAL ANGLES: the non-trivial eigenvalues are 2cos(pi/k) for k in {2,3,5}={|Z2|,N_fam,g_car}: 2cos(pi/2)=0, 2cos(pi/3)=1, 2cos(pi/5)=phi, 2cos(2pi/5)=1/phi -- the golden ratio is SPECIFICALLY the g_car=5 (5-fold) signature. [E] NEW WITNESS: g_car=5 also appears as the 5-fold spectral angle pi/5, structurally distinct from Pascal/RR/reverse-glue (raises the v305 multiplicity). [E] ICOSAHEDRAL SELECTION: 1/|Z2|+1/N_fam+1/g_car=31/30>1 (spherical => finite 2I => E8), numerator 31=2^g_car-1=248/8=1+h(E8) (the v63/v76 margin numerator), denominator 30=h(E8); HONEST anti-numerology (v305): one anchor-derived quantity, a unification not new evidence. [E] HONEST NULL: phi is NOT a TFPT readout (structural, not phenomenological). [C] DIRECTION: phi is the E8-quasicrystal (Elser-Sloane cut-and-project) ratio -> a candidate aperiodic substrate for v312. Python-only (sympy)."),
    ("v314_rate_translation", "RATE.TRANSLATE.01: do the discrete-kernel and dynamic rates translate? An exact number-field split (v312/v313 follow-up). [E] FIELD SPLIT: the affine-E8 adjacency spectrum is the rational part {0,+-1,+-2} in Q plus the golden part {+-phi,+-1/phi} in Q(sqrt5) (min poly x^2-x-1, disc 5); the dynamic transfer spectrum {1,(2/3)^6,(1/3)^6} is ENTIRELY rational. [E] TRANSLATION (the (2,3)-fold/family sector): the rational discrete angles 2cos(pi/2)=0 (|Z2|) and 2cos(pi/3)=1 (N_fam) are the SAME atoms that build the recovery rate (2/3)^6=(|Z2|/N_fam)^(2 N_fam) in Q -- same field, same atoms, so the family rates DO translate. [E] NO-TRANSLATION (the 5-fold/carrier sector): phi in Q(sqrt5)\\Q has no rational dynamic image (2/3 is neither an adjacency nor a lazy-update eigenvalue; heat-kernel t=Delta/(2-phi)~6.37 not clean) -- the carrier 5-fold is STATIC-only. [E] SHARED CLOCK: 30=h(E8)=g_car*(2 N_fam)=5*6; golden in the order-5 factor, recovery exponent 6=2 N_fam=30/g_car in the order-6=2*3 factor. [E] QUASICRYSTAL: E8=H4+phi H4 (240=2*120), the phi cut-and-project carries the 5-fold carrier but the cusp weights {0,1/3,2/3} are rational (3-fold), a separate datum (the substrate carries the carrier, not the family dynamics). [C]/[O] a static<->dynamic translation functor exists ONLY on the rational (2,3) sector; the bridge holding both is the order-30 Coxeter element. Python-only (sympy)."),
    ("v315_coxeter_coupling", "COX.COUPLE.01: couple or factorize? The order-30 Coxeter sectors couple as a cyclotomic field (the v314 follow-up). [E] GROUP FACTORIZES: gcd(5,6)=1 => Z/30 = Z/5 x Z/6 (CRT, direct product), order-5 subgroup <c^6>, order-6 <c^5> -- group-level decoupled (consistent with the v314 field obstruction). [E] EXPONENTS FACTOR: the E8 exponents = totatives(30) split as totatives(5)x totatives(6), phi(30)=phi(5)phi(6)=4*2=8=rank E8; (m mod5, m mod6) a bijection onto {1,2,3,4}x{1,5}. [E] FIELD COUPLES: [Q(zeta30):Q]=phi(30)=8=rank E8; Q(zeta30) is the COMPOSITUM of the carrier Q(zeta5) (contains sqrt5) and the family Q(zeta6)=Q(zeta3) (contains zeta3). [E] GALOIS = mu4 x Z2: (Z/30)^x=(Z/5)^x x (Z/3)^x=Z/4 x Z/2 (order 8, max element order 4, NOT cyclic Z/8); mu4=(Z/5)^x is the CARRIER Galois, Z2=(Z/3)^x the FAMILY Galois -- the seam clock mu4 IS the Galois group of the carrier's golden field (refines v223). [E] CARRIER GENERATOR: sqrt5=phi+1/phi=2phi-1 (sum of the two golden network eigenvalues) = the quadratic Gauss sum zeta5-zeta5^2-zeta5^3+zeta5^4 in Q(zeta5), g^2=5. [C] VERDICT: 30=5*6 does NOT dynamically entangle the sectors -- it couples them as the cyclotomic compositum Q(zeta30), Galois mu4 x Z2, degree rank E8; the bridge is GALOIS, not a dynamical map. Python-only (sympy)."),
    ("v316_galois_readout", "GALOIS.READOUT.01: does the Galois mu4 x Z2 (v315) organize the physical readouts? Yes -- the CP phases (the v315 follow-up to phenomenology). [E] FAMILY FACTOR: the hexagonal CP unit rho=zeta_6=zeta_30^5 is the order-6=2 N_fam factor c^5 of v315 (5=30/6); the carrier is zeta_5=zeta_30^6 (order 5=g_car, c^6) -- the CP phase lives in the FAMILY factor, not the carrier. [C] CP PHASES (inherits v231/v233): delta_CKM,lead=pi/3=arg(zeta_6), delta_PMNS=4pi/3=arg(zeta_6^4) (power 4=|mu4|). [E] SHEET FLIP: zeta_6^4=-zeta_6 (rho^3=-1), delta_PMNS=delta_CKM+pi (|Z2| sheet); mu6=mu3 x mu2 (family x sheet), zeta_6=-zeta_3^2. [E] GALOIS Z2 = CP CONJUGATION: Gal(Q(zeta_6)/Q)=(Z/6)^x={1,5}=Z2, sigma: zeta_6->zeta_6^5=conj(zeta_6) (delta->-delta) -- the FAMILY Galois factor of mu4 x Z2 IS the physical CP-conjugation symmetry. [E] CARRIER STATIC: zeta_5=zeta_30^6 (golden sqrt5) carries no phase -- mu4 organizes the lattice/spectrum. [E] HONEST SEPARATION: the magnitudes (sin^2 theta12=1/3-phi0/2, phi0=1/(6pi)+48c3^4, transcendental) are NOT cyclotomic -- Galois organizes PHASES, the magnitudes are the analytic seed. [C] VERDICT: the Galois coupling reaches phenomenology through the FAMILY factor (CP phases); the carrier factor is static; the magnitudes are the seed (v314 field split). Python-only (sympy)."),
    ("v317_galois_family", "GALOIS.FAMILY.01: are the 3 generations a mu3/Galois orbit? Yes (mu3), refined 1+2 by Galois (the v316 follow-up to the generation structure). [E] GENERATIONS = CUBE ROOTS: the 3 cusp weights {0,1/3,2/3} (Spec(Q+)=3a+1={1,2,3}=A3 exponents) map under w->e^{2pi i w} to the 3rd roots of unity {1,zeta_3,zeta_3^2}. [E] mu3 ORBIT (transitive): the cyclic family symmetry w->w+1/3 mod 1 permutes them cyclically -- ONE transitive Z/3=mu3 orbit (the family IS the cube-root orbit). [E] RECOVERY: transfer eigenvalues (1-w)^6={1,(2/3)^6,(1/3)^6} attach to the weights, the attractor (eigenvalue 1, the stationary law, v56) at w=0. [E] GALOIS 1+2: Gal(Q(zeta3)/Q)=Z2, sigma: zeta_3->zeta_3^2 acts by w->2w mod 1, FIXING w=0 (rational) and SWAPPING w=1/3<->2/3 -- Galois orbit = 1 (fixed) + 2 (pair), NOT transitive. [E] FIXED = ATTRACTOR: the Galois-fixed w=0 is the eigenvalue-1 attractor (the law); the Galois pair w=1/3,2/3 is the decaying hierarchy (2/3)^6,(1/3)^6. [E] SAME Z2 as CP conjugation (v316): sigma: zeta_3->zeta_3^2=conj(zeta_3). [E] COUNTS: N_fam=3=|mu3|=#weights=|Spec(Q+)|. [C] VERDICT: the family STRUCTURE is arithmetic (mu3 orbit, Galois-refined 1+2, the fixed one the attractor); the mass MAGNITUDES stay the analytic seed (not derived). Python-only (sympy)."),
    ("v319_translation_clock", "TRANSLATE.CLOCK.01: the discrete<->dynamic translation IS a clock -- the order-30 Coxeter element with two coprime hands 5 x 6, read law-inclusive (0..5) or live-only (1..5). A synthesis of the v313-v318 arc + v124/v55 answering 'is the static<->dynamic bridge a clock running 0,1,2,3,4,5 or 1,2,3,4,5?'. [E] THE TRANSLATION IS A CLOCK: the only object holding both the static carrier (Q(sqrt5)) and the dynamic family (rational) data is the order-30 Coxeter element (v314); 30=h(E8)=g_car*(2 N_fam)=5*6, gcd(5,6)=1 => Z/30=Z/5 x Z/6 (two coprime hands, v315). [E] DYNAMIC HAND RUNS 0..5: the dynamic factor is Z/6=2 N_fam (ticks {0,...,5}); the recovery exponent is EXACTLY 6=|Z/6|=2 N_fam, rate (2/3)^6=(|Z2|/N_fam)^(2 N_fam); order-6 generator c^5 (zeta_6=zeta_30^5, v316). [E] POSITION 0=THE CONSERVED LAW, 1..=THE LIVE PHASES: the resummed clock rate(n)=-p2 ln(1-n/N_fam) (v124) has rate(0)=0 (the attractor/law, eigenvalue 1, v56) and live modes rate(1)=6 ln(3/2); the E8 live phases (totatives of 30) start at 1, the 0 phase is not a totative -- so '0,1,2,3,4,5' is law-inclusive, '1,2,3,4,5' live-only. [E] STATIC HAND RUNS 1..5: Z/5=g_car (ticks {1,...,5}), golden Q(sqrt5) (phi=2cos(pi/5)), field-obstructed (no rational dynamic image, v314) -- static-only; zeta_5=zeta_30^6 carries no phase. [E] ONE FULL TURN=30: lcm(5,6)=30=h(E8); rank E8=8=phi(30)=#live phases pairing into |mu4|=4 planes (v55). [C] VERDICT: the bridge IS the order-30 clock = (static 5-ring) x (dynamic 6-ring), '0 vs 1' = law-inclusive vs live-only; arithmetic [E], the 'it is one clock' reading [C]. Python-only (sympy)."),
    ("v318_arithmetic_capstone", "ARITH.CAPSTONE.01: the capstone -- the SM structural sector is Q(zeta30) + Galois mu4 x Z2, and the complete input is {a, pi, v_geo} (synthesis of the v313-v317 arc). [E] ARITHMETIC SKELETON: the structural sector (3 generations, 2 CP phases, the orbit/hierarchy) lives in Q(zeta30); [Q(zeta30):Q]=phi(30)=8=rank E8, 30=|Z2|*N_fam*g_car=h(E8); Galois (Z/30)^x=mu4 x Z2 (order 8) -- carrier mu4=(Z/5)^x golden, family/sheet Z2=(Z/3)^x=CP conjugation; generations=mu3 orbit (v317), CP phases=zeta6 data (v316). [E] RIGIDITY: forced by the anchor atoms {|Z2|,N_fam,g_car}={2,3,5}=e(a); 30=2*3*5. [E] MAGNITUDE REDUCTION: phi0=(|mu4|/N_fam)c3+Omega_adm c3^4=(4/3)c3+48 c3^4 (c3=1/(8pi)) is a PURE function of pi (no free parameters), coefficients anchor-derived -- so the magnitudes (sin^2 theta12=1/3-phi0/2) are {a,pi}-determined, transcendental, NOT free. [E] FREE INVENTORY: dimensionless free parameters = 0 (everything {a,pi}); pi the unique transcendental primitive (ARCH.CORE.01); v_geo the unique dimensionful input (No-Unit Theorem) -- complete input {a,pi,v_geo}. [O] HONEST RESIDUAL: holds GIVEN the axioms; does NOT prove the raw seam REALIZES the structure (the open bedrock QGEO.SYM.01/SEAM.EQUIV.01 stays [O]). A synthesis/inventory module. Python-only (sympy)."),
    ("v320_galois_cp_relation", "GALOIS.CP.PREDICT.01: a NEW falsifiable prediction from the Galois structure -- the two CP phases are locked, delta_PMNS = delta_CKM,lead + pi (the v316 follow-up turned testable). [E] ONE UNIT TWO POWERS: delta_CKM,lead=arg(rho)=pi/3 (60 deg), delta_PMNS=arg(rho^4)=4pi/3 (240 deg), rho=zeta_6 (v316); rho^4=-rho. [E] FORCED RELATION: delta_PMNS-delta_CKM,lead=pi exactly (the Z2 sheet flip rho^3=-1), equivalently delta_PMNS=4*delta_CKM,lead -- the quark and lepton leading CP phases are NOT independent. [C] PREDICTION OF RECORD: delta_PMNS,lead=240 deg, forced from delta_CKM,lead=60 deg + the sheet flip -- upgrades the assigned texture to a Galois-forced relation to the measured quark phase. [N] currently compatible (240 deg within the broad NuFIT 6.0 NO range); decisive test = DUNE/Hyper-K/JUNO. [X] KILL TEST: a measured delta_PMNS robustly incompatible with delta_CKM,lead+pi=240 deg (>3 sigma) falsifies the Galois-CP organization. [E] NON-TRIVIALITY: a free angle would satisfy the relation only by coincidence. A genuine NEW falsifiable cross-prediction from the v313-v319 arc; does NOT derive magnitudes. Python-only (sympy)."),
    ("v321_killtest_board", "KILL.BOARD.01: the forward kill-test board -- the decisive upcoming measurements, ranked (the forward companion to v307's current-data board). [N] assembles the decisive NEXT measurements, each locked to a freeze_file.csv kill row: #1 JUNO sin^2 theta12=0.306747 (fastest, sub-percent), #2 CMB-S4/LiteBIRD r in [0.0033,0.0048] (kill r>0.01), #3 DESI/Euclid w=-1 (kill robust w!=-1), #4 DUNE/Hyper-K delta_PMNS=240 deg=delta_CKM,lead+pi (the NEW v320 Galois-CP relation; kill if away from 240 deg), #5 DUNE/LEGEND/nEXO ordering+m_betabeta, #6 PSI n2EDM theta_eff=0, #7 JUNO sin^2 theta13 (now ~2 sigma), #8 LiteBIRD beta=0.2424 deg. [N] COVERAGE: every entry backed by a freeze_file kill row (no drift); the v320 CP relation is on the board; JUNO theta12 is rank 1; >=7 decisive tests each with a concrete kill threshold. A forward decision ledger (publicly-stated experimental reach, not TFPT outputs); complements v307; no new physics. Python-only."),
    ("v322_cp_lock_sharpened", "GALOIS.CP.SHARPEN.01: the v320 CP-lock prediction sharpened into a quantitative pre-registered kill test. [E] DISCRETE LADDER: the leading CP phase sits on the six hexagonal nodes arg(rho^k)=k*60 deg; delta_CKM,lead=60 (node 1), delta_PMNS,lead=240 (node 4). [E] MULTIPLIER = DECK ORDER: delta_PMNS,lead=|mu4|*delta_CKM,lead=4*(pi/3)=4pi/3=delta_CKM,lead+pi (rho^4=-rho) -- the node selector IS the seam clock order |mu4|=4. [C] SUB-LEADING BUDGET: delta_CKM,full=pi/3+3 lambda^2 (~68.7 deg); the lepton sub-leading is a SEPARATE open holonomy term bounded by ~3 lambda^2~8.7 deg => band 240 +- ~9 deg. [N] CURRENT TENSION: vs NuFIT 6.0 NO (delta_CP=212 +26/-41 deg) the leading 240 deg sits at +1.08 sigma, band lower edge ~231 deg at +0.74 sigma -- compatible today. [X] SHARPENED KILL: the nearest wrong node (180/300) is 60 deg away, far beyond the budget; DUNE/Hyper-K at ~5-15 deg discriminate the node, >3 sigma outside kills the lock. [E] DISCRIMINATION POWER: an anarchic delta_CP hits the band with p~5% and node 4 (not 1/3/5) 1-in-6 -- a low-prior pre-registered prediction. No magnitudes derived. Python-only (sympy)."),
    ("v323_bw_geometric_modular", "QGEO.BW.01: the keystone pushed one step -- Bisognano-Wichmann makes the seam modular flow GEOMETRIC, so the mu4 deck invariance is NOT an independent axiom. [E] CLOCK = GEOMETRIC ROTATION: rho=diag(i^n)=exp(i(pi/2)L), L=diag(n) the rotation generator; rho^4=exp(i2pi L)=I -- mu4 ⊂ U(1)_rot (quarter turns). [E] BW: a rotation-covariant C=f(L) gives K=log((1-C)/C)=g(L), so [K,L]=0 (the modular flow commutes with all rotations) AND [rho,K]=[rho,C]=0 -- the mu4 clock is a modular symmetry FOR FREE. [E] DISCRIMINATOR vs v309: a period-4 curvature preserves the clock ([rho,K]=0) but its modular flow is NOT geometric ([K,L]!=0) -- BW is strictly stronger (pins the whole rotation group). [E] NEG: a non-rotation-covariant C breaks [rho,K]!=0. [C] LINKED BEDROCK: GIVEN the seam is the (E8)_1 chiral net (v308/SEAM.EQUIV.01), BW/Hislop-Longo make the vacuum modular flow geometric => QGEO.SYM.01 (omega o rho=omega) is DOWNSTREAM of SEAM.EQUIV.01 + a rotation-invariant vacuum, NOT an independent axiom (two open items collapse toward one). [O] residual: the raw collar vacuum is rotation-invariant (cleaner than v309's thermal state, shared with v308). NOT a closure. Python-only (numpy)."),
    ("v324_hypergraph_fiber", "HYP.FIBER.01: the minimal hypergraph substrate that works -- a (2,3,5)-network FIBERED by a 3-fold cusp channel reproduces BOTH the E8 skeleton AND the recovery gap (the constructive v312 follow-up). [E] NETWORK FACTOR (carrier/5-fold): T_net=(A+2I)/4 fixes the Kac marks (eigenvalue 1 = E8 skeleton), subleading (phi+2)/4 (golden); (2/3)^6 NOT in its spectrum (v312 negative). [E] CUSP FIBER (family/3-fold): T_cusp=diag((1-w)^{2N_fam}), w in {0,1/3,2/3} (N_fam=3, v317), spectrum {1,(2/3)^6,(1/3)^6}, recovery gap at w=1/3 (v76/v221). [E] FIBERED SUBSTRATE CARRIES BOTH: T=T_net (x) T_cusp has top eigenvalue 1, eigenvector marks (x) (w=0) (skeleton x democratic cusp), AND (2/3)^6 as a genuine eigenvalue marks (x) (w=1/3) (network attractor x cusp subleading). [E] HONEST INJECTION (v312): without the fiber (T_net (x) I_3) there is NO (2/3)^6 -- the cusp datum is injected, not graph-spectral; substrate = network x cusp = the v315 split 30=g_car*(2 N_fam)=5*6, gap in the family factor. [E] MINIMALITY: the smallest fiber is the 3-node cusp (=N_fam); a 2-node fiber can't hold 3 weights -> minimal substrate = (2,3,5)-net x 3-cusp = order-30 (v319 clock). [C] VERDICT: a CONSISTENT fibered realization (carrier x family), matching the arithmetic 5x6 split, but the cusp weight stays injected (v312) -- not a derivation of 2/3 from a pure rewrite. Python-only (numpy)."),
    ("v325_pillowcase_keystone", "QGEO.KEYSTONE.01: the seam keystone as ONE citable theorem -- the raw seam state is the flat tau=i pillowcase state, with EXACTLY ONE open lemma. Assembles the keystone pieces into one statement: IF (raw RP-collar seam state = flat tau=i pillowcase / rotation-invariant state) THEN 4 square marks + mu4 deck + omega o rho=omega + holomorphic c=8 => (E8)_1, with the carrier recovery gap as input. [E] FOUR SQUARE MARKS: n=2chi(S^2)=4 (Gauss-Bonnet v216); cross-ratio 2 => j=1728 (order-4 CM, v214/v267). [E] FLAT PILLOWCASE: S^2(2,2,2,2), chi_orb=2-4(1-1/2)=0 => flat tau=i (Troyanov). [E] MU4 FINGERPRINT: DtN sub-principal at m=0 mod 4 (v201/v280). [E] HOLOMORPHY SELECTOR: det Cartan(E8)=1 vs D8=4 (v83/v143/v308). [E] INPUT GAP: Delta=6 ln(3/2)>0 (v76/v302). [O] ONE OPEN LEMMA: the raw collar state IS the flat tau=i pillowcase / rotation-invariant state, SHARED by both bedrock IDs (QGEO.SYM.01, SEAM.EQUIV.01; v323) and machine-pinned in Lean (FORM.SEAMEQUIV.01 + FORM.QGEO.BW.01). An assembly/reduction certificate (like v176/v261), NOT a closure. Python-only (sympy)."),
    ("v326_ftransfer_suite", "FR.SUITE.01: the F_transfer solver suite -- the four transfer readouts as ONE runnable harness, each a gapped relaxation to a unique attractor, with values + uncertainties + honest typing (productises v303). [E] F_pole (Koide): Moebius contraction to Q*=2/3 with multiplier (2/3)^6 = the seam-clock subleading eigenvalue; |mult|<1, unique attractor at the SEAM rate. [C] F_Boltzmann (eta_B): washout contraction Y*=S/kappa=6.1e-11, monotone (H-theorem), external thermal rate. [C] F_relic (axion): the comoving number N=E/omega is the adiabatic invariant -- conserved under slow H, the relic freezes; seed theta_i=3pi/5, cosmological rate. [I] F_QCD (m_p/m_e): 1-loop RG with carrier b0=7 flows to the Gaussian UV fixed point, Lambda_QCD dynamically generated; standard RG. [N] F_RareKaon (bridge): BR(K+)=9.45e-11 on NA62 2016-2024 (v202), external SD. [O] SHARED SHAPE: all 5 are gapped relaxations to a unique attractor; only F_pole has the seam rate (2/3)^6, the other 4 share the SHAPE with external rates honestly fenced (v187/v303) -- the suite makes the frontier measurable without claiming the external rates. Python-only (numpy)."),
    ("v327_hypergraph_rewrite", "HYP.REWRITE.01: deriving the cusp weight 2/3 from a minimal rewrite (sharpening v324/v312). A minimal local rule -- a family channel with N_fam=3 slots, one absorbing attractor (w=0) and |Z2|=2 surviving (the Z2 pair) -- supplies the cusp fiber. [E] MINIMAL REWRITE: M=[[1,0,0],[0,1/3,1/3],[0,1/3,1/3]] has spectrum {1,2/3,0}; the recovery survival 2/3=(N_fam-1)/N_fam=|Z2|/N_fam EMERGES from the rule arity, not injected. [E] RECOVERY RATE DERIVED: over the order-6=2 N_fam dynamic hand the rate is (2/3)^6=64/729 = the recovery gap (v76/v324), derived not put in. [E] NON-GRAPH-SPECTRAL (proof, sharpening v312): 2/3 is NOT a root of the affine-E8 charpoly x(x^2-4)(x^2-1)(x^2-x-1)(x^2+x-1) (p(2/3)=-3520/19683 != 0), so the recovery rate cannot be an adjacency eigenvalue -- necessarily the branching channel. [E] ATTRACTOR: the absorbing state (eigenvalue 1) is the democratic w=0 law (v317). [O] HONEST RESIDUAL: the rewrite DERIVES 2/3 from the arity {|Z2|,N_fam}={2,3} (the anchor atoms, still the input P2) -- v324's injected datum reduced to the anchor arity. [C] VERDICT: substrate = (2,3,5)-adjacency (carrier) x this minimal branching rule (family), both from the atoms. Python-only (sympy)."),
    ("v329_os_gap_reduction", "QGEO.OSGAP.01: closing the OS step -- the bulk gap IS the transfer gap (second quantization), and assembling the single sufficient premise of the whole bedrock. [E] OS GAP = TRANSFER GAP: the OS/Euclidean many-body Hamiltonian is dGamma(-log T) (T the v221/v302 recovery transfer); its spectrum is sums of single-mode energies, so the many-body (bulk) gap = the smallest positive single-mode energy = 6 ln(3/2), INDEPENDENT of system size -- exactly 'OS bulk gap = transfer gap' (the v308 open input), discharged at the many-body level. [E] H => omega o rho = omega: under the premise H the covariance is rotation-covariant C=f(L), so K=log((1-C)/C)=g(L) commutes with rho=exp(i(pi/2)L) ([rho,K]=0, QGEO.SYM.01, geometric flow, v201/v309/v323). [E] H => SRE => (E8)_1: |det Cartan(E8)|=1 vs D8=4 (v237/v308). [E] SINGLE SUFFICIENT PREMISE: both bedrock IDs follow from the ONE premise H = 'raw collar = rotation-invariant flat tau=i pillowcase state', Lean-pinned (FORM.SEAMEQUIV.01 + FORM.QGEO.BW.01). [O] RESIDUAL: the NECESSITY of H on the raw (continuum) collar (NEG: a non-rotation-invariant collar breaks mark-locality). Sharpens v240/v308/v323/v325; does NOT close the bedrock. Python-only (numpy+sympy)."),
    ("v330_qgamb_admissible_measure", "QGAMB.MEASURE.01: constructing the ambient measure on the gap-decoupled admissible sector as a bona fide Osterwalder-Schrader object (with the honest fence). [E] REFLECTION POSITIVITY: the seam transfer T (v221/v311; spectrum {1,(2/3)^6,(1/3)^6}) is symmetric PSD, so the finite-volume measures are RP. [E] EXPONENTIAL CLUSTERING: the connected 2-pt C(n)/C(n-1) -> lambda_2=(2/3)^6 (xi=1/Delta, Delta=6 ln(3/2)). [E] TIGHTNESS => PROJECTIVE LIMIT: chi=sum_n C(n)=729/665 finite, so Var(S_L)/L -> chi converges => uniform tightness (Prokhorov) => the projective limit mu=lim mu_Lambda EXISTS on the admissible sector. [E] OS RECONSTRUCTION: H_OS=-log T>=0 with unique vacuum and gap 6 ln(3/2) (v240) -- mu is a genuine OS measure on the admissible sector. [E] NEG: an ungapped transfer (lambda_2->1) sends chi->inf and tightness FAILS -- the construction IS the gap. [O] THE FULL AMBIENT MEASURE: the non-admissible (metric) sector is NOT built; by the gap-decoupling margin Delta-31/(4pi^2)~1.648>0 (v76/v275) the physical readouts do not need it, but QG.AMB.01 stays open. A genuine PARTIAL construction, NOT a closure. Python-only (numpy)."),
    ("v328_theta13_pressure", "FLAV.TH13.PRESSURE.01: the theta13 pressure point -- the honest weak spot, quantified and pre-registered. [N] TENSION: sin^2 theta13 = phi0 e^{-5/6} = 0.023108 vs NuFIT 6.0 NO (0.02195 +- 0.00058) is +2.0 sigma -- the most-tensioned CORE prediction (v62/v307). [E] SEPARATE CHANNEL: theta13 is the carrier hypercharge trace (exponent gamma=tr_E Y^2=5/6 EXACT, v268), NOT the seesaw mu-tau breaking that sets theta12 (eps=3 phi0/4 induces only ~1.6e-3) -- not to be conflated. [N] NO CHEAP RELIEF: phi0(theta13)=e^{5/6} sin^2 theta13_exp=0.0505 is ~5% below the axiom; PMNS theta13 RG running is <1% (NO) so cannot close it, and the exponent 5/6 is exact -- no freeze-respecting correction relieves it; prediction stays frozen (REG.FREEZE.01). [X] PRE-REGISTERED KILL: a stable sin^2 theta13 away from 0.023108 at >3 sigma (JUNO/global) flags the carrier-trace/seed-grammar reading. [E] SEED-HYPERPLANE CONSISTENCY: exactly the v306 leave-one-out outlier (theta13 the single ~2 sigma channel, others ~1 sigma) -- one honest pressure point, not a pattern. Python-only."),
    ("v331_necessity_of_H", "QGEO.NECESS.01: the NECESSITY of H reduced -- rotation-invariance of the seam DtN is EQUIVALENT to the four marks sitting at the square (tau=i), so the one open lemma is exactly the order-4 CM selection (the necessity companion to v329's sufficiency). [E] SQUARE => [rho,Lambda]=0: with marks at {0,pi/2,pi,3pi/2} the curvature is Z4-symmetric (Fourier support 0 mod 4), M_f couples only modes differing by 4Z, [rho,Lambda]=0 (the v201/v210 sufficiency, as a DtN |k|+M_f operator). [E] NECESSITY: moving a mark off the square breaks Z4 and gives [rho,Lambda]!=0 -- so rotation-invariance of the DtN is EQUIVALENT to the square, not merely implied. [E] ORDER-4 CM: the cross-ratio of the square points (1,i,-1,-i) is 2 => j=1728, the unique 4-config with an order-4 automorphism (v214/v267); H <=> square <=> order-4 CM <=> mu4. [E] NEG: a Z2 (period-2) mark set commutes with rho^2 but not rho. [O] SHARPENED RESIDUAL: 'necessity of H' is now exactly 'the raw dynamics places the four Gauss-Bonnet marks (v216) at the order-4 CM (square) point' -- the marks are forced to be 4, the square is the unique order-4 CM config, but the dynamical SELECTION of the square is the irreducible residual (not closed). Python-only (numpy)."),
    ("v332_qgamb_metric_sector", "QGAMB.METRIC.01: the metric sector of QG.AMB.01 characterized -- the obstruction is exactly the conformal-mode (Gibbons-Hawking-Perry) problem, the physical sector is gap-insulated, and the only route is the conditional IDG taming (makes v330's metric-sector fence precise). [E] CONFORMAL-MODE WRONG SIGN: c_conf(D)=-(D-1)(D-2)/4 is NEGATIVE for D>=3 (c_conf(4)=-3/2) while the TT coefficient is positive -- the conformal-factor problem. [E] MEASURE OBSTRUCTION: the kinetic form is indefinite (one negative eigenvalue), so exp(-S)~exp(+|c|phi^2) DIVERGES over the conformal mode; the bare metric-sector measure is not directly definable. [E] PHYSICAL SECTOR INSULATED: the obstruction is in the conformal/gauge direction, not the admissible sector (positive+gapped, v330), gap-decoupling margin Delta-31/(4pi^2)~1.648>0 (v76). [C] IDG CONDITIONAL ROUTE: the entire form factor e^{z/M^2} (v259/v304) dresses the conformal propagator with no extra pole -- conditional taming. [E] NEG: a polynomial (R+R^2) truncation crosses zero (the Stelle ghost, v304/v278). [O] METRIC SECTOR OPEN: the full QG.AMB.01 needs the conformal mode resolved nonperturbatively (GHP rotation / IDG), gap-decoupled but NOT constructed. A precise characterization, NOT a closure. Python-only (numpy)."),
    ("v333_cm_selection", "QGEO.CMSELECT.01: the CM-selection mechanism -- tau=i (the square) is the UNIQUE order-4 modulus and the attractor of mark-equilibration, so the last keystone residual is 'the deck acts geometrically', not 'why the square' (the v331 follow-up). [E] ORDER-4 MODULAR ELEMENT: S=[[0,-1],[1,0]] in SL(2,Z) has S^2=-I, S^4=I (order 4) and fixes tau=i (S.i=-1/i=i); i is the unique order-4 elliptic point of PSL(2,Z) (the other, rho, is order 3). [E] DECK ORDER -> CM POINT: order-4 deck -> cross-ratio 2 -> j=1728 -> tau=i (square); order-3 -> equianharmonic lambda -> j=0 -> tau=rho (hexagon); the carrier |mu4|=4 selects tau=i uniquely. [E] MARK-EQUILIBRATION ATTRACTOR: 4 points minimizing the log-energy (Fekete) converge to equal spacing (gaps pi/2 = the square) from random starts, and the square beats random perturbations -- the unique (mod rotation) attractor of symmetric mark-equilibration. [E] NEG: an order-3 (hexagonal) deck selects rho (j=0) not the square -- deck-order-specific. [O] SHARPENED RESIDUAL: given mu4, tau=i is FORCED (arithmetic) and is the attractor (dynamical); only 'the deck acts GEOMETRICALLY (conformal automorphism, = QGEO.SYM.01) vs an abstract Z4 on labels' stays open -- the residual sharpens from 'why the square' to 'the deck acts geometrically'. NOT a closure. Python-only (numpy+scipy)."),
    ("v334_conformal_resolution", "QGAMB.CONFORMAL.01: the conformal-mode resolution -- the Gibbons-Hawking-Perry contour rotation (IR sign) + the infinite-derivative (IDG) dressing (UV pole) give a CONDITIONALLY convergent metric-sector measure; the residual is the nonperturbative validity of the contour (the v332 follow-up). [E] THE OBSTRUCTION: c_conf(4)=-3/2<0, so the unrotated conformal Gaussian int(exp(+|c|phi^2)) DIVERGES. [E] GHP CONTOUR ROTATION: phi->i phi flips (i phi)^2=-phi^2, so +|c|phi^2 -> -|c|phi^2 and int(exp(-|c|phi^2))=sqrt(pi/|c|) is FINITE (the GHP 1978 prescription). [E] IDG UV DRESSING: the entire form factor a=exp(p^2/M^2)>0 (no ghost pole, v304), the dressed per-mode action is positive post-GHP and UV-suppressed. [E] NEG: a polynomial truncation a=1+p^2/M^2 crosses zero (the Stelle ghost, v304/v278). [C] CONDITIONAL CONSTRUCTION: GHP+IDG give a convergent metric-sector Gaussian mode-by-mode -- conditional on the contour AND entire analyticity. [O] RESIDUAL: whether the GHP-rotated IDG-dressed measure is the CORRECT nonperturbative QG.AMB measure (the contour's nonperturbative validity, Euclidean QG's standing issue); gap-decoupled (v76), blocks no test. NOT a closure. Python-only (numpy+scipy)."),
    ("v336_continuum_limit", "SEAM.EQUIV.CONTINUUM.01: the ONE open lemma of SEAM.EQUIV.01, stated precisely and mapped to the recent rigorous literature -- the continuum-limit and OS-reconstruction legs are now CITABLE, the genuinely-open residual narrows. [C] CONTINUUM LEG: Morinelli-Morsella-Stottmeister-Tanimoto (CFT from Lattice Fermions, doi:10.1007/s00220-022-04521-8; CMP 387 (2021) 299; PRL 127 (2021) 230601) give, by operator-algebraic (wavelet/Wilson-Kadanoff) renormalization, the chiral-CFT scaling limit of free lattice fermions (Koo-Saleur -> Virasoro, correct c); their WZW range is rank <= c <= D (D Majorana copies). (E8)_1: c=8, rank 8, D=16 Majoranas (SO(16)_1 -> (E8)_1) => 8<=8<=16 IN range; the collar is a gapped quasi-free (CAR) state, this class. [C] OS LEG: Adamo-Moriwaki-Tanimoto (arXiv:2407.18222, 2024) prove the conformal OS axioms (linear growth) for unitary VOAs incl. WZW/lattice VOAs, so Euclidean correlators reconstruct Wightman/AQFT data; (E8)_1 is the even self-dual rank-8 lattice VOA. [E] TARGET PINNED: c=g_car+N_fam=8, det Cartan E8=1, the D=16 Majorana SO(16)_1 IS the carrier-16 and the mu4 simple-current extension SO(16)_1 -> (E8)_1 IS the seam glue. [O] OPEN RESIDUAL: c=8 alone does NOT pin the net (SO(16)_1 also c=8, det Cartan D8=4, four primaries), so the one open lemma = 'the raw collar is a gapped quasi-free state whose massless scaling limit is the c=8 (E8)_1 net' = the holomorphy discriminator det K=1 (v277/v281/v335). A literature-mapping/reduction module; does NOT close SEAM.EQUIV.01. Python-only (sympy)."),
    ("v337_decoupling_theorem", "DECOUPLING.THEOREM.01: every TFPT dimensionless readout factors through the gapped admissible sector and is INDEPENDENT of the ambient QG measure -- the theorem that makes the QG.AMB.01 reclassification (v335) honest. [E] GAP MARGIN: Delta - 2*dim(E8)*c3^2 = 6 ln(3/2) - 496/(64 pi^2) = 6 ln(3/2) - 31/(4 pi^2) ~ 1.648 > 0 (the ambient back-reaction scale 2*248*c3^2 = 31/(4 pi^2) exactly). [E] FACTORIZATION: every readout (mass ratios, mixings, alpha^-1, R+R^2) is a function of the admissible (gapped) transfer spectrum {1,(2/3)^6,(1/3)^6} + the discrete kernel alone; the ambient couples only above the gap. [E] THE THEOREM: margin>0 => exponential clustering (lambda_2=(2/3)^6) with finite susceptibility chi=1/(1-(2/3)^6)=729/665, so the ambient contribution is gap-suppressed and the readout = its admissible-sector value -- no readout depends on the ambient measure => QG.AMB.01 decoupled. [E] NEG CONTROL: if the gap closed (lambda_2->1) chi diverges and decoupling fails -- non-vacuous. [E] COROLLARY: of the frozen kill tests, ZERO depend on the ambient measure. Consolidates v76/v311/v330/v332; does NOT construct the ambient measure (that is QG.AMB.01). Python-only (sympy)."),
    ("v338_theta13_budget", "THETA13.BUDGET.01: the theta13 sub-leading budget vs the current global fit -- the +2 sigma pressure point (v328) quantified against BOTH NuFIT 6.0 NO variants and JUNO; neither defuses nor excludes, fences correctly. [N] SK-DEPENDENT TENSION: sin^2 theta13 = phi0 e^{-5/6} = 0.023108 is +2.0 sigma vs the no-SK central (0.02195+-0.00058) and +1.7 sigma vs the with-SK NO best fit (0.02215+-0.00057) -- a ~0.3 sigma spread from one systematic, NOT a clean 2 sigma. [E] WITHIN 3 SIGMA: 0.023108 < the with-SK 3 sigma upper bound 0.02388, INSIDE the allowed region (not falsified). [N] SUB-LEADING BUDGET: moving to the central needs -4.1%; RG < 1% and the exponent 5/6 is exact, so ~3% would need a sub-leading channel larger than natural -- no freeze-respecting relief (v328). [X] JUNO DECIDES: sub-1% precision (sigma ~ 1.5e-4) turns 1.7-2.0 sigma into ~6 sigma either way -- near-term pre-registered kill/confirm. [E] one honest pressure point (v306/v328), correctly fenced. Python-only (mpmath)."),
    ("v351_continuum_realisation_sharpened", "SEAM.EQUIV.CONTINUUM.02: the continuum realisation sharpened -- the 'c=8 ambiguity' flagged open in v277/v344 (E8 vs SO(16) both have c=8) is RESOLVED, non-circularly, by the seam's ORDER-4 mu4 clock. [E] two c=8 lattices: E8 (det Cartan 1, holomorphic) and D8=SO(16) (det Cartan 4). [E] the order-4 clock resolves it: the seam clock is mu4 (order 4, forced by the four Gauss-Bonnet marks |mu4|=4=h(A3), v216); index-4 extension of D5(+)A3 = E8 (v154), index-2 = SO(16); so the order-4 clock selects E8 (full mu4 condensation 16->4->1, det 1) not SO(16) (partial Z2 16->4, det 4) -- the order (4 not 2) is the discriminator. [E] the bootstrap agrees: h(E8)=30 (max prime 5=g_car) vs h(D8)=14 (max prime 7); SO(16) fails the Coxeter-match. [E] so the which-net ambiguity is RESOLVED (c=8 + the order-4 clock pin E8; det K=1 is then a consequence). [O] the residual of SEAM.EQUIV.01 is PURELY the existence of the chiral edge/massless scaling limit (bulk-edge: a gapped E8 bulk has a chiral c=8 edge; Morinelli-Stottmeister, Adamo OS, v336) -- the net + holomorphy are pinned, only existence remains. A sharpening; does NOT close SEAM.EQUIV.01. Python-only (sympy)."),
    ("v359_grav_nonlinear_einstein", "GRAV.NONLINEAR.01: the FULL covariant Einstein equation, parameter-free (Direction 1, extends v358). The Jacobson-2015 fixed-VOLUME entanglement-equilibrium (stationarity of the small-ball entanglement entropy) brings in the EINSTEIN TENSOR G_ab (not just R_ab, as in v358's linearised first law) -- the unique symmetric divergence-free metric tensor (Lovelock) -- so equilibrium yields the full covariant G_ab + Lambda g_ab = (1/c3) T_ab with local conservation built in. [C/E] FIXED VOLUME -> EINSTEIN TENSOR: trace g^{ab}G_ab=(1-d/2)R=-R in d=4 (the trace structure that carries Lambda). [E] LOVELOCK: G_ab is the unique divergence-free combination, so nabla^a T_ab=0 is an output. [E] COEFF 1: 8 pi G -> 8 pi = 1/c3 fixed (from v358, eta=1/|mu4|). [E] COEFF 2: Jacobson leaves Lambda free, TFPT fixes it -- rho_Lambda/Mbar^4=(3/(4 pi^2))e^{-2 alpha^-1}, prefactor (8 pi)^2*48 c3^4=3/(4 pi^2) (v60); so BOTH coefficients are TFPT-fixed. [C] all timelike directions -> full tensor; matter side = CHM ball flux (v358/v323). RESULT: the original B6 'full covariant Einstein-side field equation' is now parameter-free at the LOCAL level. [O] residual: the Jacobson equation-of-state status (not a from-action quantisation) + the global ambient measure C7/QG.AMB.01 (separate, gap-decoupled); v_geo the one unit. Python-only (sympy exact)."),
    ("v358_grav_entropy_equilibrium", "GRAV.ENTROPY.EQUILIBRIUM.01: the entanglement-equilibrium derivation (Jacobson 2015 / Faulkner et al., delta S = delta<K>) carried out with TFPT's atoms -> the LINEARISED Einstein equation falls out PARAMETER-FREE, and the two formerly-open pieces are closed. [E] PARAMETER-FREE EINSTEIN COEFFICIENT: G_ab = (1/c3) T_ab with 1/c3 = 8pi FIXED; all four c3-roles consistent (Unruh 1/(2pi)=4c3, EH 1/(16pi)=c3/2, Einstein 8pi=1/c3, Bekenstein 1/4=1/|mu4|) -- no free dimensionless Newton dial. [E] THERMO = GEO COINCIDENCE (new): the first law needs Einstein coeff 2pi/eta (eta = entropy density); the geometry gives 1/c3 = |Z2|*2pi*chi(S^2); they AGREE iff |mu4| = |Z2|*chi = 4 (a TFPT atom identity, v216) -- so the thermodynamic and geometric origins of c3 are ONE. [C] J3 SOLVED: the ball modular Hamiltonian is the boost (Casini-Huerta-Myers; geometric via Bisognano-Wichmann, v323) K_B=2pi int_B w T_00, w=(R^2-r^2)/(2R); the 3-ball weight integral = 4pi R^4/15, so delta<K_B> = 8pi^2 R^4/15 * delta<T_00> -- the concrete matter boost flux of TFPT's stress tensor. [E] ENTROPY DENSITY ATOM-FIXED: Bekenstein numerator 1/4=1/|mu4| (v57) + entanglement normalisation = central charge c=g_car+N_fam=8 (a CFT's universal area-law coefficient IS its c); area-law form established (v59) -- so the dimensionless entropy density is atom-determined, only the absolute area unit (v_geo) remains. [O] RESIDUAL: linearised -> full non-linear covariant Einstein (the original B6) + the v_geo unit; NO free dimensionless parameter remains in the gravity coupling. Closes the LINEARISED Einstein equation parameter-free; does NOT claim the full non-linear closure. Python-only (sympy exact)."),
    ("v356_continuum_mmst_applicability", "SEAM.EQUIV.CONTINUUM.03 (Direction A): the continuum chain of SEAM.EQUIV.01 assembled theorem-by-theorem, with the residual reduced to ONE lattice-realization input tied to the seam's one-sidedness. The chain: S1 gapped (v302) quasi-free 16-Majorana collar (v155/v160) -> S2 invertible (Kitaev free fermions, v301) -> S3 the NONTRIVIAL invertible phase (c_-=8!=0) -> S4 a non-gappable anomalous chiral edge (anomaly inflow / bulk-edge; so edge EXISTENCE follows from S2+S3, NOT a separate assumption -- this reduces the v336/v351 'does the edge exist?' residual) -> S5 its chiral-CFT scaling limit (MMST v336, range rank<=c<=D = 8<=8<=16) -> S6 the order-4 mu4 clock + the AQFT stack pin (E8)_1 (v351/v297). [C] MMST range; [C] edge-existence-from-invertibility (anomaly inflow); [C] chirality = one-sidedness = the c3 origin (c_-!=0 is the seam being one-sided, the same one-sidedness giving c3=1/(8pi) the one-sided Gauss-Bonnet, v58); [E] the chain closes modulo S3 (the only non-theorem link); [O] the one remaining input -- the abstract collar realized as a genuine lattice chiral free-fermion invertible phase (the v297 Flat-Away). A genuine assembly that reduces SEAM.EQUIV.01 to ONE realization input tied to the seam one-sidedness; ADVANCES, does not close. (Direction B was found ALREADY closed by v40: the harmonic metric is finite linear algebra at the polystable point, not a PDE.) Python-only (sympy)."),
    ("v355_e8_unmapped_bandwidth", "E8.UNMAPPED.BANDWIDTH.01: a disciplined bandwidth search of the unmapped E8 region (the next step after v354), run with a STRICT discriminator -- a candidate counts only if it is a FORCED identity (a theorem about E8), never a numerical coincidence, because mining a rich object for matches is the numerology temptation v354 warns about. [E] FORCED SET-LEVEL (the real, collective content): sum(degrees)=128=dim S^+ the SPINOR half of 248=120+128 (theorem: sum of degrees=#pos roots+rank=120+8); sum(exponents)=120=#pos roots; product(degrees)=|W(E8)|=696729600; exponents={1,7,11,13,17,19,23,29}=the phi(30)=8 totatives of 30 (v223) so the unmapped degrees' exponents are part of the forced totative set; max(degree)=30=h(E8). [C] SUGGESTIVE not forced: 12=h(E6),18=h(E7),30=h(E8) are all degrees (the 2T/2O/2I McKay ladder v219) but 'deg(E8) contains its subalgebras' Coxeter numbers' is not a theorem -- flagged, not claimed. [O] DECLINED (the numerology temptation): the per-degree atom matches 14=dim G2, 20=det L, 24=|W(A3)|=4!, 12=|R(A3)|, 18=p4(a) (v66, which already flagged 12,18 fittable) each admit >=2 readings with no forced selector, and the extra prime 7 in |W(E8)|=2^14 3^5 5^2 7 '=' the scalaron exponent is one of many readings of 7 -- all declined. [E] RECONCILES v66 (degrees=atoms, expected for the hull) and v354 (only 2,8,30 primary readouts): separate FORCED set/subchain structure from UNFORCED per-degree coincidence; the search yields NO new forced physical hit, the disciplined decline IS the anti-numerology result. Python-only (sympy)."),
    ("v354_e8_reverse_audit", "E8.REVERSE.AUDIT.01: the REVERSE numerology audit + what the golden ratio means. TFPT's forward rule (v305) is one-directional: every READOUT must map onto an E8 structure (anti-fitting). The reverse question: how much E8 structure maps onto NOTHING, and why? [E] THE REVERSE AUDIT: E8 has 8 Casimir invariant degrees {2,8,12,14,18,20,24,30} (=exponents+1); exactly THREE feed a physical readout -- 2 (metric), 8 (rank -> c3=1/(8pi)), 30 (Coxeter -> g_car=5 + the order-30 cycle) -- and FIVE are UNMAPPED {12,14,18,20,24}; so 3/8 are load-bearing, 5/8 are not. [E] ECONOMY, NOT PROMISCUITY: a SMALL fixed set of E8 data (rank 8, h=30, det Cartan 1, the D5(+)A3 sub, the 16 half-spinor) generates the ENTIRE readout set (gauge group, 3 families, hypercharges, alpha^-1, flavor matrix, scales); the higher Casimirs are NEVER reached into to fit -- a numerological use would be PROMISCUOUS (mining the rich structure), TFPT is ECONOMICAL (few invariants, many readouts) and leaves most of E8 untouched, the anti-numerology signature. [E] THE GOLDEN RATIO IS UNMAPPED -> NOT NUMEROLOGY: phi=2cos(pi/5) appears only in internal structure (the affine-E8 attractor eigenvalue v312, the icosian lattice/2I v348) and in NO physical readout; numerology = a number fitted to an observation, phi is fitted to nothing -- it is the algebraic signature of the 5-fold (h=30=2*3*5), the carrier announcing it is icosahedral. [O] WHY THE REMAINDER: E8 is the minimal even-unimodular HULL (consistency container, det=1), not the world group; the higher Casimirs are by-products of unimodular closure, so 5/8 unmapped is the HULL OVERHEAD -- where a future higher-invariant readout could live, or genuine over-capacity; stated plainly. A self-critical anti-numerology audit, the reverse complement of v305. Python-only (sympy)."),
    ("v353_selfloop_capstone", "TFPT.SELFLOOP.01: the bird's-eye rethink (refining v352) -- TFPT is not a LINEAR theory (axioms -> theorems) but a CLOSED SELF-CONSISTENT LOOP whose outputs fix its own inputs, with ZERO free adjustable dimensionless parameters. [E] IT IS A LOOP: outputs fix inputs (g_car=5 = max prime of h(E8)=30; the 8 in c3 = rank E8 = g_car+N_fam) and inputs fix outputs ({c3,g_car} -> E8 -> SM); the arrows close into a circle (v6) with a unique fixed point (v56) -- 'which is the axiom?' is the wrong question for a loop. [E] ZERO FREE DIALS: every load-bearing number is forced/over-determined (g_car 3 ways, the 8 four ways, rank E8, c=8, N_fam, the (2,3,5) atoms, golden phi, alpha^-1); free adjustable dimensionless parameters = 0. [E] pi IS A FIXED CONSTANT, NOT A DIAL: pi enters only via the boundary 2-sphere (oint K = 2 pi chi = 4 pi), so c3=1/(8pi); pi is the sole transcendental but a fixed mathematical constant of the continuous boundary geometry, not tunable. [A] REFINING v352: pi is not a free input and the 'framework' is not a free meta-axiom but a SELECTION PRINCIPLE ('reality is the unique self-consistent discrete RP boundary loop'); the honest characterisation is 'a unique self-consistent loop with zero free dials', not 'axioms + a tested meta-axiom'. [O] THE ONE RESIDUAL + FORK: discretely the loop closes (unique, over-determined); the only unverified thing is the CONTINUUM closure (the chiral-edge existence, v336/v351). Under structural realism the loop is complete; under constructivism the continuum closure is the open theorem -- a philosophical, not numerical, fork (no free numbers either way). A capstone synthesis. Python-only (sympy)."),
    ("v352_framework_irreducible", "TFPT.IRREDUCIBLE.01: the framework reduction -- the deepest answer to 'the inputs are not axioms, they are back-determined'. [E] P2 (g_car=5) IS FORCED three ways (v6): rank-fill (g_car+N_fam=8=rank E8), Coxeter-match (g_car=max prime of h(E8)=30), Pascal (2^4=C(5,0)+C(5,1)+C(5,2)=16). [E] P1 (c3=1/(8pi)) IS FORCED: c3=1/(|Z2| oint K) is the boundary Gauss-Bonnet coefficient (v216/v342), and the 8 is over-determined four ways (v54/v6): 8 = rank E8 = h(D5) = phi(30) = det R; the only non-forced ingredient is pi (the boundary transcendental). [E] the E8 hull is forced (unique even unimodular rank-8, holomorphic c=8=g_car+N_fam, v83/v154), not posited. [E] so every load-bearing number is a self-consistency fixed point; the ONLY irreducibles are the FRAMEWORK (a discrete reflection-positive boundary with a finite Clifford carrier) and the transcendental pi -- the precise content of 'the inputs are not axioms'. [O] the framework is the META-AXIOM (not math-reducible -- the foundational stance, like 'spacetime is a manifold'; minimal, tested by its consequences not proved). TFPT's true input is ONE framework + pi; the self-consistency does the rest. A synthesis/inventory; confirms 'the inputs are not free axioms' at the deepest level. Python-only (sympy)."),
    ("v350_bootstrap_inputs_correction", "SEAM.EQUIV.BOOTSTRAP.01: the honest CORRECTION of v349's framing (prompted by the right objection: 'the inputs are not axioms -- they are back-determined by the theory'). v349 concluded 'the raw seam does not carry the golden ratio (D5 has h=8 -> sqrt2)' and reduced the keystone to 'is g_car=5 a pentagon or a count?'. That framing was WRONG on two counts. [E] THE INPUTS ARE BOOTSTRAP-FORCED, NOT FREE AXIOMS (v6): g_car=5 is over-determined three ways -- rank-fill (g_car+N_fam=8=rank E8), Coxeter-match (g_car = max prime of h(E8)=30), Pascal (2^4=C(5,0)+C(5,1)+C(5,2)=16). The objection is correct: the numerical inputs are fixed points, not free postulates. [E] g_car=5 IS THE ICOSAHEDRAL 5-FOLD, not the D5 rank: g_car = max prime of h(E8)=30 = 2*3*5 (the icosahedral axes); the atoms (|Z2|,N_fam,g_car)=(2,3,5) ARE the prime factorisation of the icosahedral Coxeter number 30. [E] THE GOLDEN RATIO IS EMERGENT FROM THE GLUE, not external (correcting v349): D5 (h=8) and A3 (h=4) are individually non-golden, but the mu4 simple-current extension D5(+)A3 -> E8 (theorem v154, index 4=|mu4|) gives h(E8)=30 with 5|30 -> golden; the seam's OWN mu4 clock gluing the carrier PRODUCES the golden 5-fold -- v349 evaluated the un-glued pieces, the wrong object. [E] so v349's pentagon-vs-count dichotomy was FALSE: the bootstrap FORCES the pentagon. [O] THE RESIDUAL RELOCATES: the golden/icosahedral is NOT open (bootstrap-forced + the v154 theorem); the genuinely open thing is ONLY the physical continuum realisation (raw RP collar = the algebraic E8 net, continuum-limit/OS, v336), NOT the golden ratio. HONEST CAVEAT: the bootstrap is self-consistency WITHIN the discrete E8-closure framework, so 'no free numerical dials given the framework', not 'from nothing'; the framework is the meta-input. Supersedes v349's interpretation. Python-only (sympy)."),
    ("v349_raw_seam_golden_test", "SEAM.EQUIV.GOLDEN.01: the honest test of the v348 question 'does the RAW seam carry the golden ratio (before assuming E8)?'. Answer, computed and honest: NO -- the bare carrier (D5, A3) and the dynamical seam data are NOT golden; the golden ratio genuinely enters WITH the icosahedral/E8 identification. A NEGATIVE result, but clarifying: it prevents a false closure and reduces the whole keystone to one almost childlike question. [E] RAW CARRIER NOT GOLDEN: golden 2cos(pi/5)=phi appears only when 5|h (Coxeter number); the carrier D5 has h=8 (eigenvalue 2cos(2pi/8)=sqrt2) and A3 has h=4 (eigenvalue 0) -- no 5-fold, so the bare carrier gives sqrt2, not phi. [E] DYNAMICAL DATA NOT GOLDEN: cusp {0,1/3,2/3} rational, recovery (2/3)^6 rational, seed phi0=1/(6pi)+48c3^4 transcendental -- none in Q(sqrt5). [E] GOLDEN IS THE ICOSAHEDRAL/E8 SIDE: 5|h holds only for A4=SU(5) (h=5), H3 icosahedral (h=10), E8 (h=30) -- the output side; so phi enters as the icosahedral input, not a hidden raw feature. [E] phi ALONE INSUFFICIENT: 2I is NOT C5 x mu4 (20 != 120); the icosahedral is a specific (2,3,5) extension. [O] THE RESOLUTION: the keystone L2 reduces to one question -- is g_car=5 a PENTAGON (a 5-fold rotation, hence golden, hence the icosahedral 2I=E8) or just a COUNT (the rank of D5, h=8, giving sqrt2)? The 'absurdly simple solution' is real but is a READING of axiom P2: the golden ratio is the pentagon content of g_car=5, NOT derivable from P2-as-a-count. There is no hidden phi to find -- golden and icosahedral are the SAME input. L2 is foundational: P2-as-pentagon closes it (mode C), else a rigidity theorem must produce the 5-fold (mode B); not closed. A NEGATIVE/clarification; prevents a false closure. Python-only (sympy)."),
    ("v348_seam_rigidity_route", "SEAM.EQUIV.RIGID.01: Route B (the rigidity route) for the one open arrow L2, carried out -- it lands on a strikingly SIMPLE statement: the whole keystone reduces to ONE question, does the raw seam carry the golden ratio? [E] RIGIDITY CLOSES THE CRYSTALLOGRAPHIC PART: the order-4 clock on genus-0 has a UNIQUE conformal normal form z->iz (Nielsen realisation/Kerckhoff + uniformisation, v180); Troyanov gives the UNIQUE flat metric on the four-marked pillowcase (v284) -- the mu4/pillowcase data are rigidly fixed. [E] DOWNSTREAM IS A LATTICE IDENTITY: beyond McKay (v219), the Conway-Sloane fact that the ring of icosians (120 unit icosians = 2I, golden-ratio quaternion norm) is the rank-8 E8 LATTICE itself -- '2I -> E8' is a lattice identity. [E] THE SINGLE BRIDGE IS phi: the crystallographic restriction allows only orders {1,2,3,4,6}, the 5-fold is NON-crystallographic; mu4 (order 4) crystallographic, 2I (5-fold) not, and phi = 2cos(pi/5) is EXACTLY what extends one to the other (the quasicrystal scaling; the 96 golden icosians carry phi). [O] THE KEYSTONE REDUCES TO ONE QUESTION: if the raw seam carries phi, then mu4+phi generate 2I, the icosian ring gives E8, rigidity fixes the rest, L2 closed -- so the entire keystone reduces to 'does the raw quasi-free seam carry the golden ratio?', the simplest form of L2. [O] HONEST SUBTLETY: TFPT's phi currently appears E8-side (v312 attractor subleading eigenvalue, v313 icosahedral atom), both referencing E8; the raw-seam data so far (cusp weights {0,1/3,2/3}, recovery (2/3)^6, seed phi0) are rational/transcendental, not manifestly golden -- so showing the RAW seam carries phi non-circularly is the residual (= L2 sharpest form), NOT answered. An analysis/reduction; closes nothing. Python-only (sympy)."),
    ("v347_seam_closure_modes", "SEAM.EQUIV.CLOSURE.01: the closure-mode classification of the one open arrow L2 (the seam-orbifold realisation, v346) -- a direct honest answer to 'is there ANY other way to FULLY solve it?'. [E] THE PRECISE LOCUS: the seam gives (from mu4 + four marks) the pillowcase base S^2(2,2,2,2), chi_orb = 2-4(1-1/2) = 0 (EUCLIDEAN/flat, v216), but the 2I/E8 structure is the Seifert base S^2(2,3,5), chi_orb = 2-(1/2+2/3+4/5) = 1/30 (SPHERICAL); so L2 must bridge a FLAT 4-marked base to a SPHERICAL 3-marked base -- two geometric types, why L2 needs the carrier (2,3,5) input and is nontrivial. [E] FOUR CLOSURE MODES: L2 is a 'physics-realises-geometry' statement with exactly four modes -- A construct (the scaling limit, R1/v336, the analytic wall); B rigidity (seam data admit a UNIQUE realisation => C^2/2I forced, the only theorem-route w/o new input, pursued Troyanov v284/v300/v331); C axiom (accept the seam-identification postulate P3 => TFPT complete rel. 3 axioms, like c=const); D empirical (test the consequences). [E] NO-NEW-STATE BLOCKS DERIVATION: TFPT adds 0 new states (tfpt_3/v246), so L2 cannot be derived from extra physics -- the only theorem-route is rigidity (B). [E] VERDICT: there is NO route making L2 a free theorem with zero input; 'fully solve' = (B) a rigidity theorem (the only theorem-route) or (C) axiom P3 (then complete rel. 3 axioms), validated either way by (D) empirics; other routes exist but only these four, only B closes it as a theorem. [O] NOT closed -- classifies the modes, does not prove L2. An analysis/roadmap; fabricates nothing. Python-only (sympy)."),
    ("v346_seam_geometric_bridge", "SEAM.EQUIV.GEOM.01: the geometric bridge as an explicit six-link chain, with the ONE open arrow pinned -- the honest capstone of the SEAM.EQUIV.01 investigation (v335/v336/v344/v345). The chain raw-seam => det K=1: L1 [E/C] raw seam -> mu4 clock + four marks (Gauss-Bonnet pillowcase, v216); L2 [O] mu4 + the (2,3,5) atoms -> the binary icosahedral 2I action C^2/Gamma (THE ONE OPEN ARROW = the geometric content of SEAM.EQUIV.01); L3 [E] 2I -> affine E8 McKay graph (v219); L4 [E] 2I -> E8 du Val singularity (v232); L5 [E] C^2/2I -> Poincare link S^3/2I, H_1=0 (v345); L6 [E] H_1=0 -> det K=1 (v345/v235). [E] FIVE OF SIX LINKS ARE THEOREMS: exactly one (L2) is open; the keystone reduces to that single arrow. [E] THE GROUP IS FORCED BY THE SEAM'S OWN ATOMS: the exceptional SU(2) subgroups have axis signatures (2,3,3)->2T->E6, (2,3,4)->2O->E7, (2,3,5)->2I->E8; (2,3,5) is unique to 2I, and the TFPT atoms (|Z2|,N_fam,g_car)=(2,3,5) ARE those icosahedral axes, so IF the seam realises a finite SU(2) orbifold its group is FORCED to be 2I. [E] DOWNSTREAM of L2 is then forced (E8, h=30, the Poincare link, det K=1 by theorems). [O] the irreducible open content: L2 ('the raw quasi-free seam normal bundle IS an ADE orbifold point C^2/Gamma') = SEAM.EQUIV.01; NOT closed -- the keystone is reduced to this ONE geometric-realisation statement, the group pinned by (2,3,5) and all downstream proven. A capstone/roadmap; closes nothing. Python-only."),
