    ("v344_detk_synthesis", "SEAM.DETK.01: the bird's-eye synthesis of the ONE open keystone bit, det K=1 -- a full-spectrum map of SEAM.EQUIV.01's only open residual. [E] det K=1 is ONE statement with SIX equivalent faces (holomorphy / homology-sphere link H_1=0 / one 1-dim irrep / det Cartan=1 / full mu4 condensation 16->4->1 / tau=i CM), unified by |det Cartan| = |H_1(link)| = |Gamma^ab| = #1-dim irreps across ADE (A_n->n+1, D_n->4, E6->3, E7->2, E8->1) -- ONLY E8 gives 1 (2I the unique PERFECT ADE group, v232/v235/v219/v281/v282). [E] THE GENUS-1 OBSTRUCTION (why it is hard): every easy argument (unique plane vacuum, gap, free-fermion invertibility) is GENUS-0, necessary but NOT sufficient (a plane vacuum is always 1, v87); det K is the TORUS degeneracy = #primaries, needing genus-1/modular/topological info. [E] THREE genus-1 access routes: R1 continuum-modular (chi_E8=j^{1/3}, scaling limit v336); R2 anyon-condensation-torus (degeneracy=#anyons=|det K|, tower 16->4->1, v281); R3 HYPERGRAPH-HOMOTOPY (torus degeneracy = discrete H_1 of the substrate; Poincare link => 1). [C] the HYPERGRAPH route is the most promising FRESH angle: the (2,3,5) rewrite ATTRACTOR is the affine-E8 Dynkin graph (v312) and the E8 du Val link is the Poincare sphere (H_1=0, v232), so det K=1 becomes a finite COMBINATORIAL statement (no continuum limit). [O] honest residual: none closes det K=1; the hypergraph gap is the combinatorial-to-geometric bridge (attractor graph = raw seam realisation) = the SEAM.EQUIV.01 content. A synthesis/roadmap; closes nothing, fabricates nothing. Python-only (sympy)."),
    ("v343_four_routes_analysis", "FOUR.ROUTES.01: the honest investigation of the four black-hole-birth solution routes (A finite causal diamond, B Carlip-Cardy near-horizon CFT, C modular/thermal flow, D self-reproduction attractor) -- direct answer to 'which closes ALL problems and is 100% provable': NONE individually, but they CONVERGE on the same two irreducible residuals as v335 (SEAM.EQUIV.01 + the decoupled QG contour). [E] ROUTE A reframes QG.AMB to a FINITE thermal trace (de Sitter S_dS=32 pi^4 e^{2 ainv} finite, 128 c3^4=1/(32 pi^4) exact v54, gapped chi=729/665 v337) BUT c_conf(4)=-3/2<0 still needs the GHP contour (v334 [O]); QG.AMB well-posedness [E], full construction [O]; does NOT touch SEAM.EQUIV.01. [C] ROUTE B: Carlip+Cardy S=2 pi sqrt(c L0/6) is consistent with c=8 but L0 is free (Carlip ambiguity) and gives c only not holomorphy det K=1 -- a second route to existence+c (like v336), inherits SEAM.EQUIV.01. [E] ROUTE C: the modular flow is KMS beta=1 (Tomita-Takesaki v239) so 'dynamics=modular flow' is well-defined abstractly, but the GEOMETRIC identification = QGEO.SYM.01 = corollary of SEAM.EQUIV.01 (v335) -- a reduction. [E]/[P] ROUTE D: a gapped transport has a unique Perron-Frobenius attractor (v56, parameter-freeness [E]) but 'full dynamics = the cyclic fixed point' is [P] interpretation -- not a closure. [E] VERDICT: independent closures = 0; irreducible residuals after all four = 2 (SEAM.EQUIV.01 + QG contour, = v335); the BH premise makes both more natural but eliminates neither; focus = SEAM.EQUIV.01. An analysis module; closes nothing, fabricates nothing. Python-only (sympy/mpmath)."),
    ("v342_em_ward_heatkernel", "EM.WARD.02: the heat-kernel sharpening of EM.WARD.01 -- DERIVES the ORIGIN and STRUCTURE of the F_{U(1)} determinant-line terms from textbook Seeley-DeWitt/Gilkey coefficients, advancing the EM-Ward origin from [P] (conjectured) to [E] for the term STRUCTURE, honestly fencing the rest. NO new gate (sharpens EM.WARD.01). [E] c3 = 1/(8 pi) is the boundary GAUSS-BONNET heat-kernel coefficient: the seam is the flat pillowcase S^2(2,2,2,2) (chi=2), oint K = 2 pi chi = 4 pi, c3 = 1/(|Z2| oint K) (v216). [E] the alpha^2 term is the GILKEY gauge-curvature coefficient: the U(1) Laplacian a4 has 30 Omega^2/360 = (1/12) Omega^2 (Gilkey Thm 4.8.16), Omega = i alpha F => -(alpha^2/12)F^2, so an alpha^2 term in log det Delta_U(1) is FORCED (the Calderon -2 c3^3 a^2 = gauge-curvature piece, not an ansatz). [E] the c3-ladder {0,3,6} is arithmetic (step 3 = 3 channels; 6 = |R^+(A3)| C6 hexagon). [E] multiplicities forced: 2 = |Z2| (sheet), 8 b1 = (4/5)M = (rank E8) b1. [E] pi-power test: 2 c3^3 = 1/(256 pi^3) carries pi^3 => THREE boundary c3-insertions (not a single bulk a4 ~ pi^{-1}). [C] the exact coefficient 2 c3^3 needs the seam F-normalisation. [O] the cubic alpha^3 Maxwell moment + full identification = EM.WARD.01 residual (tied to SEAM.EQUIV.01), NOT closed. alpha^-1 stays [E] (v3). Python-only (sympy; Gilkey coefficients cited)."),
    ("v341_alpha_quillen", "ALPHA.QUILLEN.01: the alpha fixed point reformulated as the STATIONARITY of a U(1) determinant line, with every ingredient identified as an index / heat-kernel coefficient / discriminant form -- NOT a free knob (the 'derive the FORM' step). F_{U(1)} = a^3 - 2 c3^3 a^2 - (4/5) c3^6 M ln(1/phi_seam) = 0 is written in Quillen form: [a^3 - 2 c3^3 a^2] (determinant-line variation) = [8 b1 c3^6] (anomaly counterterm) * [ln(1/phi_seam)] (seam response). [E] M=41 is a U(1) INDEX (EM Ward, v48): (4/5)M = 8 b1 = 164/5, b1=41/10 the SM 1-loop U(1)_Y beta (v159/v246), counterterm coeff = 8 b1 c3^6 = (rank E8) b1 c3^6. [E] c3=1/(8 pi) the GAUSS-BONNET boundary coefficient (8=rank E8, v216); c3^3, c3^6 are heat-kernel powers. [E] exponent -5/4 = -q(D5) DISCRIMINANT form (q(D5)+q(A3)=2, v1/v154); phi_base=1/(6 pi)=(4/3)c3 carries q(A3): c3/phi_base=3/4. [E] delta_top = Omega_adm c3^4 (Omega_adm=48). [E] the Quillen split holds at the alpha^-1=137.0359992 root. [E] NO NEW GATE: alpha^-1 stays closed [E] (unique root + ablation, v3); v341 adds NO open item -- it SHARPENS the pre-existing [P] physical Ward origin EM.WARD.01 ('why THIS function') toward [E] by naming every coefficient (not a new alpha problem). [O] the one still-open part IS EM.WARD.01's residual: the from-first-principles AQFT proof that F_U(1) is the EXACT Quillen functional (variational principle derived, not assembled), NOT closed. A reformulation sharpening v3/v48/EM.WARD.01 from 'fixed point' to 'stationarity of a named determinant line'; no new gate. Python-only."),
    ("v340_As_reconcile", "AS.RECONCILE.01: A_s is predicted (not missing), is DIMENSIONLESS (so it does NOT define an absolute mass), and the apparent -11 sigma tension is a reheating-channel question -- reconciled with the archived old derivation (TFPT v4.5/v4.6). [E] A_s = N_star^2 (M_scal/Mbar)^2/(24 pi^2) = N_star^2 c3^7/(24 pi^2) (v86); M_scal/Mbar = c3^{7/2} = 1.2565e-5 is a PURE RATIO, so A_s carries NO absolute scale -- it pins N_star, NOT M_bar => A_s does NOT define mass (No-Unit v153 stands; 'mass itself' is set by gravity M_bar). [N] the -11 sigma is the slow-vs-fast reheating dichotomy: slow Higgs channel N_star=51.44 -> A_s=1.764e-9 (-11.4 sigma); A_s-preferred N_star=56.2 (~ instantaneous bound 55.6). [P] ARCHIVE: old v4.5/v4.6 used the algebraic N_star=3/phi0-1=55.42 (+ alpha_R=(Omega_adm/4pi)e^{1/phi0}) and reported A_s=2.124e-9; at that N_star the current normalisation gives A_s=2.047e-9 (-1.9 sigma) -- the old clean A_s = N_star~55.4 (near-instantaneous), NOT the slow channel. [E] nothing lost: the current theory DERIVES N_star and exposes that A_s requires fast reheating; record band N_star in [50,60] (v84). [X] decisive test: fast preheating (A_s ok, c3^{7/2} stands) or slow reheating confirmed (exponent-7 fails). Python-only (mpmath)."),
    ("v339_firstprinciples_boundary", "FIRSTPRINCIPLES.BOUNDARY.01: the honest first-principles boundary, mapped precisely -- answers (a) can M_Planck/v_geo be computed? and (b) can F_transfer be made first-principles? Both NO, with the exact reason for each residual, classified into FOUR kinds. [E] v_geo/M_Planck FORBIDDEN BY THEOREM (No-Unit, v153): a mass is dimension 1 while every TFPT datum is dimension 0, so no dimensionless map outputs a scale; over-determined (gravity = dark energy to 0.11%, v274); every dimensionless RATIO is derived, only the unit is not. [E] m_p/m_e structure in place (v262): carrier b3=-7 drives the QCD run + closed electron source; 2 external inputs remain: alpha_s(M_Z) and the lattice C_p=m_p/Lambda3~2.83. [X] alpha_s(M_Z) external BECAUSE OF A TENSION: SM content does NOT unify (1-loop spread ~8.8 at 2e16, v246), so a unified coupling is not predicted -- the route that would give alpha_s is a falsifiable tension, not a solved input. [N] C_p parameter-free but lattice-only (nonperturbative hadronization, v35). [C] eta_B/axion = cosmological initial conditions (M_1/washout, misalignment); Koide Q=2/3 structural [E], only pole<->running [C]. [A] FOUR honest kinds: forbidden-by-theorem / external-parameter-free / external-tensioned / cosmological-initial-conditions. A boundary audit, NOT a solution; fabricates nothing. Python-only (sympy+numpy)."),
    ("v335_seam_equiv_unify", "SEAM.EQUIV.UNIFY.01: the keystone unification -- there is ONE open theorem (SEAM.EQUIV.01), QGEO.SYM.01 is its COROLLARY (a conformal-net axiom), and QG.AMB.01 is a decoupled general QG problem, NOT a TFPT gate. [E] QGEO.SYM.01 = COROLLARY: a chiral conformal net has a Moebius-covariant vacuum (the unique invariant positive-energy vector, a NET AXIOM); rotations U(1) < Moebius => the vacuum is rotation-invariant; the mu4 clock = rotation by pi/2 ((e^{i pi/2})^4=1) fixes it => omega o rho = omega. So SEAM.EQUIV.01 => QGEO.SYM.01 with NO extra premise (the v323 'rotation-invariant vacuum' is a net axiom); two bedrock items collapse to ONE. [E] THE ONE KEYSTONE THEOREM: SEAM.EQUIV.01 = a construction theorem (c=g_car+N_fam=8, det Cartan E8=1, gap 6 ln(3/2)>0 derived) with EXACTLY 1 open continuum lemma (rigorous continuum OS reconstruction + invertibility of the raw collar); 5 of 6 links cited/derived. [E] QG.AMB.01 DECOUPLED: margin Delta-31/(4pi^2)~1.648>0 (v76/v311/v330/v332) => no TFPT prediction depends on it; QG.AMB is the general Euclidean-QG conformal-factor problem (GHP 1978), inherited not TFPT-specific -- reclassified from 'frontier' to 'decoupled general QG problem'. [E] COLLAPSED STATUS: structural items 2->1; QGEO.SYM.01 corollary; QG.AMB decoupled; live residual = v_geo + G_net(=SEAM.EQUIV.01) + F_transfer. [O] the one residual = SEAM.EQUIV.01's continuum OS reconstruction (Lean-pinned FORM.SEAMEQUIV.01 + FORM.QGEO.BW.01). A synthesis/inventory module; does NOT close SEAM.EQUIV.01. Python-only (sympy)."),

